<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1000> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: ROUX-EN-Y GASTRIC BYPASS (RYGB) IS THE MOST PERFORMED SURGICAL TECHNIQUE TO TREAT SEVERE OBESITY, HOWEVER THE NUMBER OF SLEEVE GASTRECTOMIES PERFORMED IN THE LAST YEARS HAS INCREASED. UPPER GASTROINTESTINAL ENDOSCOPY IS FREQUENTLY USED IN THE POSTOPERATIVE PERIOD TO EVALUATE, TO DIAGNOSE AND TO TREAT COMPLICATIONS, AS WELL AS TO IDENTIFY FACTORS THAT COULD BE ASSOCIATED WITH INSUFFICIENT WEIGHT LOSS. AIM: TO EVALUATE WHETHER GASTROJEJUNAL ANASTOMOSIS SIZE AND GASTRIC POUCH DIMENSIO"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "EVOLUÇÃO ENDOSCÓPICA E CORRELAÇÃO COM PERDA DE PESO DAS DIMENSÕES GÁSTRICAS E DIÂMETRO DA ANASTOMOSE GASTROJEJUNAL APÓS DERIVAÇÃO GÁSTRICA EM Y DE ROUX:ESTUDO DE COORTE PROSPECTIVO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/CINTHIA_BARBOSA_DE_ANDRADE> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1001> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BACKGROUND: NOWADAYS, ROUX-EN-Y GASTRIC BYPASS AND SLEEVE GASTRECTOMY ARE THE TWO MOST PERFORMED BARIATRIC SURGERIES, WITH PROVEN SAFETY AND EFFICACY. HOWEVER, COMPLICATIONS, SUCH AS GASTRIC FISTULA, CAN OCCUR, GREATLY INCREASING MORBIMORTALITY. OBJECTIVE: TO ANALYZE THE HEALING TIME AND THE OUTCOMES OF PATIENTS WITH GASTRIC FISTULA AFTER SLEEVE GASTRECTOMY (SG) AND AFTER ROUX-EN-Y GASTRIC BYPASS (RYGB) WHO WERE SUBMITTED TO ENDOSCOPIC TREATMENT. METHODS: THIS IS A RETROSPECTIVE, OBSERVATIONAL, "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "08FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "FÍSTULA GÁSTRICA APÓS GASTRECTOMIA VERTICAL E DERIVAÇÃO GÁSTRICA EM Y DE ROUX: ANÁLISE DE UMA NOVA ABORDAGEM ENDOSCÓPICO-CIRÚRGICA PRECOCE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/HELGA_CRISTINA_ALMEIDA_WAHNON_ALHINHO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1002> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: COLORECTAL CANCER (CRC) HAS AN ANNUAL INCIDENCE OF 1,400,000 CASES REPRESENTING ABOUT 9.7% OF ALL CANCER INCIDENTS WORLDWIDE. CCR IS THIRD MOST COMMON CANCER AND FOURTH LEADING CAUSE OF CANCER-RELATED DEATH IN THE WORLD, WITH 750,000 DEATHS EACH YEAR. IN BRAZIL, IT IS ESTIMATED 34,280 NEW CASES FOR 2016, AND IT IS THE SECOND TYPE OF CANCER IN WOMEN AND THIRD INCIDENT IN MEN. TUMOR BIOMARKERS CAN BE USED TO EVALUATE THE PATIENT IN A VARIETY OF SETTINGS, INCLUDING SCREENING, DIAGNOSI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INVESTIGAÇÃO DE POTENCIAIS BIOMARCADORES PROTEÔMICOS EM CÂNCER COLORRETAL RECIFE,"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/CAMILA_ROCHA_DA_CRUZ> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1003> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: PHYSICAL ACTIVITY ENHANCES QUALITY OF LIFE AND BODY IMAGE IN OBESE. BEHAVIOURAL CHANGES ARE USEFUL TOOLS TO INCREASE LIFE CONDITIONS OF THIS POPULATION. AIM: THIS STUDY AIMED TO EVALUATE THE PHYSICAL ACTIVITY LEVEL OF CANDIDATES TO BARIATRIC SURGERY AND ITS RELATION WITH QUALITY OF LIFE AND BODY IMAGE, WHEN PATIENTS ARE ENCOURAGED WEEKLY BY PERSONAL TRAINERS. METHOD: THIS IS A PROSPECTIVE, INTERVENTIONAL AND LONGITUDINAL STUDY WITH QUANTITATIVE ANALYSIS. PATIENTS WERE DIVIDED INTO "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "NÍVEL DE ATIVIDADE FÍSICA, IMAGEM CORPORAL E QUALIDADE DE VIDA DE PACIENTES CANDIDATOS A CIRURGIA BARIÁTRICA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
