    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: ADVERSE EVENTS THAT MAY OCCUR DURING OPERATIONS ON THE BILE DUCTS IN HUMANS, WHETHER BY THE OPEN OR LAPAROSCOPIC APPROACH, CONSTITUTE A CHALLENGE TO THERAPY EVEN IN REFERRAL CENTERS FOR LIVER SURGERY. AS BILIO-DIGESTIVE BYPASS SURGERY, USUALLY CARRIED OUT TO RESOLVE THESE CASES, DOES NOT ALWAYS PRODUCE SATISFACTORY RESULTS, THE REPAIR OF EXTRAHEPATIC BILE DUCT LESIONS USING SUGARCANE BIOPOLYMER MEMBRANE HAS ARISEN AS A PROMISING LOW-COST ALTERNATIVE TREATMENT. ALTHOUGH A NUMBER OF "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "03MAR2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "SUBSTITUIÇÃO TECIDUAL PARCIAL DO COLÉDOCO DE SUÍNOS COM REMENDO (PATCH) DE BIOPOLÍMERO DE CANA-DE-AÇÚCAR"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
