<http://example.com/capes#thesis/10195> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: THE INCREASED SURVIVAL BEFORE BREAST CANCER HAS PRODUCED QUESTIONS ABOUT THE PERCEPTION OF WOMEN REGARDING THEIR BODY IMAGE EVEN YEARS AFTER THE DIAGNOSIS. THERE IS EVIDENCE THAT WOMEN EXPERIENCE BODY IMAGE DISTURBANCES, AND THESE MAY BE RELATED TO THE LIFE SITUATION AFTER TREATMENT, I.E., THE INFLUENCE OF DEMOGRAPHIC VARIABLES, SUCH AS AGE, MARITAL STATUS, FAMILY INCOME, OCCUPATIONAL EXPOSURE AND SCHOOLING LEVEL, ON THE PERCEPTION OF BODY IMAGE. THE BODY IMAGE AFTER BREAST CANCER "@pt ;
