<http://example.com/capes#thesis/10204> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COPING WITH LIVING WITH HIV IS STILL QUITE CHALLENGING TO DIAGNOSED PEOPLE, BOTH BY THE DISEASE ITSELF AND BECAUSE SOCIETY'S JUDGMENT IN GENERAL, CONSIDERING THAT IT IS A DISEASE PERMEATED BY SOCIAL REPRESENTATIONS RELATED TO STIGMAS AND STEREOTYPES INHERENT TO THE INFECTION. THIS STUDY AIMED TO ANALYSE THE PROCESS OF COPING WITH LIVING WITH HIV AMONGST SEROPOSITIVE ADULTS FROM THEIR SOCIAL REPRESENTATIONS TOWARDS HIV. CONSIDERING THE NATURE OF THE RESEARCH OBJECT, IT WAS DECIDED TO CONDUCT AN E"@pt ;
