<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1025> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE TEMPOROMANDIBULAR DISORDER (TMD) REPRESENT A CHALLENGE IN DIAGNOSIS AND THERAPEUTICS FOR DENTISTS. FREQUENTLY, INDIVIDUALS WHO HAVE TMD SHOW A DISTURBING COMBINATION OF CLINICAL AND PSYCHOLOGICAL SIGNS. DUE TO THESE POTENTIALLY COMPLEX CIRCUMSTANCE, IT IS INTERESTING FOR THE SCIENTIFIC COMMUNITY THE USE OF PREDICTIVE STATISTICAL APPROACHES THAT EASE THE PROCESS OF RECOGNITION AND/OR PREDICTION OF TMD OCCURRENCE, SO THAT THE PATIENTS CAN DIRECTED TO THE MOST SUITABLE TREATMENT FOR EACH CASE. "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAÇÃO DE MUTAGENICIDADE DO GEL DE CLAREAMENTO DENTAL EM LINFÓCITOS HUMANOS \" DA CD. CLEUDES HERCILA DO NASCIMENTO LIMA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/CLEUDES_HERCILA_DO_NASCIMENTO_LIMA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ODONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1026> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PENTRAXIN 3 (PTX3) IS A PROTEIN WITH IMPORTANT ROLE IN IMMUNE AND INFLAMMATORY PROCESSES ACTING ON MICRORGANISMS FAGOCYTOSIS, MODULLATION OF CYTOKINE EXPRESSION AND ACTIVATION OF COMPLEMENT SYSTEM. THUS, THIS STUDY AIMED TO EVALUATE TWO PTX3'S POLYMORPHISMS (RS1840680 AND RS2305619) IN PATIENTS WITH RHEUMATOID ARTHRITIS (RA) AND SJOGREN'S SYNDROME (SS). IT WAS A CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY AND 266 PATIENTS WERE ALLOCATED IN 3 DISTINCT GROUPS: AR - N=117, AR/SS - N=25 AND C - N=124. XEROSTOMIA, XEROPHT"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21AUG2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAÇÃO DE POLIMORFISMOS GÊNICOS DA PENTRAXINA 3 EM INDIVÍDUOS COM ARTRITE REUMATÓIDE E SÍNDROME DE SJOGREN"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/RUI_MEDEIROS_JUNIOR> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ODONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1027> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE TEMPOROMANDIBULAR DISORDER (TMD) REPRESENT A CHALLENGE IN DIAGNOSIS AND THERAPEUTICS FOR DENTISTS. FREQUENTLY, INDIVIDUALS WHO HAVE TMD SHOW A DISTURBING COMBINATION OF CLINICAL AND PSYCHOLOGICAL SIGNS. DUE TO THESE POTENTIALLY COMPLEX CIRCUMSTANCE, IT IS INTERESTING FOR THE SCIENTIFIC COMMUNITY THE USE OF PREDICTIVE STATISTICAL APPROACHES THAT EASE THE PROCESS OF RECOGNITION AND/OR PREDICTION OF TMD OCCURRENCE, SO THAT THE PATIENTS CAN DIRECTED TO THE MOST SUITABLE TREATMENT FOR EACH CASE. "@pt ;
