    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ODONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1029> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ORAL MUCOSITIS (OM) IS A STOMATITIS RESULTING FROM ANTICANCER THERAPY RADIOTHERAPY AND/OR CHEMOTHERAPY). WITH PREVALENCE RANGING FROM 10% TO 100%, THIS MORBID CONDITION REPRESENTS A SIGNIFICANT PROBLEM IN THIS AREA. THIS DOUBLE-BLIND RANDOMIZED CLINICAL TRIAL EVALUATED THE EFFICACY OF PHOTOBIOMODULATION IN THE PREVENTION AND TREATMENT OF OM IN 32 PATIENTS WITH GASTROINTESTINAL NEOPLASMS UNDERGOING CHEMOTHERAPY (FLUOROURACIL) AT THE ONCOLOGY CLINIC OF THE HOSPITAL DAS CLÍNICAS,RECIFE, PERNAMBUCO,"@pt ;
