    capes:hasAbstract "THE AIM OF THE STUDY WAS TO ANALYZE THE IMPACT OF REPEATED TREATMENT WITH BOTULINUM TOXIN TYPE A ON THE GLANDULAR STRUCTURE AND ORAL MICROBIOTA OF RATS. THIRTY FIVE WISTAR RATS (RATTUS NORVEGICUS ALBINUS) WERE DIVIDED INTO THREE GROUPS: GROUP C (CONTROL, N = 7), WHERE THE ANIMALS WERE NOT TREATED; THE G GROUP (N = 14) UNDERWENT INTRAGLANDULAR INJECTION WITH THE BOTULINUM TOXIN TYPE A STABILIZER WHICH IS BOVINE GELATIN; AND GROUP B (N = 14) TREATED WITH 2.5U BOTULINUM TOXIN TYPE A (PROSIGNE®, CRI"@pt ;
