    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/10394> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THIS THESIS WE PRESENTED ESTIMATORS AND TESTS FOR PARAMETERS THAT INDEX MANLY AND BOX-COX TRANSFORMATIONS, TO TRANSFORM RESPONSE VARIABLE OF THE LINEAR REGRESSION MODEL. IT WAS INITIALLY PROPOSED TWO SCORE TESTS TO TEST THE PARAMETERS THAT INDEXES MANLY AND BOX-COX TRANSFORMATIONS. WE PROCEDURE MONTE CARLO AND BOOTSTRAP SIMULATIONS. THE BOOTSTRAP VERSION OF THE TEST PROVIDED BETTER RESULTS THAN THE ASYMPTOTIC VERSION, AS WELL AS THE TEST BASED ON EXPECTED INFORMATION. ADDITIONALLY, WE VERIFIE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "13FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ESSAYS IN DATA TRANSFORMATION AND REGRESSION ANALYSIS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ANA_HERMINIA_ANDRADE_E_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/10395> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN REGRESSION THEORY A WIDE RANGE OF TECHNIQUES CAN BE PERFORMED TO INVESTIGATE THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE RESPONSE AND THE REGRESSORS. A LARGE NUMBER OF POSSIBLE REGRESSION MODELS ALLOWS PRACTITIONERS TO REACH A BETTER FIT TO A DATASET. IN SOME SITUATIONS, TWO OR MORE COMPETING MODELS MAY FIT THE DATA EQUALLY WELL. WHEN NONE OF THEM CAN BE OBTAINED FROM THE OTHERS BY IMPOSING PARAMETRIC RESTRICTIONS, WE SAY THESE MODELS ARE NONNESTED. IN ORDER TO CHOOSE THE BETWEEN COMPETING NONNESTED LINEAR "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "10FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ESSAYS ON NONNORMAL REGRESSION MODELING"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
