    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1040> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PHOTOBIOMODULATION HAS BEEN USED ON HEALING WOUND, PAIN TREATMENT, REGENERATIVE THERAPY AND INFLAMMATION AT LEAST 30 YEARS. HAS BEEN DEMONSTRATED THAT THE LLLT CAN INTERFERE IN CELL PROLIFERATION, BESIDES EXERTING EFFECTS ON THE METABOLISM OF SOME CELLS, FAVORING THE PRODUCTION OF SUBSTANCES SUCH AS REACTIVE SPECIES OF NITROGEN AND OXYGEN AND SOME CYTOKINES IN LYMPHOCYTES AND MACROPHAGES IN VITRO. THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE INFLUENCE OF LLLT WITH DIFFERENT PARAMETERS (GAALAS A"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "30AUG2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFLUÊNCIA DA TERAPIA LASER DE BAIXA POTÊNCIA SOBRE A MODULAÇÃO DA RESPOSTA INFLAMATÓRIA E DA ATIVIDADE MITOCONDRIAL EM MACRÓFAGOS ATIVADOS\""@pt ;
