<http://example.com/capes#thesis/10701> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN PERFORMING THE EXERCISE ON THE FOREARM THE ARTERIOLES DILATE BY RELEASE OF NITRIC OXIDE (ON), INCREASING THE DIAMETER AND BLOOD FLOW. THE TRAINING ASSOCIATED WITH RESTRICTION OF BLOOD FLOW (RBF) ALLOWS THE ACCOMPLISHMENT OF EXERCISES WITH LOW INTENSITY, FAVORING ITS APPLICATION TO PATIENTS INTOLERANT TO HIGH LOADS, SUCH AS CHRONIC KIDNEY PATIENTS. THIS PAPER WILL BE PRESENTED IN TWO ARTICLES, BEING A REVIEW AND AN ORIGINAL ARTICLE. THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO ANALYZE THE EFFICACY OF EXERCISE"@pt ;
