    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: OBESE PATIENTS PRESENT HIGHER CHANCE OF DEVELOPING COMORBIDITIES, SUCH AS METABOLIC SYNDROME AND GASTRO ESOPHAGEAL REFLUX DISEASE. BARIATRIC SURGERY IS THE MOST EFFICIENT TREATMENT, LEADING TO IMPROVEMENTS OF THESE COMORBIDITIES, HOWEVER, PROGRESSION OF GERD SYMPTOMS IN PATIENTS WHO UNDERGO SLEEVE GASTRECTOMY (SG) IS STILL CONTROVERSIAL. OBJECTIVES: TO EVALUATE UPPER GASTROINTESTINAL ENDOSCOPIC (UGE) FINDINGS IN RELATION TO ESOPHAGITIS BEFORE AND AFTER SG, BESIDES THE GASTRIC TUBE "@pt ;
