<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1082> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INADEQUATE CONTROL OF TRACHEAL TUBE CUFF PRESSURE CAN RESULT IN IMMEDIATE OR LATE COMPLICATIONS, SUCH AS BRONCHIAL ASPIRATION OR TRACHEAL INJURIES, WHICH MAY REQUIRE COMPLEX MEDICAL INTERVENTIONS TO CORRECT THEM AND CONSEQUENT INCREASE IN MORBIDITY AND MORTALITY. THE OBJECTIVE TECHNIQUE USING A PRESSURE GAUGE IS THE MOST RECOMMENDED FOR MAINTAINING SAFE PRESSURE VALUES (20-30 CM H2O). BUT AS THIS DEVICE IS NOT WIDELY AVAILABLE IN OPERATING ROOMS, HEALTH PROFESSIONALS, INCLUDING ANESTHESIOLOGISTS"@pt ;
