    capes:hasAbstract "ROUX-EN-Y GASTRIC BYPASS (RYGB) IS ONE OF THE MOST COMMONLY PERFORMED SURGERIES TO TREAT OBESITY WORLDWIDE. HOWEVER, APPROXIMATELY 20% OF PATIENTS HAVE RECURRENCE OF OBESITY AND ENLARGEMENT OF THE GASTROJEJUNAL ANASTOMOSIS IS ONE OF THE ASSOCIATED FACTORS. ENDOSCOPIC TREATMENT OF ANASTOMOSIS HAS BEEN PROPOSED FOR FURTHER WEIGHT LOSS. ONE OF THE MOST COMMONLY USED TECHNIQUES FOR ANASTOMOTIC NARROWING IS THE ARGON PLASMA COAGULATION (APC). HOWEVER, THERE ARE NO RANDOMIZED CONTROLLED TRIALS PROVING"@pt ;
