<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1085> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE GROWTH RATE OF MORBID OBESITY IS HIGHER THAN THAT OF OBESITY IN GENERAL. THEREFORE, THE NUMBER OF BARIATRIC SURGERIES GREW BY 84.73% BETWEEN 2011 AND 2018 IN BRAZIL. BETTER POSTOPERATIVE RESULTS DEPEND ON PREVIOUS NUTRITIONAL STATUS. THE AIM OF THE STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE ASSOCIATION OF BODY COMPOSITION WITH FOOD INTAKE AND LIFESTYLE IN THE PREOPERATIVE PERIOD OF BARIATRIC SURGERY. THIS IS A CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY, CONDUCTED IN 2018-2019 TIME PERIOD, WITH ADULT PATIENTS ADMITTED FOR SURGERY"@pt ;
