    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: PERIPHERAL OBSTRUCTIVE ARTERY DISEASE (PAD) OF THE LOWER LIMBS (LL) IS PREVALENT WORLDWIDE. ISCHEMIC WOUNDS (IW) REPRESENT THE FINAL STAGE OF PAD AND REQUIRE, IN MOST CASES, ARTERIAL REVASCULARIZATION PROCEDURES, EITHER ENDOVASCULAR OR OPEN SURGERY, IN ADDITION TO DEBRIDEMENTS AND DRESSINGS FOR ADEQUATE HEALING. THERE IS NO CONSENSUS ON WHICH DRESSING IS IDEAL FOR USE IN IW, BUT FEATURES SUCH AS LOW COST, HYPOALLERGENIC AND PROVIDING SPACED EXCHANGES ARE EXPECTED. THE FILM AND GEL "@pt ;
