<http://example.com/capes#thesis/11364> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ELEPHANT GRASS [CENCHRUS PURPUREUS (SCHUM.) MORRONE SIN. PENNISETUM PURPUREUM SHUM.] HAS A HIGH POTENTIAL FOR DRY MATTER PRODUCTION, HOWEVER, IT PRESENTS AN EARLY STEM ELONGATION THAT CONTRIBUTES TO A RAPID DECLINE IN THE FORAGE NUTRITIVE VALUE. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE AND EXPLAIN VARIATIONS IN MORPHOLOGICAL CHARACTERISTICS AND IN VITRO GAS PRODUCTION KINETICS OF IRRIGATED ELEPHANT GRASS GENOTYPES OF DIFFERENT SIZES UNDER TWO HARVESTING FREQUENCIES. THE EXPERIMENT WAS CARRIED"@pt ;
