<http://example.com/capes#thesis/11368> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRODUCTION OF CACTUS PEAR SILAGE MAY OPTIMIZE THE USE OF THIS IMPORTANT FORAGE RESOURCE IN THE SEMI-ARID REGION. HOWEVER, THE LOW CONCENTRATION OF DRY MATTER (DM) AND HIGH CONCENTRATION OF SOLUBLE CARBOHYDRATES MAY AFFECT FERMENTATIVE CHARACTERISTICS OF THE PRODUCED SILAGE. THE INCLUSION OF LEUCAENA HAY [LEUCAENA LEUCOCEPHALA (LAM.) WIT] DURING THE CACTUS PEAR ENSILAGE PROCESS MAY CONTRIBUTE TO INCREASE THE SILAGE DM CONCENTRATION, REDUCE EFFLUENT LOSSES, AND IMPROVE THE FERMENTATIVE CHARACT"@pt ;
