<http://example.com/capes#thesis/11462> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: ARBOVIRUSES, SUCH AS DENGUE, CHIKUNGUNYA AND ZIKA, ARE TRANSMITTED BY ARTHROPODS OF THE GENUS AEDES, IN GENERAL, AEDES AEGYPTI OR ALBOPICTUS AND ARE CLASSIFIED IN THE GROUP OF EMERGING AND REEMERGING INFECTIOUS DISEASES. THEY ARE CURRENTLY IMPORTANT CHALLENGES FOR PUBLIC HEALTH, DUE TO THEIR HIGH TRANSMISSION CAPACITY AND MORBIDITY AND MORTALITY. BRAZIL IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE MAJORITY OF REPORTED CASES ON THE CONTINENT, WITH EMPHASIS ON THE NORTHEAST REGION, WHERE THERE IS A HIGH I"@pt ;
