<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1151> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE HELIOTHERMIC GENERATION OF ELECTRICITY PRESENTS ITSELF AS AN EXCELLENT OPTION FOR THE NATIONAL ELECTRICITY SECTOR, BECAUSE AS THE WATER SOURCES DECREASE IN THE PERIOD OF DROUGHT, THE SOLAR POTENTIAL INCREASES DUE TO THE SOLAR RADIATION MORE INTENSE IN SEVERAL REGIONS OF THE COUNTRY. A CENTRAL TOWER HELIOTHERMIC PLANT HAS THE CHARACTERISTIC OF FOCUSING THE SUN'S RAYS ON A SINGLE POINT AND TRANSFORMING THE THERMAL ENERGY INTO ELECTRICITY THROUGH SOLAR COLLECTORS, HEAT EXCHANGERS AND ELECTRIC T"@pt ;
