<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1155> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE USE OF HEAVY FUEL OIL AS FUEL ON SHIPS HAS BEEN A DIFFERENTIATING FACTOR FOR THE MARITIME MARKET TO REMAIN COMPETITIVE AND PROVIDE AFFORDABLE SERVICES. THE LOW COST OF HEAVY FUEL OIL COMPARED TO ITS MAIN COMPETITOR DIESEL CAN MAKE A CRUCIAL DIFFERENCE IN SHIP CHARTER AGREEMENTS. HOWEVER, THE USE OF HEAVY FUEL OIL HAS SOME LIMITATIONS, AMONG WHICH ARE ITS HIGH VISCOSITY. CURRENTLY, TO OVERCOME THIS LIMITATION, THE FUEL GOES THROUGH AN ELECTRIC HEATING, WHICH IMPLIES AN INCREASE IN THE UTILIZA"@pt ;
