<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1175> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN A SCENARIO WHERE THE DEMAND FOR ELECTRIC ENERGY HAS GROWTH PROJECTION OF 45% UNTIL 2035, WIND ENERGY TENDS TO GROW AS A STRONG ALTERNATIVE FOR THE PRODUCTION AND SUPPLY OF WORLD ENERGY DEMAND. IN PARALLEL TO THIS SCENARIO, THE ESTIMATE IS THAT BY 2050; 2.5 BILLION PEOPLE WILL TEND TO OCCUPY LARGE URBAN CENTERS. IN VIEW OF THESE ENERGY SUPPLY CHALLENGES IN LARGE CITIES, APPLICATIONS OF SMALL WIND TURBINES IN URBAN AREAS ARISE AS AN OPTION TO SAVE ELECTRICITY. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS CASE ST"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "07JUN2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
