    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIA_DA_ENERGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1178> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN ORDER TO MAINTAIN LIFECYCLE, PLANTS ABSORB MACRO AND MICRONUTRIENT, SUCH AS CU, NI, MN AND ZN WHICH ARE IMPORTANT FOR PLANT GROWTH. SOILS CONTAMINATED WITH METALS CAN BE REMEDIATED BY MEANS OF THE PHYTOREMEDIATION PROCESS, WHICH USES PLANTS TO ABSORB SOME METAL DURING THEIR GROWTH. THESE SOILS ARE USUALLY CONTAMINATED THROUGH THE PROCESSES OF MINING, INDUSTRIAL WASTE RELEASE, AND METALS DISPERSED PARTICLES IN THE AIR. THE WORK AIMS AT THE USE OF LIGNOCELLULOSIC BIOMASS FROM HEAVY METALS CONTA"@pt ;
