<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1184> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE USE OF SHIPS TO TRANSPORT NATURAL GAS OVER LONG DISTANCES IS A MEDIUM WIDELY USED BY GAS PRODUCERS, HOWEVER THIS TRANSPORT IS USUALLY MADE WITH COMPRESSED NATURAL GAS OR LIQUEFIED GAS SO THAT A GREATER AMOUNT OF GAS IS TRANSPORTED ON EACH TRIP. . THIS WORK PROPOSES THE INSERTION OF THE USE OF ADSORPTION TECHNOLOGY TO THE PROCESS OF TRANSPORT AND STORAGE OF GAS IN THE GAS VESSELS. FOR THIS PURPOSE, THE TRANSPORT WAS MODELED AND SIMULATED NOT ONLY IN COMPRESSED FORM, BUT RATHER THAT PART OF TH"@pt ;
