<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1185> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS WORK STUDIES A DYNAMICS MATHEMATICAL MODEL COUPLED THE ADSORPTION ISOTHERM (TOTH MODEL) THAT DESCRIBES THE ADSORPTION OF CO2 IN A FIXED-BED ADSORBER (FBA). THE DEVELOPED DYNAMICS MODELLING REPORTS THE DIFFUSION-ADSORPTION PROCESS IN TERMS OF MASS TRANSFER PHENOMENA (EXTERNAL AND INTERNAL). THE ADSORPTION EQUILIBRIUM EXPERIMENTAL DATA OF CO2 WERE MEASURED USING AN ELECTROMAGNETIC SUSPENSION MICROBALANCE. THE EXPERIMENTAL DATA WERE CORRELATED WITH THE TOTH ISOTHERM MODEL USING NONLINEAR REGRE"@pt ;
