<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1187> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN OFF-GRID PHOTOVOLTAIC SYSTEMS, THE LEAD-ACID BATTERY IS STILL THE MOST USED TECHNOLOGY FOR ENERGY STORAGE AND IS THE COMPONENT THAT HAS THE SHORTEST LIFE OF THE SYSTEM, AROUND 2 TO 3 YEARS, SO IT IS A DEVICE THAT REQUIRES SPECIAL ATTENTION TO ENSURE THAT SITUATIONS DO NOT OCCUR DURING THEIR USE WHICH REDUCE THEIR LIFESPAN. IN VIEW OF THIS BATTERY-CRITICAL NATURE, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO USE THE KALMAN FILTER TECHNIQUE TO ESTIMATE THE STATE OF CHARGE OF LEAD-ACID BATTERIES AND TO LOA"@pt ;
