<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1194> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BIOGAS IS A PROMISING SOURCE OF RENEWABLE ENERGY, AND AMONG EXISTING TECHNOLOGIES THAT USE BIOGAS, BIOGAS DROUGHT REFORM HAS BECOME A PROMISING TECHNOLOGY FOR THE CONVERSION OF STUDY GASES, METHANE (CH4) AND CARBON DIOXIDE (CO2) IN GAS IF SYNTHESIS (CO AND H2). IN ORDER TO REDUCE GREENHOUSE GASES, DRY REFORMING PRODUCES AN H2/CO ~ 1 RATIO, WHICH MAKES IT MORE FEASIBLE TO OBTAIN LIQUID SYNTHETIC FUELS THROUGH THE FISCHER - TROPSCH SYNTHESIS (SYNGAS) THROUGH THE BIOGAS PRODUCED AT RESERVA CAMARÁ I"@pt,
