<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1195> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "EVALUATION OF ACID DIGESTION METHODOLOGY IN SAMPLES OF POLY (ETHYLENE TEREPHTHALATE) RESIN FOR ELEMENTAL DETERMINATION BY ICP OES"@pt,
        "VAPORIZED PROPANE IS WIDELY USED BY INDUSTRY IN HEAT GENERATION FOR PRODUCTION PROCESSES. PROPANE VAPORIZATION IS OBTAINED FROM THE POWER SUPPLY FOR PHASE CHANGE IN EQUIPMENT CALLED VAPORIZERS. THIS ENERGY SUPPLY, OFTEN ELECTRICITY OR PROPANE ITSELF, HAS HIGH OPERATING COSTS. THIS WORK AIMS TO ANALYZE THE APPLICATION OF INDIRECT SOLAR HEATING AS THE MAIN ENERGY SOURCE FOR PROPANE VAPORIZATION FROM A CLOSED SYSTEM THAT USES WATER AS A WORKING FLUID AND TO PRESENT THE DESIRED VARIABLES FOR THE MAI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "28NOV2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAÇÃO DE METODOLOGIA DE DIGESTÃO ÁCIDA EM AMOSTRAS DE RESINA DE POLI (TEREFTALATO DE ETILENO) PARA DETERMINAÇÃO ELEMENTAR POR ICP OES"@pt,
        "SISTEMA TERMOSSOLAR PARA VAPORIZAÇÃO FORÇADA DO PROPANO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ABINOAN_DA_SILVA_RODRIGUES>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/ANDRE_LUIZ_FERREIRA_DE_BARROS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/QUÍMICA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIA_DA_ENERGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1196> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "NORTHEAST BRAZIL HAS HIGH RADIATION RATES, HOWEVER, DUE TO THE CLIMATIC CONDITIONS, THIS REGION HAS HIGH TEMPERATURE INDEXES, WHICH DIRECTLY AFFECTS THE EFFICIENCY OF PHOTOVOLTAIC PANELS. THE WORK PRESENTED HERE EVALUATED SUSTAINABLE PRACTICES FOR THE REDUCTION OF TEMPERATURE OF THE PANELS, THROUGH THE INTEGRATION WITH ROOFS THAT PROVIDE EVAPOTRANSPIRATION COOLING AND TEMPERATURE REDUCTION DUE TO THE ALBEDO. AN EXPERIMENTAL EVALUATION OF THE METHOD OF INTEGRATING PHOTOVOLTAIC SYSTEMS TO GREEN AN"@pt,
        "PH SENSITIVE ALGINATE AND IONIC LIQUIDS HYDROGEL BEADS AS DRUG CARRIERS"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "02MAR2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "04JUN2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "BEADS DE HIDROGEL PH SENSIVEIS A BASE DE ALGINATO E LIQUIDOS IONICOS PARA CARREAMENTO DE FARMACOS"@pt,
        "TELHADOS VERDES FOTOVOLTÁICOS - AVALIAÇÃO EXPERIMENTAL DE DESEMPENHO TÉRMICO E ENERGÉTICO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ARTHUR_DE_ALMEIDA_BARROS>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/BARBARA_EMANUELLE_MARIA_DA_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/QUÍMICA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIA_DA_ENERGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1197> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BIOTRANSFORMATION OF ACETYLENE COMPOUNDS AIMING AT THE SUSTAINABLE PREPARATION OF YNONAS AND CHEMICAL PROPARGILIC ALCOHOLS"@pt,
        "THE INCREASE IN THE AMOUNT OF URBAN SOLID WASTE (MSW), JUSTIFIED BY THE INTENSIFICATION OF HUMAN ACTIVITIES, HAS BECOME A PROBLEM FOR URBAN CENTERS AS TO THEIR FINAL DESTINATION, SINCE IN WRONG PLACES THEY CAUSE VISUAL AND ENVIRONMENTAL POLLUTION. TO AVOID THIS PROBLEM, THE NATIONAL SOLID WASTE POLICY (PNRS) WAS LAUNCHED IN 2010, WHICH OBLIGES STATES AND MUNICIPALITIES TO ELABORATE THE MANAGEMENT OF THIS WASTE AND ITS DESTINATION IN SANITARY LANDFILLS, AND THIS MANAGEMENT INCLUDES THE USE OF MSW"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "07JAN2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "28NOV2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "BIOTRANSFORMAÇÃO DE COMPOSTOS ACETILENICOS VISANDO A PREPARAÇÃO SUSTENTAVEL DE YNONAS E ALCOOIS PROPARGILICOS QUIRAIS"@pt,
        "UTILIZAÇÃO DE FRAÇÕES ORGÂNICAS DE RESÍDUOS SÓLIDOS URBANOS PARA A GERAÇÃO DE BIOGÁS E ENERGIA ELÉTRICA EM UMA CENTRAL DE TRATAMENTO DE RESÍDUOS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ALANA_BITTENCOURT_VIEIRA_DA_SILVA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/EDESIO_DE_LIMA_CAVALCANTE_FILHO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/QUÍMICA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIA_DA_ENERGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1198> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DEVELOPMENT OF BIMODAL CONTRAST AGENTS FOR OPTICAL IMAGE AND MAGNETIC RESONANCE BASED ON QUANTUM POINTS OF CDTE AND GD CHELATES (III)"@pt,
        "LEACHATE IS A SERIOUS AND VERY COMMON ENVIRONMENTAL PROBLEM IN DUMPS AND LANDFILLS, WHICH HAS SEVERE CONSEQUENCES, SUCH AS CONTAMINATING GROUNDWATER AND WATER BODIES, FOR EXAMPLE. LEACHATE IS PRODUCED FROM THE NATURAL DECOMPOSITION OF MATTER. IN ADDITION TO THIS, OTHER COMPOUNDS SUCH AS METHANE AND HYDROGEN SULFIDE ARE ALSO FORMED AND, LIKE SLUDGE, ARE EXTREMELY HARMFUL TO THE ENVIRONMENT. THE LEACHATE HAS AS ITS MAIN CHARACTERISTICS BEING A DARK LIQUID, OF UNPLEASANT ODOR, WITH HIGH ORGANIC MAT"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28NOV2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "30OCT2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DESENVOLVIMENTO DE AGENTES DE CONTRASTE BIMODAIS PARA IMAGEM ÓPTICA E POR RESSONÂNCIA MAGNÉTICA BASEADOS EM PONTOS QUÂNTICOS DE CDTE E QUELATOS DE GD (III)"@pt,
        "VIABILIDADE ECONÔMICA DE PROPOSTA ALTERNATIVA PARA TRATAMENTO DE LIXIVIADO E ANÁLISE DE PRODUÇÃO ENERGÉTICA DE UMA CTR"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/GABRIELA_MARQUES_DE_ALBUQUERQUE>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/JOSE_ANTONIO_RIBEIRO_DE_ARAUJO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/QUÍMICA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIA_DA_ENERGIA> .

