<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12178> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MUSEUMS ARE SPACES FOR CONSERVATION, STUDIES, DISSEMINATION AND ENJOYMENT OF THE CULTURAL AND ARTISTIC HERITAGE PRODUCED BY SOCIETY. THEY ARE NON-PROFIT INSTITUTIONS THAT, AMONG COUNTLESS POSSIBILITIES, PUT THE PUBLIC IN CONTACT WITH THE MOST DIVERSE CATEGORIES OF HERITAGE THAT, IN TURN, PROMOTE THE UNDERSTANDING OF SOCIAL AND CULTURAL LIFE. THE EDUCATIONAL FUNCTION OF MUSEUMS HAS BEEN PART OF THE REFLECTIONS OF RECOGNIZED INSTITUTIONS SUCH AS THE UNITED NATIONS EDUCATIONAL, SCIENTIFIC AND CULTU"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "23FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "MUSEU DO HOMEM AMERICANO: DESCORTINANDO A EDUCAÇÃO MUSEAL SOBRE A ARTE PRÉ-HISTÓRICA EM SÃO RAIMUNDO NONATO,"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/NALIANA_DA_SILVA_MENDES> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ARTES_VISUAIS_(UFPB_J.P._-_UFPE)> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12179> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ARCHITECTURE, STUDIED FROM THE MOST DIVERSE PERSPECTIVES, CAN EVOKE TWO IMPORTANT AXES: YOUR HISTORICAL ASPECT, FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF MONUMENTS, AND YOUR MNEMONIC ASPECT, WHICH STARTS FROM BOTH, YOUR MATERIALITY AND YOUR IMMATERIALITY, LIFE TRAJECTORY AND USE. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH IS TO ANALYZE EDIFÍCIO 34 IN AN ARTISTIC-HISTORICAL-PATRIMONIAL WAY IN AN ATTEMPT TO UNDERSTAND YOUR ARTISTIC TRAJECTORY. THE RESEARCH ANALYZES FROM THESE THREE AXES EDIFÍCIO 34 - CURRENTLY KNOWN AS CA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "O EDIFÍCIO 34 COMO PALIMPSESTO PARA AS ARTES VISUAIS EM JOÃO PESSOA/PB"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/EMANUELLY_MYLENA_VELOZO_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ARTES_VISUAIS_(UFPB_J.P._-_UFPE)> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12180> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH PRESENTS MY PLASTIC PROCESS AND SOME RESEARCH RESULTS IN THE GRAPHIC ARTS CONTAMINATED BY SOILS FROM CARIRI CEARENSE. I UNDERSTAND THE WORK PROCESS AS SOMETHING CONTINUOUS AND OF SIMILAR IMPORTANCE TO THE RESULTS. THE PROCESSES ARE CROSSED BY CONCEPTS SUCH AS NATURE, TERRITORY AND IDENTITY, BASED ON MY EXPERIENCES. I INITIALLY PRESENT THESE PROCESSES AND IN THE SECOND VOLUME, O CARIRI CEARENSE AND LIRA NODESTINA, WHICH ALSO CROSSED MY TRAINING AND RESEARCH PROCESSES."@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "31AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "O QUE FAZ DE UMA CASA UM LAR?"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ANDREA_SOBREIRA_DE_OLIVEIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ARTES_VISUAIS_(UFPB_J.P._-_UFPE)> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12181> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH SEEKS TO INVESTIGATE HOW THE SIGHT-SIZE METHOD CONTRIBUTED TO MY STUDY AND ARTISTIC DEVELOPMENT IN OBSERVATIONAL DRAWING, HAVING AS SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES, 1- TO EXAMINE THE LEARNING PROCESS OF OBSERVATIONAL DRAWING FROM THE SIGHT-SIZE METHOD; 2- IDENTIFY THE MAIN CONCEPTS OF THE SIGHT-SIZE METHOD FROM INVESTIGATIONS OF THE LEARNING AND STUDY PROCESS, THROUGH THE ANALYSIS OF MY DRAWINGS BETWEEN 2015 AND 2021; 3- ANALYZE HOW MY PROCESS OF STUDY AND CREATION OF THE OBSERVATIONAL DRAWING"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "23FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PROCESSOS DE APRENDIZAGEM COM O DESENHO DE OBSERVAÇÃO ATRAVÉS DO MÉTODO SIGHT-SIZE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOAO_VICTOR_PINTO_BAIA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ARTES_VISUAIS_(UFPB_J.P._-_UFPE)> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12182> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE (RE)PERFORMANCE, A METHODOLOGY THAT MAKES IT POSSIBLE TO REVISIT PERFORMATIVE WORKS, CAN ENHANCE NEW LOOKS AND PERSPECTIVES IN RELATION TO WORKS THAT HAVE BEEN PRODUCED PREVIOUSLY. THIS RESEARCH DIALOGUES WITH THE FIELD OF VISUAL ARTS THEORY THROUGH THE STUDY OF (RE)PERFORMANCE, VIRTUAL MEDIA AND AUDIENCES. THE GENERAL OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH IS TO INVESTIGATE THE POTENTIAL OF THE USE OF CULTURAL MEDIATION IN MUSEUMS THROUGH (RE)PERFORMANCE IN THE PERMANENT EXHIBITION OF THE MUSEU DO HOME"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28JUN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
