<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1260> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SYSTEMIC LUPUS ERYTHEMATOSUS (SLE) IS A SEVERE CHRONIC AUTOIMMUNE DISORDER, CHARACTERIZED BY LOSS OF TOLERANCE TO ITS OWN ANTIGENS WITH DEREGULATION IN THE RESPONSE OF INTERFERONS, WHICH CAN OCCUR IN THE MOST DIVERSE SYSTEMS OF THE ORGANISM. IT COMES FROM THE ASSOCIATION OF GENETIC FACTORS WITH OTHERS OF ENVIRONMENTAL, IMMUNOLOGICAL OR HORMONAL ORIGIN. A POLYCLONAL IMMUNE RESPONSE OCCURS AGAINST NUMEROUS NUCLEAR AUTOANTIGENS WITH PERSISTENT ANTINUCLEAR ANTIBODIES. MANY GENE LOCI OF INVOLVEMENT I"@pt ;
