    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PATOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12791> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FORENSIC EXPERTISE RELIES ON TECHNIQUES FROM OTHER AREAS OF KNOWLEDGE, WHICH SUPPORT AN INVESTIGATION OF INTEREST TO SOCIETY. THUS, IT IS UNDERSTOOD THAT MAKEUP - USED IN THE EVOLUTION OF HUMANITY AS A RESOURCE FOR TRANSFORMATION, BEAUTIFICATION, ART AND DIFFERENTIATION - CAN CONTRIBUTE SIGNIFICANTLY TO THE FIELD OF FORENSIC TRAINING AND PRACTICE. PROSTHESES MAKEUP SIMULATE INJURIES AND DEFORMITIES AND MATERIALS SUCH AS SILICONE AND POLYURETHANE ARE USED TO MAKE THEM. WE SEE THE POSSIBILITY OF I"@pt ;
