<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12792> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: THE OCCUPATIONAL ACCIDENT WITH BIOLOGICAL MATERIAL CONSISTS OF THE WORKER'S CONTACT WITH BLOOD AND/OR OTHER ORGANIC FLUIDS DURING THE WORKDAY. OBJECTIVE: TO DESCRIBE THE EPIDEMIOLOGICAL PROFILE OF OCCUPATIONAL ACCIDENTS WITH EXPOSURE TO BIOLOGICAL MATERIAL REPORTED IN A UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO FROM 2009 TO 2019. METHODOLOGY: A RETROSPECTIVE CROSS-SECTIONAL DESCRIPTIVE STUDY WAS CONDUCTED BASED ON THE ANALYSIS OF 134 NOTIFICATION FORMS OF ACCIDENTS INVOLVING E"@pt ;
