<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12796> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: IN 2019, THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC SURGED, AND, ALONG WITH IT, SEVERAL MODIFICATIONS IN THE SOCIAL STRUCTURE EMERGED FOLLOWING THE MEASURES ADOPTED TO CONTAIN THE SPREAD OF THE VIRUS, NAMELY: MASK WEARING, SOCIAL ISOLATION, AND THE RACE TO DEVELOP VACCINES. ONE OF THE GROUPS THAT SUFFERED THE MOST SIGNIFICANT EFFECTS WAS THE FEMALE GENDER. SOCIAL ISOLATION AND HOME STAYING DURING THE PANDEMIC WAS A CONDITION THAT REVEALED CHALLENGES, ESPECIALLY FOR WOMEN, WHO OFTEN HAD TO SPEND MORE TI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "30SEP2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAR PREVALÊNCIA DA VIOLÊNCIA DO GÊNERO FEMININO DURANTE A PANDEMIA: REVISÃO INTEGRATIVA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/PEDRO_AUGUSTO_DE_OLIVEIRA_FEITOSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PERÍCIAS_FORENSES> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12797> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AS THE CORONAVIRUS DISEASE 2019 (COVID-19) PANDEMIC ACCELERATED ACROSS THE WORLD, HEALTHCARE SYSTEMS BECAME OVERWHELMED, LEADING TO PSYCHOLOGICAL PRESSURE ON HEALTHCARE PROFESSIONALS, ESPECIALLY NURSES WHO FOUND THEMSELVES ON THE FRONT LINES OF CARE. TO PATIENTS. OBJECTIVE: TO KNOW THE WORKING CONDITIONS EXPERIENCED BY NURSES WORKING IN INTENSIVE CARE AND EMERGENCIES, REFERENCES IN THE CARE OF PATIENTS WITH COVID-19. METHOD: THIS IS A QUALITATIVE STUDY CARRIED OUT IN A CAPITAL CITY IN NORTHEASTE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20APR2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "CONDIÇÕES DE TRABALHO: VIVÊNCIA DE ENFERMEIROS EM SERVIÇOS DE UTI E EMERGÊNCIA DURANTE A PANDEMIA DA COVID-19"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/BRUNO_ALBUQUERQUE_CAMPOS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PERÍCIAS_FORENSES> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12798> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WITH THE ONSET OF THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC IN BRAZIL, LABOR RELATIONS VISIBLY AND SIGNIFICANTLY WERE SIGNIFICANTLY DECIDED. WITH THE QUARANTINE GOVERNMENT ANNOUNCED IN MARCH 20, A CRISIS BEGAN IN THE LABOR MARKET, WITH THE MISSION OF WORKERS IN KNOWN WORK TO WORK IN THE WORK REGIME, OF THE POPULARLY KNOWN WORK MISSION, OF WORK IN THE WORK REGIME, OF WORKERS AT HOME. IT WAS A SUDDEN CHANGE, THERE IS NO MODERN MEANS OF CONSTRUCTION, FOR MANY YEARS, AND A MODERN AND SOPHISTICATED ENTERPRISE FOR MANY Y"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "29SEP2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DIREITO DE TRABALHO E A PANDEMIA DO COVID-19: QUAIS SÃO AS MODIFICAÇÕES DURANTE A PANDEMIA DO COVID-19 RELACIONADO AO DIREITO DO TRABALHO COMPARADO COM O PERÍODO PRÉ-PANDÊMICO NO BRASIL"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOSE_MARCOS_DE_LIRA_OLIVEIRA_FILHO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PERÍCIAS_FORENSES> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12799> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC HAS GENERATED STRESS IN THE ECONOMIC, EMOTIONAL AND PSYCHOLOGICAL SPHERES OF SOCIAL STRUCTURES, ESPECIALLY THE FAMILY. COMBINED WITH MEASURES TAKEN TO REDUCE THE SPREAD OF SARS-COV-2, THESE FACTORS FAVOR AN INCREASE IN THE INCIDENCE OF CASES OF ABUSE/VIOLENCE AGAINST CHILDREN AND ADOLESCENTS. THIS WORK AIMED, THROUGH AN INTEGRATIVE REVIEW, TO VERIFY IF AFTER THE ESTABLISHMENT OF PERIODS OF SOCIAL ISOLATION AND LOCKDOWN THERE WAS AN INCREASE IN ABUSE/VIOLENCE AGAINST CHILDRE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21SEP2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ESTUDO COMPARATIVO DE CASOS DE ABUSO/VIOLÊNCIA EM CRIANÇAS E ADOLESCENTES ANTES E DURANTE A PANDEMIA DA COVID-19: REVISÃO INTEGRATIVA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JORGE_ANTONIO_DA_COSTA_PEREIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PERÍCIAS_FORENSES> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12800> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SPINA BIFIDA OCCULTA IS A CONGENITAL MALFORMATION IN INTRAUTERINE DEVELOPMENT CAUSED BY A FAILURE TO CLOSE THE POSTERIOR VERTEBRAL ARCHES AND CAN PROVIDE VALUABLE INFORMATION FOR HUMAN IDENTIFICATION. THIS RESEARCH AIMED TO EVALUATE THE OCCURRENCE OF HIDDEN SPINA BIFIDA IN HUMAN BONES OF BOTH SEXES FROM AN OSTEOLOGICAL COLLECTION IN NORTHEASTERN BRAZIL, CHECKING ITS FREQUENCY, THE REGION OF THE SPINE MOST AFFECTED, AND ITS INDIVIDUALIZING POTENTIAL. THE SAMPLE OF THIS STUDY WAS COMPOSED OF 427 S"@pt ;
