<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12802> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FEMINICIDE, THE MURDER OF WOMEN FOR GENDER REASONS, IS PRESENT IN REGIONAL, NATIONAL AND INTERNATIONAL NEWS. IT IS CHARACTERIZED BY THE LAST, AND MOST CRUEL, ACTION FROM THE AGGRESSOR TO THE VICTIM. EVEN TODAY, WOMEN ARE MURDERED ON A RECURRING BASIS, THE RESULT OF A HISTORICALLY PATRIARCHAL SOCIETY, WHERE MEN EXERCISE AUTHORITY OVER WOMEN AND ALWAYS OCCUPY A DOMINANT POSITION, GIVING NO SPACE TO FEMALE VOICES. BEING A WOMAN IS THE RISK FACTOR IN SEXIST SOCIETY, WHERE CRIMES BASED ON INEQUALITY "@pt ;
