<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12807> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IDENTITY IS THE SET OF PHYSICAL OR FUNCTIONAL AND PSYCHIC CHARACTERS, HOWEVER, PERMANENT, WHICH MAKE A PERSON DIFFERENT FROM OTHERS AND OCCUR TO THEISELF. FORENSIC DENTISTRY PARTICIPATES IN POST-MORTEM IDENTIFICATION PROCESSES IN SEVERAL WAYS, SUCH AS: SEX AND AGE ESTIMATION, OR EVEN IN THE DETERMINATION OF ETHNIC GROUPS. THE FRONTAL SINUS IS CHARACTERIZED BY BEING UNIQUE AND INDIVIDUAL, ITS SHAPE REMAINS PRACTICALLY UNCHANGED THROUGHOUT THE INDIVIDUAL'S ADULT LIFE. THUS, THE APPLICABILITY OF HU"@pt ;
