<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12809> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FORENSIC SCIENCES ARE BASED AND CONSTITUTED ON TECHNICAL/SCIENTIFIC FOUNDATIONS, WHOSE LEGAL CHARACTER HAS THE PURPOSE OF INVESTIGATING CRIMES IN THEIR MOST VARIED CONFIGURATIONS OF VIOLENCE, WITH THE MOST DIVERSE LEGAL CONSEQUENCES. CONSIDERING THAT THE COLLECTED TRACES ARE, FOR THE MOST PART, THE \"EYES\" OF THE JUDICIARY AT THE CRIME SCENE, IT IS ESSENTIAL TO TRAIN AND INFORM PROFESSIONALS WHO WORK IN A PRE-HOSPITAL CONTEXT IN ORDER TO \"KNOW HOW TO PROTECT THE PLACE/SCENE OF CRIME\", KNOWING HOW"@pt ;
