<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12836> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH IS AIMED TO ANALYZE THE OVERCOMING OF THE FINALIST SOCIAL ADEQUACY THEORY BY THE FUNCTIONALIST OBJECTIVE IMPUTATION THEORY, IMBRICATING THE CONJECTURE OF THE RISK ALLOWED AS AN INTERTWINING FOUNDATION BETWEEN THESE TWO THEORIES, DEMONSTRATING TO BE A CONTROVERSIAL AND A RELEVANT THEME TO THE LEGAL-CRIMINAL SCOPE, ESPECIALLY IN THE THEORY OF CRIME. FOR THE CHAPTER STRUCTURING OF THIS THEME, BIBLIOGRAPHIC RESEARCH WAS USED, BASED ON THE MAIN ISSUES RELATED TO CAUSALISM, NEOKATISM, FI"@pt ;
