    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/DIREITO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12852> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CONSTITUTIONAL JURISDICTION HAS AN INCREASINGLY PROMINENT FORUM, BEING RESPONSIBLE FOR CONDUCTING SEVERAL SENSITIVE TOPICS, SUCH AS PUBLIC POLICIES, MORAL ISSUES (ABORTION OF ANENCEPHALIC FETUSES, FOR EXAMPLE), AMONG MANY OTHERS. NOT ENOUGH, THE WAY IN WHICH THE SUPREME COURT USES TO BUILD PRECEDENTS, IN SUBSTANCE, HOW THE DEBATE BETWEEN THE JUDGES IS CARRIED OUT, HAS CHANGED RADICALLY, MOVING FROM AN ARTISANAL JURISDICTION, WITH SYNCHRONOUS AND FACE-TO-FACE DEBATES, TO AN ESSENTIALLY DIGITA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "03AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PLENÁRIO VIRTUAL E ACELERAÇÃO DOS JULGAMENTOS NO STF: DEBATE ELETRÔNICO E DEVIDO PROCESSO LEGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUIZ_BISPO_DA_SILVA_NETO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/DIREITO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12853> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CIVIL JUSTICE SYSTEM IS GENERALLY INEFFECTIVE, INEFFICIENT, EXPENSIVE, SLOW AND UNDEMOCRATIC. ATTEMPTS AT IMPROVEMENT HAVE CONTRIBUTED LITTLE TO IMPROVEMENT, AS METHODOLOGY ADOPTED CURRENTLY IS FLAWED: THE PROCEDURAL INSTRUMENTALITY AND ITS POSITIVIST MATRIX. FOCUSED ON DOGMATISM, SCIENTISM, CONCEPTUALISM AND AUTHORITARIANISM, PROCEDURAL INSTRUMENTALITY IS MORE SYMBOLIC THAN REAL. IT FAVORS THE DEBATE OF THESES IN DETRIMENT OF FACTICITY, FOR BELIEVING THAT THE APPLICATION OF THE LAW IS ENOUG"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "03AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PROCESSO CIVIL PRAGMATISTA DEMOCRÁTICO: PROPOSTA DE NOVA METODOLOGIA PROCESSUAL, A PARTIR DA CONSTATAÇÃO DE QUE A HISTÓRICA TRAJETÓRIA POSITIVISTA DO PROCESSO (INSTRUMENTALISMO) É INADEQUADA PARA A SOLUÇÃO DOS CONFLITOS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/MATUSALEM_JOBSON_BEZERRA_DANTAS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/DIREITO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12854> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH SEEKS TO UNDERSTAND THE LOGICAL DYNAMICS INVOLVED IN THE EVIDENTIARY REASONING OF THE CRIMINAL JUDGE WHO IS IN CHARGE OF ANALYZING A CASE THAT INVOLVES MULTIPLE ARGUMENTS AND EVIDENCE. THE MAIN QUESTION IS WHETHER THE CRIMINAL JUDGE FORMULATES HYPOTHESES. WE BEGIN OUR INVESTIGATION BY STUDYING THE JUDICIAL SYLLOGISM. WE REALIZED THAT IT WOULD BE NECESSARY TO CUT THE SYLLOGISM OF LEGAL SUBSUMPTION IN ORDER TO KEEP THE FOCUS ON FACTUAL PLURISYLLOGISMS, DISTINGUISH INFERENCES OF THE I"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "27JUN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "RACIOCÍNIO PROBATÓRIO DO JUIZ CRIMINAL: ANÁLISE DE EVIDÊNCIAS E FORMULAÇÃO DE HIPÓTESES"@pt ;
