<http://example.com/capes#thesis/12855> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE DEFINITION OF THE CONCEPT OF UNIT OF ACTION CAN BE UNDERSTOOD AS THE TOUCHSTONE FOR THE THEME OF THE COMPETITION OF CRIMES, ESPECIALLY SINCE THE NUMBER OF ACTIONS IS DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE NUMBER OF CRIMES, WITH REPERCUSSIONS ON PUNISHMENT. IT HAPPENS THAT, ON NOT RARE OCCASIONS, THE INTERPRETERS GIVE DIFFERENT TREATMENT TO SIMILAR FACTS, EVIDENCING THE LACK OF SAFE CRITERIA FOR THE EXAMINATION OF A CERTAIN CRIMINAL ACTIVITY, IN THE ASPECT OF UNITY OR PLURALITY OF CONDUCT. GIVEN THAT JUDICI"@pt ;
