<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13003> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INDUSTRIAL ACTIVITY PLAYS A RELEVANT ROLE IN THE SOCIOSPATIAL CONTEXT, DIRECTLY INFLUENCING WEALTH'S PRODUCTION IN SOCIETY, THE WAY OF APPROPRIATING SPACES AND THE INTENSIFICATION OF URBANIZATION PROCESSES. ON THE OTHER HAND, THE HYPOTHESIS THAT DEINDUSTRIALIZATION GIVES NEW MEANING TO SPACE, RESTRUCTURING IT THROUGH NEW APPROACHES AND CONTRIBUTING TO THE CHANGE IN REGIONAL SOCIOECONOMIC DYNAMICS, IS INCREASINGLY WIDESPREAD. THIS RESEARCH AIMS TO ANALYZE THE DEINDUSTRIALIZATION IN THE RECIFES M"@pt ;
