<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13005> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "VIOLENCE HAS BEEN PRESENTED AS SOMETHING ROUTINE, ESPECIALLY IN LARGE URBAN CENTERS. AS IS WELL KNOWN, THERE ARE DIFFERENT FORMS OF VIOLENCE AND CERTAIN ASPECTS PROMOTED BY IT ARE IMMEASURABLE. THIS SUBJECTIVITY LED THE PRESENT WORK TO CONSIDER THE PERSPECTIVE OF CRIMINAL VIOLENCE AS ONE THAT CAUSES HARM TO ANOTHER; AND, AS A QUANTIFIER OF ITS PERFORMANCE, THE NUMBERS OF INTENTIONAL LETHAL HOMICIDES AND/OR VIOLENT CRIMES. THE CENTRAL IDEA IS TO UNDERSTAND HOW THIS VIOLENCE ACTED IN THE CITY OF"@pt ;
