<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13008> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "LANDSLIDES ARE PROCESSES OF NATURAL DYNAMICS OF SLOPES WHOSE MAIN CONSTRAINTS ARE PHYSICAL AND BIOGEOCHEMICALS PARAMETERS, HOWEVER THEY CAN BE INDUCED BY ANTHROPIC INFLUENCE. THEY OCCUR ON A VARIETY OF SCALES, BOTH SPATIAL AND TEMPORAL. THE MAPPING OF AREAS PRONE TO THESE PROCESSES HAS BEEN RECOMMENDED BY GOVERNMENT AND ACADEMIC BODIES, IN LINE WITH FEDERAL LAW N. 12,608, WHICH INSTITUTED THE NATIONAL CIVIL DEFENSE AND PROTECTION POLICY (PNPDEC). THE GENERAL OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH IS TO EVAL"@pt ;
