    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOGRAFIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13009> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE WORK OF GEOMORPHOLOGY IS TO INVESTIGATE THE PROCESSES THAT SHAPE THE RELIEF OF EARTH'S SURFACE, SO THIS RESEARCH INVOLVES THE EVOLUTIONARY UNDERSTANDING OF THE PHENOMENA PARTICIPATING IN THIS CONSTRUCTION. THE LANDSCAPE ASSSEMBLAGESS OF THE CANHOTO RIVER WATERSHED, IN THE AGRESTE REGION OF THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO, WERE INVESTIGATED, AS WELL AS THEIR DYNAMIC INTERACTION WITH ONE ANOTHER AND THE MORPHOTECTONIC INFLUENCE, AIMING AT THE DEVELOPMENT OF QUALITATIVE LANDSCAPE EVOLUTIONARY MODELS. T"@pt ;
