    capes:hasAbstract "THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS THESIS WAS TO ANALYZE THE IMPLICATIONS OF THE INTEGRATED AND SUSTAINABLE MANAGEMENT OF WATER RESOURCES OF TRANSBOUNDARY HYDROGRAPHIC BASINS SHARED, HAVING AS OBJECT OF STUDY DOWNSTREAM OF THE LIMPOPO RIVER BASIN, CALLED IN THIS WORK AS CHOKWÉ MICROBASIN, ESTABLISHING AN ARTICULATION BETWEEN DIFFERENT SYSTEMS: POLICIES, LAWS, STRUCTURES, VALUES, LINKED TO DIFFERENT COUNTRIES, IS UNDOUBTEDLY ONE OF THE GREAT CHALLENGES THAT WE STILL HAVE TODAY IN THE MANAGEMENT OF WATER "@pt ;
