    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOGRAFIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13013> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SOCIAL GENDER RELATIONS IN THE COUNTRYSIDE AND IN PEASANT FAMILY FARMING ARE CONSTITUTED AS UNEQUAL AND CONSERVATIVELY HIERARCHICAL POWER RELATIONS, IN SUCH A WAY THAT THEY NEGLECT THE ROLE AND SOCIAL AND POLITICAL IMPORTANCE OF WOMEN IN THE ORGANIZATIONAL PROCESSES AND DYNAMICS OF LIFE, WORK AND SOCIETY. PEASANT ECONOMY. ¿¿ BASED ON THE ABOVE, THIS RESEARCH ANALYZES THE PARTICIPATION AND EXPERIENCE OF PEASANT WOMEN AND RURAL WORKERS IN THE PROCESS OF PRODUCTION AND RESIGNIFICATION OF AGRICULTUR"@pt ;
