<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13391> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AS HUMAN BEINGS DEVELOPED AGRICULTURE, HUMAN CIVILIZATION WAS MODIFIED. INNOVATIONS IN THE WORLD'S AGRICULTURE HAVE TURNED THIS ACTIVITY INTO A MAJOR ENERGY DRAIN. IN THIS WAY, THE AGRICULTURAL SECTOR BECOME HEAVILY DEPENDENT ON ENERGY PRICES THROUGH THE COST OF TRANSPORT, FERTILIZERS, PESTICIDES AND FOOD PROCESSING. ENERGY PRICES ALSO AFFECT THE FOOD MARKET BY INDUCING POLICIES THAT DIVERT FOOD CROPS TO THE PRODUCTION OF BIOFUELS. THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN OIL PRICES AND AGRICULTURAL COMMODITY ("@pt ;
