<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13469> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: MOST CHRONIC DISEASES CAN BE CONTROLLED BY THE USE OF MEDICINES, TAKING INTO CONSIDERATION THAT ACCESS AND APPROPRIATE USE ARE FUNDAMENTAL REQUIREMENTS FOR SUCCESSFUL TREATMENT. AMONG THE RESULTS THAT DIRECTLY INFLUENCE THE BENEFITS OF MEDICATION, WE SHOULD HIGHLIGHT THE ADHERENCE TO DRUG TREATMENT. BY CONSIDERING THE POSSIBLE BARRIERS TO TREATMENT ADHERENCE, A SPECIFIC QUESTIONNAIRE WAS DEVELOPED TO IDENTIFY THEM, THE ADHERENCE BARRIERS QUESTIONNAIRE (ABQ). THIS INSTRUMENT AIMS TO"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "17NOV2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ADAPTAÇÃO TRANSCULTURAL E VALIDAÇÃO DO ADHERENCE BARRIERS QUESTIONNAIRE PARA USO NO BRASIL"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/HIRLA_VANESSA_SOARES_DE_ARAUJO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ENFERMAGEM_-_FESP-UPE_-_UEPB> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13470> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PRADO, ADRIANA VITORINO ARRUDA. ADHERENCE TO ANTIRETROVIRAL THERAPY FOR PEOPLE LIVING WITH HIV / AIDS AND ITS ASSOCIATION WITH QUALITY OF LIFE. 2016. 104 F. DISSERTAÇÃO. FACULDADE NOSSA SENHORA DAS GRAÇAS, UNIVERSIDADE DE PERNAMBUCO, RECIFE, 2016. SEVERAL FACTORS MAY INFLUENCE ADHERENCE IN ANTIRETROVIRAL THERAPY (ART). ITS IRREGULAR USE MAY CAUSE THERAPEUTIC FAILURE, THREATENING THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE TREATMENT, INCREASING MORBIMORTALITY AND REDUCING VIRAL SUPPRESSION, WORSENING THE QUALITY OF"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "23FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ADESÃO À TERAPIA ANTIRRETROVIRAL DE PESSOAS VIVENDO COM HIV/AIDS E SUA ASSOCIAÇÃO COM A QUALIDADE DE VIDA"@pt ;
