    capes:hasAbstract "THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO MAKE AN INVENTORY OF THE MARINE PLANKTON FLORA AND TO IDENTIFY PATTERNS OF GEOGRAPHIC DISTRIBUTION OF THE SPECIES IN THE COAST OF PERNAMBUCO, RELATING THEM WITH CHLOROPHYLL DATA AND HYDROLOGICAL PARAMETERS (TEMPERATURE, SALINITY, PH, NUTRIENT SALTS AND OD) THROUGH PRIOR CONSULTATION IN ARTICLES, DISSERTATIONS AND THESES OF 35 AREAS. IT WAS VERIFIED THAT THE PLANKTONIC FLORA IS RICH AND DIVERSIFIED, CONSTITUTED BY 1.061 SPECIES DISTRIBUTED IN 10 PHYLA (BACILLARI"@pt ;
