    capes:hasAbstract "COGENERATION OF HEAT AND POWER OR THE COMBINED HEAT AND POWER (CHP) MODE OF OPERATION OF POWER PLANTS HAS LONG BEEN USED IN VARIOUS INDUSTRIES AROUND THE WORLD. THE PURPOSE OF THIS METHOD IS TO OPTIMIZE ENERGY FLOWS AND REDUCE ENERGY LOSSES, ENABLING THE IMPROVEMENT OF ENERGY EFFICIENCY (FUEL), ENERGY SECURITY AND REDUCTION OF INDUSTRIAL CO2 EMISSIONS. BASED ON THIS PREMISE, NUCLEAR COGENERATION EMERGES AS AN EXCELLENT ALTERNATIVE TO THE USE OF NUCLEAR ENERGY. NUCLEAR COGENERATION IS THE SIMULTA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "23FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAÇÃO DA VIABILIDADE DA DESSALINIZAÇÃO DE ÁGUA DO MAR EMPREGANDO O REATOR NUCLEAR AP1000 COMO FONTE DE ENERGIA"@pt ;
