<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13756> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "POLY(METHYL METHACRYLATE) OR PMMA IS A POLYMER USED IN THE MEDICAL, PHARMACEUTICAL, AUTOMOTIVE, LENS MANUFACTURING AND OTHER DIVERSE APPLICATIONS INVOLVING EXPOSURE TO IONIZING RADIATION. HOWEVER, THE PROCESS OF RADIOLYSIS IN PMMA RESULTS IN THE SCISSION OF THE POLYMER CHAIN AND CONSEQUENTLY IN THE DECREASE OF THE MOLAR MASS, AFFECTING THE PROPERTIES OF THE MATERIAL. IN VIEW OF THIS, THE IMPORTANCE OF CONDUCTING RESEARCH THAT ENABLES THE MANUFACTURE OF MATERIALS THAT ARE RESISTANT TO RADIATION A"@pt ;
