    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/TECNOLOGIAS_ENERGÉTICAS_E_NUCLEARES> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13757> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "RADON IS A NATURALLY OCCURRING, ALPHA-EMITTING, RADIOACTIVE GAS FROM NATURAL RADIOACTIVE SERIES. RN-222, WHICH IS FROM THE U-238 SERIES, IS THE MOST RELEVANT FROM AN ENVIRONMENTAL POINT OF VIEW, DUE TO THE ISOTOPIC ABUNDANCE OF ITS PRECURSOR IN THE COMPOSITION OF NATURAL URANIUM, AND ITS LONGEST PHYSICAL HALF-LIFE OF 3.82 DAYS. THIS GAS AND ITS PROGENY HAVE SIGNIFICANT CONTRIBUTIONS TO HUMAN INTERNAL EXPOSURE. IN THE STUDY, A SIMULATOR WAS DEVELOPED TO CHARACTERIZE AND VALIDATE RADON LEVELS IN A"@pt ;
