<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13768> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "A PROPOSAL UNDER DEVELOPMENT IS THE APPLICATION OF SOLID-STATE DOSIMETRY SO THAT IT IS PART OF THE SAFEGUARDS PROTOCOL EMPLOYED BY THE INTERNATIONAL ATOMIC ENERGY AGENCY (IAEA). THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS PAPER WAS TO EVALUATE THE LUMINESCENT RESPONSES OF CALCIUM FLUORIDE DOPED WITH RARE EARTHS AND CODOPED WITH METALS BY COMBUSTION SYNTHESIS IN SOLUTION. THE BEST LUMINESCENT RESPONSES FOR THE 100 MGY DOSE WERE CAF2:CE:AL AND CAF2:TB:LI. THE CAF2:CE:AL SAMPLES WITH ALUMINUM CONCENTRATION OF 0.005 MOL "@pt ;
