<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13769> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SOIL WATER INFILTRATION IS A COMPLEX HYDROLOGICAL PROCESS THAT HAS A HIGH DEPENDENCE ON HYDRODYNAMIC PROPERTIES SUCH AS THE RETENTION CURVE AND THE HYDRAULIC CONDUCTIVITY CURVE. IN THE CONTEXT OF THE CAATINGA BIOME, KNOWLEDGE OF THE HYDRODYNAMIC PROPERTIES OF THE VADOSE ZONE IS STILL SCARCE. DETERMINING THE HYDRODYNAMIC PROPERTIES FOR THIS BIOME IS OF FUNDAMENTAL IMPORTANCE FOR MODELING AND IMPROVING THE KNOWLEDGE OF WATER TRANSFER PROCESSES, AS WELL AS FOR THE DYNAMICS OF CARBON AND ENERGY BALA"@pt ;
