<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13773> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FOOD WASTE (FW) EMITS GREENHOUSE GASES INTO THE ENVIRONMENT AND CONTRIBUTES TO SOIL AND GROUNDWATER CONTAMINATION. THIS MATERIAL, HOWEVER, HAS EXCELLENT POTENTIAL TO PRODUCE BIOFUELS AND BIOPRODUCTS, AND ITS IMPACTS CAN BE MINIMIZED THROUGH ITS ENERGY USE. IN THIS SENSE, THE PRESENT WORK AIMED TO INVESTIGATE THE USE OF FW TO PRODUCE FERMENTABLE SUGARS AND BIOETHANOL. USING CELLULASES AND AMYLASES AS DIGESTIVE ENZYMES, FW ENZYMATIC HYDROLYSIS ASSAYS WERE PERFORMED WITH AND WITHOUT A PREVIOUS LIPI"@pt ;
