<http://example.com/capes#thesis/13781> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SCHISTOSOMIASIS AFFECTS 236.6 MILLION PEOPLE IN TROPICAL AND SUBTROPICAL REGIONS OF THE WORLD, MAINLY IN BASIC COMMUNITIES WITHOUT ACCESS TO SANITATION. IN BRAZIL, SCHISTOSOMA MANSONI IS THE ETIOLOGICAL AGENT OF SCHISTOSOMIASIS AND SNAILS OF THE GENUS BIOMPHALARIA SPP ARE THE MAIN INTERMEDIATE HOST. THUS, IN THE ABSENCE OF HEALTH POLICIES, ONE OF THE STRATEGIES TO REDUCE THE PREVALENCE OF SCHISTOSOMIASIS, ADVOCATED BY THE WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION (WHO) IS THE POPULATION CONTROL OF B. GLABRATA. "@pt ;
