    capes:hasAbstract "GIVEN THE ADVANTAGES OF NATURAL PIGMENTS OVER SYNTHETICS AND THE GROWING WORLDWIDE TREND FOR NATURAL AND SUSTAINABLE PRODUCTS, THE SEARCH FOR BIOLOGICAL SOURCES THAT GENERATE BIOACTIVE PIGMENTS IN SIGNIFICANT QUANTITIES HAS INCREASED SUBSTANTIALLY. FILAMENTOUS FUNGI ARE POTENTIAL PRODUCERS OF BIOACTIVE METABOLITES, SUCH AS PIGMENTS. THE PRESENT STUDY AIMED TO EVALUATE THE USE OF AGRO-INDUSTRIAL RESIDUES (BANANA AND PASSION FRUIT PEEL) AS A SUBSTRATE OF CULTURE MEDIA FOR GROWTH AND PRODUCTION OF "@pt ;
