<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14054> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE YEAST BRETTANOMYCES BRUXELLENSIS IS FREQUENTLY FOUND IN INDUSTRIAL ALCOHOLIC FERMENTATION PROCESSES, ALTHOUGH, IN MOST CASES, IT IS CONSIDERED A CONTAMINATING MICROORGANISM. IN THE PRODUCTION OF FUEL ETHANOL, FOR EXAMPLE, IT IS ASSOCIATED WITH LOW INDUSTRIAL PRODUCTIVITY AS IT COMPETES WITH SACCHAROMYCES CEREVISIAE FOR THE SUBSTRATE. ON THE OTHER HAND, THIS YEAST IS CLASSIFIED AS CRABTREE POSITIVE, WHICH INDICATES ITS ABILITY TO PRODUCE ETHANOL BY FERMENTATION EVEN IN THE PRESENCE OF OXYGEN."@pt ;
