<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14060> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE TEXTILE SECTOR REPRESENTS IMPACTS ON THE COUNTRY'S ECONOMY. HOWEVER, THE TEXTILE INDUSTRY, PRODUCES HIGH VOLUMES OF EFFLUENTS THAT NEED PROPER TREATMENTS. THEREFORE, SUSTAINABLE AND INEXPENSIVE TREATMENT ALTERNATIVES NEED TO BE PROSPECTED. THUS, THIS PROJECT AIMED TO PROSPECT MICROORGANISMS CAPABLE OF BIODEGRADING EFFLUENTS OF THE TEXTILE INDUSTRY LOCATED IN THE INDUSTRIAL TÊXTIL POLE OF PERNAMBUCO. SIX MICROORGANISMS WERE EVALUATED, 4 FUNGI (F24 = ASPERGILLUS SPP., F48 = ASPERGILLUS SPP., F"@pt ;
