<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14479> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "RECENT DATA INDICATE A STRONG ASSOCIATION BETWEEN THE CURRENT OUTBREAK OF ZIKA VIRUS (ZIKV) INFECTION AND A MARKED INCREASE IN THE DETECTION OF MICROCEPHALY AND FETAL MALFORMATIONS, ALERTING HEALTH SURVEILLANCE IN BRAZIL. MICROCEPHALY IS A CONDITION IN WHICH THE CHILD'S HEAD CIRCUMFERENCE IS SMALLER THAN IN CHILDREN OF THE SAME AGE AND SEX, USUALLY WITH NEUROLOGICAL SEQUELAE. DUE TO THE COMPLEXITY OF THE INFECTION CAUSED BY THE ZIKA VIRUS, ITS SEQUELS HAVE NOT BEEN FULLY ELUCIDATED. SINCE DENTAL"@pt ;
