    capes:hasAbstract "OPTICAL COHERENCE TOMOGRAPHY (OCT) IS A HIGH RESOLUTION NONINVASIVE DIAGNOSTIC TECHNIQUE THAT GENERATES SECTIONAL IMAGES OF INTERNAL STRUCTURES BY THE INCIDENCE AND PROPAGATION OF A LOW COHERENCE LIGHT BEAM. ITS APPLICATIONS IN DENTISTRY INCLUDES FROM THE DIAGNOSIS OF CARIOUS LESIONS TO THE ANALYSIS OF DENTAL MATERIALS BEHAVIOR. THIS THESIS APPLIED OCT TO EVALUATE (1) THE INFLUENCE OF THE MONOMERIC COMPOSITION (UDMA / TEGDMA) ON THE LINEAR POLYMERIZATION SHRINKAGE AND IN THE THERMAL DEGRADATION "@pt ;
