<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14486> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO COMPARE THE EFFECTS OF DIPYRONE ADMINISTRATION ON 1000 MG AND 500 MG DOSAGES, VIA ORAL, COADMINISTERED WITH NIMESULIDE IN PAIN CONTROL AFTER REMOVAL OF LOWER THIRD MOLARS. A PROSPECTIVE, RANDOMIZED, TRIPLE-BLIND CLINICAL TRIAL WAS DEVELOPED WITH A TOTAL SAMPLE OF 26 PATIENTS. THROUGH THE SPLIT-MOUTH METHOD, THE PATIENTS UNDERWENT TWO SIMILAR SURGERIES UNDER LOCAL ANESTHESIA, AND AT DIFFERENT TIMES. THE MEDICATIONS USED WERE RANDOMIZED AND ALLOCATED TO 2 GROUPS:"@pt ;
