<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14487> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENTATION FORMAT OF THIS THESIS IS A SET OF FOUR ARTICLES, THE FIRST TWO BEING INTEGRATIVE REVIEWS OF THE LITERATURE, AND THE LAST TWO THE RESULTS OF THE RESEARCH. OBJECTIVES: TO REVIEW SCIENTIFIC EVIDENCE ON THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN MALOCCLUSION AND AUDITORY TUBE DYSFUNCTION (ARTICLE 1), AND ON THE IMPACT OF MALOCCLUSIONS ON THE ORAL HEALTH-RELATED QUALITY OF LIFE (OHRQOL) OF CHILDREN AND THEIR FAMILIES (ARTICLE 2). THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN MALOCCLUS"@pt ;
