<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14491> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "OBJECTIVE: THE OBJECTIVE OF THE STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE IN VITRO RESISTANCE OF ADHESIVE BONDING SHEAR EXTRUSION - PUSH-OUT - FIBERGLASS PINS IN DIFFERENT ROOT THIRDS OF RESIN CEMENTS AND ADHESIVE SYSTEMS WITH PHOSPHATE MONOMER (MDP). METHODS: THIRTY-TWO WERE USED (32) ROOTS OF BOVINE INCISORS DIVIDED INTO 04 GROUPS (N = 08) WITH THE FOLLOWING RESIN CEMENTS AND ADHESIVE SYSTEMS: G1 RELYX ULTIMATE (UK) + SINGLE BOND UNIVERSAL (SB); G2 - CLEAR FILL LUTING AS (CF) + SINGLE BOND ADHESIVE; G3 - CLEAR FI"@pt ;
