<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14826> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "RESPONSIBLE FOR MILLIONS OF INFECTIONS AND DEATHS AROUND THE WORLD, COVID-19 REMAINS WITH GAPS IN ITS UNDERSTANDING. THE SECOND SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME CORONAVIRUS (SARS-COV-2) PROVED TO BE A COMPLEX INFECTIOUS AGENT, RESPONSIBLE FOR EXTRAPULMONARY MANIFESTATIONS, INCLUDING CARDIOVASCULAR CHANGES. THE ANGIOTENSIN-CONVERTING ENZYME 2 (ACE-2), ONE OF THE MAIN TARGETS OF THE VIRUS, IS ABUNDANTLY EXPRESSED ON THE SURFACE OF THE VASCULAR ENDOTHELIUM, IMPLYING THAT VESSELS MAY BE SUSCEPTIBLE"@pt ;
