    capes:hasAbstract "ABSTRACT OBJECTIVE: TO INVESTIGATE THE QUALITY OF LIFE (QOL) OF PATIENTS WHO DEVELOPED SEVERE COMPENSATORY HYPERHIDROSIS, AFTER SYMPATHECTOMY FOR LOCALIZED SWEATING, WITH A NEW APPROACH USING THE MODIFIED TECHNIQUE OF BILATERAL THORACIC SYMPATHECTOMY AT THE R5-R8 LEVEL. METHODS: EIGHTEEN PATIENTS WITH SEVERE COMPENSATORY HYPERHIDROSIS UNDERWENT THE MODIFIED PROCEDURE OF BILATERAL THORACIC SYMPATHECTOMY AT THE LEVEL OF R5-R8, BY VIDEO THORACOSCOPY, LOCALIZED IN THE PALMAR AND AXILLARY REGION, IN "@pt ;
