<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14828> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ABSTRACT PARKINSON'S DISEASE IMPACTS INDIVIDUALS AND THEIR FAMILIES, AS WELL AS THE HEALTH AND SOCIAL SECURITY SYSTEMS. MOTOR SYMPTOMS ARE USUALLY PRECEDED BY NON-MOTOR SYMPTOMS, WHICH CAN BE EARLY MARKERS OF THE DISEASE. OLFACTORY LOSS, PRESENT IN THE VAST MAJORITY OF AFFECTED INDIVIDUALS, HAVE BEEN ASSOCIATED WITH THE DEVELOPMENT OF DEMENTIA AFTER FEW YEARS, BUT THE RELATIONSHIP WITH THE PROGRESSION OF MOTOR SYMPTOMS IS NOT WELL ESTABLISHED. THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EXTRACT PATTERNS WITHIN"@pt ;
