<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14830> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ABSTRACT INTRODUCTION: NEOADJUVANT CHEMOTHERAPY, USED BEFORE SURGICAL TREATMENT, HAS BECOME THE STANDARD FOR INFLAMMATORY AND LOCALLY ADVANCED TUMORS, ALLOWING A SURGICAL APPROACH THAT ALLOWS FOR GREATER CONSERVATION OF BREAST TISSUE. THERE IS EVIDENCE THAT THE CHANGE IN WEIGHT DURING TREATMENT WITH CHEMOTHERAPY MAY BE RELATED TO REDUCED SURVIVAL AND INCREASED RISK OF DISEASE RECURRENCE, THROUGH THE PROLIFERATION OF NEOPLASTIC CELLS INDUCED BY OBESITY. OBJECTIVE: THE RESEARCH AIMED TO DETERMINE "@pt ;
