<http://example.com/capes#thesis/14915> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CIVIL PROCEDURE CODE DETERMINES IN ART. 15, THAT ITS PROVISIONS ARE APPLIED IN ADMINISTRATIVE PROCEEDINGS, OF WHICH THE TAX ADMINISTRATIVE PROCEEDINGS ARE A TYPE, IN A SUBSIDIARY AND SUPPLEMENTARY MANNER. HOWEVER, CPC IS AN ORDINARY FEDERAL LAW, PUBLISHED UNDER NO 13,105 OF 2015, AND ITS VALIDITY AND INCIDENCE BASIS IS NOT CLEAR FOR AUTOMATIC OBSERVATION AND APPLICATION BY SUBNATIONAL ENTITIES DUE TO THE FEDERATIVE AUTONOMY OF EACH STATE. THE APPLICABILITY OF THE CPC IN THE TAX ADMINISTRATIV"@pt ;
