    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENT DISSERTATION PROPOSES TO INVESTIGATE HOW POPULISM IN BRAZIL, AS OF 2019, HAS WEAKENED THE FEDERAL SUPREME COURT. FOR THE ANALYSIS, IT WILL BE CONSIDERED AS A SET OF BASIC PRINCIPLES BY GOVERNMENTS THAT HAVE ANTI-INSTITUTIONAL AND ANTI-PLURALISM CHARACTERISTICS. WHILE A-INSTITUTIONALITY ESTABLISHES ITSELF AS A MOVEMENT OF DEFENDERS AS DEMOCRATIC INSTITUTIONS, ANTI-PLURALISM SEEKS TO PREVENT DEMOCRATIC PLURALISM, IN ADDITION TO ATTACKING DIVERSITY. IN ORDER TO ANSWER THE CANDIDATE'S RE"@pt ;
