    capes:hasAbstract "SCENARIO: OBESITY IS A COMPLEX AND MULTIFACTORIAL CHRONIC DISEASE, WHICH CONSISTS IN THE UNNECESSARY STORAGE OF ENERGY IN FAT CELLS. SEVERAL COUNTRIES ARE EXPERIENCING A RAPID INCREASE IN RISK FACTORS FOR NONCOMMUNICABLE DISEASES SUCH AS OBESITY. THIS IS ASSOCIATED WITH SECONDARY MORBIDITY AND INCREASED INSULIN RESISTANCE, DIABETES, HYPERTENSION AND DYSLIPIDEMIA. THEREFORE, THE NUMBER OF BARIATRIC SURGERIES BETWEEN 2012 AND 2017 INCREASED BY 47.7%. IN BRAZIL, IN 2017, 105,642 THOUSAND SURGERIES "@pt ;
