<http://example.com/capes#thesis/15420> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE SETTLEMENT OF THE NORTHEAST REGION OF BRAZIL IS CONSIDERED A REMARKABLE EXAMPLE OF MASS MIGRATION, RESULTING IN DRAMATIC MODIFICATION OF THE GENETIC MAKE-UP OF THE LOCAL POPULATION. IT BELIEVED THAT ABOUT 46 MILION EUROPEANS AND 10 MILION AFRICAN HAVE LANDED IN SOUTH AMERICA UNTIL THE EARLY 20TH CENTURY. HOWEVER, THIS CONTINENT ALREADY INHABITED BY INDIGENOUS PEOPLES. IN THE STUDY OF HUMAN POPULATIONS, THE USE OF MICROSATELLITE MARKERS OF THE Y CHROMOSOME (Y-STRS) HAS BEEN GAINING PROMINENCE"@pt ;
