    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOTECNOLOGIA_-_REDE_RENORBIO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/15428> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "STAPHYLOCOCCUS SPP. WITH ABILITY TO FORM BIOFILMS ARE INCREASINGLY KNOWN TO CAUSE PERSISTENT INTRAMAMMARY INFECTIONS AND THE SEARCH FOR ALTERNATIVES TO INHIBIT THE DEVELOPMENT OF BIOFILMS IS CRITICAL, ESPECIALLY WHEN USING PLANTS WITH THERAPEUTIC POTENTIAL. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE ANTIMICROBIAL, SYNERGISTIC AND ANTIBIOFILM EFFECT OF THE CRUDE ETHANOLIC EXTRACT OF MIMOSA TENUIFLORA (CEEMT) AGAINST STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS BIOFILM PRODUCERS, IN ADDITION TO VERIFY THE PRESENCE "@pt ;
