<http://example.com/capes#thesis/15560> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ATEMOIEIRA IS A HYBRID RESULTING FROM THE CROSSING OF TWO SPECIES OF THE ANNONA GENUS (A. CHERIMOLA AND A. SQUAMOSA) THAT ARE KNOWN FOR THE RICHNESS OF BIOLOGICALLY ACTIVE COMPOUNDS. DUE TO THE INCREASING NUMBER OF NEW CASES OF CANCER EACH YEAR AND AGGRESSIVE AND OFTEN INEFFICIENT TREATMENTS, IT IS NECESSARY TO SEARCH FOR NEW EFFECTIVE CYTOTOXIC COMPOUNDS. THE USE OF HYPHENATED TECHNIQUES OF SEPARATION AND IDENTIFICATION OF PLANT MATRIX MOLECULES HAS BEEN HIGHLY VALUED, SINCE THEY CAN ACCELERATE"@pt ;
