<http://example.com/capes#thesis/16254> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COMBINATORIAL REASONING PLAYS AN IMPORTANT ROLE IN THE COGNITIVE DEVELOPMENT OF CHILDREN AND ADOLESCENTS. THE PRESENT STUDY, BASED ON THE THEORY OF CONCEPTUAL FIELDS, INVESTIGATED THE EFFECT OF MAKING THE INVARIANTS EXPLICIT ON THE ERRORS EMPLOYED BY CHILDREN IN SOLVING PROBLEMS OF ARRANGEMENT, PERMUTATION AND COMBINATION IN TWO CONDITIONS: WITH STATEMENTS THAT MADE THE INVARIANTS EXPLICIT OR WITH STATEMENTS THAT LEFT THE INVARIANTS IMPLIED. THE STUDY WAS BUILT FROM THE SILVA ET AL. WERE DIVIDED"@pt ;
