<http://example.com/capes#thesis/16358> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE SET OF ELEMENTS KNOWN AS GEOMORPHOLOGICAL HERITAGE IS COMPOSED BY TOPOGRAPHIC RELIEF FORMS, GENESIS PROCESSES AND THE EVOLUTION OF THE GEOMORPHOLOGICAL LANDSCAPE, WHICH ARE ASSIGNED SOME VALUES (SCIENTIFIC, TOURISTIC, ARTISTIC, DIDACTIC, AMONG OTHERS), AND IT NEEDS TO BE PRESERVED WHEN IT PRESENTS SOME EXCEPTIONAL CHARACTERISTICS. THIS RESEARCH HAS AS ITS MAIN PURPOSE A SEARCH DEVELOPMENT OF AN EVALUATION METHODOLOGY ON GEOMORPHOLOGICAL HERITAGE TO DEVELOP A NEW PROPOSITION TO BE APPLIED IN "@pt ;
