<http://example.com/capes#thesis/16363> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE REGIONAL IMBALANCES FOUND IN BRAZIL COME FROM ITS HISTORICAL PROCESS OF TERRITORIAL FORMATION. AT TIMES, THE ECONOMIC CYCLES FOCUSED ON THE EXTERNAL OR INTERNAL MARKET FAVOURING CERTAIN SCALES LEFT THE MARGIN OF THE PROCESS LARGE TERRITORIAL PORTIONS AND SOCIAL STRATA, CREATING A PASSIVE OF BASIC DEMANDS THAT ARE NOT MET IN MOST OF THE COUNTRY'S INTERIOR REGIONS. IN THE STATE OF RIO GRANDE DO SUL IT IS POSSIBLE TO VERIFY THIS PHENOMENON BY APPROACHING ITS HETEROGENEOUS HISTORY OF OCCUPATION "@pt ;
