    capes:hasAbstract "QUANTUM DOTS (QDS) ARE SEMICONDUCTOR NANOCRYSTALS WITH EXCELLENT OPTICAL PROPERTIES DUE TO THEIR QUANTUM CONFINEMENT REGIME. THEY HAVE FOUND APPLICATIONS IN VARIOUS FIELDS, SUCH AS BIOMEDICINE, PARTICULARLY AS DIAGNOSTIC AND THERANOSTIC AGENTS. FOR EXAMPLE, THE ASSOCIATION OF FLUORESCENT QDS WITH GD3+ COMPLEXES, ALREADY USED CLINICALLY, RESULTS IN CONTRAST AGENTS (CAS) FOR MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING (MRI), THUS ENABLING THEIR USE IN MORE THAN ONE IMAGING TECHNIQUE. THE DEVELOPMENT OF THESE NANOP"@pt ;
