<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1712> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "METAL-ORGANIC NETWORKS (MOFS) ARE HYBRID MATERIALS THAT HAVE HIGH POTENTIAL FOR APPLICATION IN SEVERAL AREAS OF RESEARCH. IT IS POSSIBLE TO OBTAIN THESE MATERIALS THROUGH DIFFERENT SYNTHETIC ROUTES, WHICH IN A WAY DIRECTLY INFLUENCE THEIR PROPERTIES, SUCH AS POROSITY, CRYSTALLINITY AND STRUCTURE. IN GENERAL, THESE METHODOLOGIES ARE WELL ESTABLISHED, HOWEVER, THEY HAVE DISADVANTAGES, SUCH AS LONG SYNTHESIS TIMES, THE NEED TO SUPPLY HIGH ENERGY AND/OR GENERATION OF BYPRODUCTS. THEREFORE, THE UNCON"@pt ;
