<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17124> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SUPERABSORBENT HYDROGELS ARE THREE-DIMENSIONAL POLYMERIC WEBS THAT ARE CAPABLE OF ABSORBING LARGE QUANTITIES (MORE THAN 100% OF THEIR INITIAL MASS) OF AQUEOUS SOLUTIONS IN A SHORT TIME (FEW MINUTES) AND THESE MAINTAIN THEIR STRUCTURE WITHOUT DISSOLVING. THESE HYDROGELS AREFORMED OF POLYMERS, WHICH MAY BE BONDED TOGETHER BY PHYSICAL OR CHEMICAL LINKAGES. THIS WORK AIMED TO DEVELOP AND CHARACTERIZE SUPERABSORBENT HYDROGELS PRODUCED FROM NATURAL POLYMER MATRICES BY MEANS OF POLYIONIC COMPLEXATION, "@pt ;
