        <http://example.com/capes#author/MARCIANA_BIZERRA_DE_MORAIS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOTECNOLOGIA_-_REDE_RENORBIO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17211> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COLOMBIA IS THE COUNTRY IN TROPICAL AMERICA WITH THE GREATER RICHNESS OF LIVERWORTS, 705 SPECIES. THIS DIVERSITY IS ATTRIBUTED TO THE VARIATION OF DIFFERENT ENVIRONMENTAL FACTORS, AMONG THEM, THE LARGE ALTITUDINAL RANGE OF 0-5000 M. ALTHOUGH NUMEROUS STUDIES HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT ON THE TAXONOMY AND DIVERSITY OF LIVERWORTS IN THE COUNTRY, FUNCTIONAL DIVERSITY IN THE ALTITUDINAL GRADIENT IS AN UNEXPLORED TOPIC. MOST STUDIES ON PLANT DIVERSITY IN THE ALTITUDINAL GRADIENT HAVE CONFIRMED AS A GENERA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "24FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DIFERENCIAÇÃO TAXONÔMICA E FUNCIONAL DE HEPÁTICAS (MARCHANTIOPHYTA) NO GRADIENTE ALTITUDINAL DA COLÔMBIA"@pt ;
