<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17218> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SPECIES THAT OCCUR IN DRY ENVIRONMENTS CAN ADJUST THEIR MORPHOPHYSIOLOGICAL BEHAVIOUR, ADOPTING MORE CONSERVATIVE STRATEGIES, IT IS, RELATED TO THE SAFETY OF TRANSPORT AND ASSIMILATION PROCESSES, OR ACQUISITIVE, ASSOCIATED WITH THE EFFICIENCY OF THESE PROCESSES. THUS, SPECIES DISTRIBUTED IN A GRADIENT OF WATER AVAILABILITY MAY PRESENT DIFFERENT PHENOTYPES DEPENDING ON THE CONDITIONS TO WHICH THEY ARE SUBMITTED. LEAF AND VASCULAR TISSUES ARE STRONGLY RELATED TO THESE CHANGES AND TO WATER USE EFFI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "19JUL2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ESTUDO MORFOFISIOLÓGICO EM ESPÉCIES LENHOSAS SOB DIFERENTES DISPONIBILIDADES HÍDRICAS NA CAATINGA"@pt ;
