    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17225> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "EXTENSIVE LIVESTOCK IN NATURAL ECOSYSTEMS CAN REDUCE PLANT REGENERATION CAPACITY AND INDUCE ECOSYSTEMS TO PERMANENT STATES OF DEGRADATION, ESPECIALLY IN AREAS OF DRY FORESTS WHERE THESE PRACTICES ARE CONSTANT AND PROVIDES THE SUBSISTENCE OF HUMAN POPULATIONS. CONSIDERING STUDIES OF HOW THE GRAZING OF LARGE HERBIVORES IMPACTS REGENERATION MECHANISMS THAT PROVIDES THE RESILIENCE OF THESE FORESTS (IE, SEED BANK AND SEEDLING BANK), THIS THESIS ADDRESSES THE EFFECT OF GOATS CREATED EXTENSIVELY IN THE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "24FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFLUÊNCIA DE CAPRINOS NA REGENERAÇÃO DA CAATINGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LAYS_KLECIA_SILVA_LINS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17226> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN SEASONALLY DRY TROPICAL FORESTS (FTSS) SUCH AS THE CAATINGA, SOME WOODY SPECIES USE THE REGROWTH CAPACITY AS A WAY OF TOLERATING ANTHROPOGENIC STRESSES. THIS IS IMPORTANT IN RELATION TO SLASH AND BURN AGRICULTURE (ACQ), A HISTORICAL PRACTICE, KNOWN FOR GENERATING SEVERE IMPACTS ON THE SOIL AND PLANT COMMUNITY. IN THIS SENSE, ANALYZING HOW THESE SPECIES ECOPHYSIOLOGICALLY MODULATE THEIR RESPONSES TO THIS STRESS CAN HELP TO UNDERSTAND CURRENT AND FUTURE PATTERNS AND DYNAMICS FOR FTSS. THUS, THE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28APR2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "O IMPACTO DA AGRICULTURA DE CORTE E QUEIMA EM ATRIBUTOS ECOFISIOLÓGICOS DE ESPÉCIES LENHOSAS DA CAATINGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ZILDA_ELLEN_BAIAO_NEVES> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17227> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE RICH FLORA OF BRAZILIAN BIOMES PROBABLY INCLUDES MANY SPECIES CAPABLE OF BOTH NOURISHING AND PREVENTING OR TREATING DISEASES WHOSE POTENTIAL IS STILL LITTLE EXPLORED. BRAZIL ALSO HAS A GREAT DIVERSITY OF TRADITIONAL PEOPLES, INCLUDING QUILOMBOLA PEOPLES, WHICH ARE DESCENDANTS OF AFRICAN SLAVES WHO MANAGED TO ESCAPE CAPTIVITY AND TAKE REFUGE FAR FROM THE URBAN CENTERS. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO BRING INFORMATION ABOUT THE RICHNESS OF KNOWLEDGE OF QUILOMBOLA PEOPLE ABOUT MULTIFUNCTION"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
