<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17337> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AMONG THE COMPOUNDS KNOWN AS NITROPHENOLICS, WHOSE APPLICATIONS ARE PRESENT IN OUR DAILY LIVES, 4-NITROPHENOL (4-NP) STANDS OUT AS A SERIOUS ENVIRONMENTAL CONTAMINANT. 4- NP CAN BE REDUCED TO THE SAFER COMPOUND 4-AMINOPHENOL USING SILVER NANOCATALYSTS. THUS, THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS THE DEVELOPMENT OF SILVER NANOPARTICLES (AGNPS) WITH DIFFERENT STABILIZERS AND SHAPES, TO EVALUATE THEIR CATALYTIC AND PHOTOCATALYTIC ACTIVITY IN THE 4-NP REDUCTION REACTION. AGNPS WERE PREPARED IN SPHERIC"@pt ;
