<http://example.com/capes#thesis/17340> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE IMPROPER DISPOSAL OF POLYMERS IS RESPONSIBLE FOR ITS ACCUMULATION IN NATURE, GENERATING GREAT ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS, SINCE DEGRADATION OF POLYMERS FROM NONRENEWABLE SOURCES IS QUITE SLOW. A VIABLE ALTERNATIVE TO MINIMIZE THIS PROBLEM IS THE TOTAL OR PARTIAL REPACEMENT OF SYNTHETIC POLYMERS BY BIODEGRADABLE POLYMERS. POLYCAPROLACTONE (PCL) IS CONSIDERED ONE OF THE MOST PROMISING POLYMERS FOR THE PRODUCTION OF BIODEGRADABLE FILM PACKAGING. THE PRESENT STUDY DEALS WITH THE PRODUCTION, CHARACTER"@pt ;
