    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/NIVOLA_BEATRIZ_MENDONCA_DE_ARRUDA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GERONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/18779> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CORONAVIRUS DISEASE 2019 PANDEMIC, DECLARED ON MARCH 11, 2020 BY THE WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION, HAS BEEN PRESENTING ITSELF AS A MAJOR PUBLIC HEALTH PROBLEM, WITH A STILL HIGH NUMBER OF DEATHS, REQUIRING MORE EXPLANATIONS ABOUT THE RISK FACTORS FOR NEGATIVE OUTCOMES. THE PRESENT STUDY AIMS TO ANALYZE THE PREDICTIVE FACTORS OF DEATH IN HOSPITALIZED ELDERLY PATIENTS WITH NEUROLOGICAL OR CARDIAC DISEASE CONCOMITANT WITH COVID-19.THIS IS A QUANTITATIVE, LONGITUDINAL, RETROSPECTIVE, UNPAIRED CASE-"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "03MAR2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "FATORES PREDITIVOS DO ÓBITO EM PACIENTES IDOSOS COM COVID-19: UM ESTUDO DE CASO CONTROLE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/NATALY_ANNES_E_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GERONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1878> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE OVERDISPERSED GENERALIZED LINEAR MODELS (MLGS) ALLOW, IN GENERAL, THAT THE DISPERSION AND THE MEAN TO BE MODELED SIMULTANEOUSLY IN THE CONTEXT OF GENERALIZED LINEAR MODELS. THE MLGS ARE VERY USEFUL FOR MODELING A DISPERSION WHEN THE VARIANCE OF THE RESPONSE VARIABLE EXCEEDS THE NOMINAL VARIANCE PREDICTED BY THE MODEL. THIS DISSERTATION HAS THREE PURPOSES. THE FIRST PURPOSE IS TO DESCRIBE IMPORTANT RESULTS ON BARTLETT AND BARTLETT-TYPE CORRECTIONS TO THE LIKELIHOOD RATIO AND SCORE STATISTICS "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "31JUL2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "CORREÇÃO TIPO-BARTLETT À ESTATÍSTICA GRADIENTE NO MODELOS LINEARES GENERALIZADOS SUPERDISPERSADOS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOAS_SILVA_DOS_SANTOS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/18780> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: BEING A VERY COMMON CONDITION IN AGING, SARCOPENIA IS RELATED TO THE REDUCTION OF MUSCLE STRENGTH AND MASS, WHICH CAN NEGATIVELY INTERFERE WITH THE AUTONOMY, FUNCTIONALITY AND QUALITY OF LIFE OF THE ELDERLY. OBJECTIVE: TO ASSESS THE IMPACT OF SARCOPENIA ON THE FUNCTIONALITY OF THE ELDERLY. METHODS: THIS IS A CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY, WHICH WAS CONDUCTED FROM DECEMBER 2020 TO JUNE 2021, AT HOSPITAL OTÁVIO DE FREITAS. THE SAMPLE CONSISTED OF 124 ELDERLY PEOPLE (= 60 YEARS), OF BOTH SEXE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "16FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "IMPACTO DA SARCOPENIA NA FUNCIONALIDADE DO IDOSO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/SHIRLEY_TAVARES_DE_OLIVEIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GERONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/18781> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "KNOWLEDGE OF INFORMATION ABOUT DIABETES HAS A GREAT IMPACT ON MAINTAINING HEALTH AND DELAYING THE ONSET OF COMPLICATIONS. NUTRITIONAL LITERACY CONSISTS OF THE ABILITY TO OBTAIN, PROCESS AND UNDERSTAND INFORMATION ABOUT NUTRITION. THE AIM OF THIS STUDY IS TO ANALYZE NUTRITIONAL LITERACY AND ASSOCIATED FACTORS IN ELDERLY PEOPLE WITH DIABETES MELLITUS. CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY, WITH AN ANALYTICAL APPROACH, DEVELOPED AT THE ENDOCRINOLOGY OUTPATIENT CLINIC OF THE HOSPITAL DAS CLÍNICAS DA UFPE, WITH 135 "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "05AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "LETRAMENTO NUTRICIONAL E FATORES ASSOCIADOS EM IDOSOS COM DIABETES"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ISABELA_CATARINA_LEAO_DA_COSTA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GERONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/18782> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ADDUCTOR POLLICIS MUSCLE THICKNESS (APMT) HAS BEEN USED AS A MARKER OF MUSCLE MASS. IT IS INTERESTING TO INVESTIGATE ITS RELATIONSHIP WITH FUNCTIONAL CAPACITY IN ELDERLY, IT IS INFLUENCED BY THE PHYSIOLOGICAL CHANGES OF AGING. THE AIMED WAS TO ANALYZE THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN APMT AND FUNCTIONAL CAPACITY IN OLDER ADULTS OUTPATIENT. THIS IS A CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY, WITH A SAMPLE COMPOSED OF OLDER ADULTS AGED = 60 YEARS, OF BOTH SEXES, TREATED AT AN OUTPATIENT GERIATRIC CLINIC. DATA WERE COLLECTED"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "RELAÇÃO ENTRE ESPESSURA DO MÚSCULO ADUTOR DO POLEGAR E A CAPACIDADE FUNCIONAL EM IDOSOS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ELIDA_DE_ANDRADE_BARBOZA_SOUZA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GERONTOLOGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1879> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THIS DISSERTATION, WE CONSIDER AN IMPORTANT CLASS OF REGRESSION MODELS, NAMELY: THE CLASS OF GENERALIZED EXTREME VALUE NONLINEAR REGRESSION MODELS. THE LINEAR MODEL IS OBTAINED AS A PARTICULAR CASE. SUCH MODELS ARE COMMONLY USED IN MANY FIELDS TO MODEL EXTREMAL EVENTS. THE MAIN MODEL FOUNDATIONS INVOLVE EXTREME VALUE THEORY, WHICH PROVIDES UNDERLYING LAWS FOR SCENARIOS IN WHICH THE DATA MAY CONTAIN ATYPICAL OBSERVATIONS WHICH RESULTS FROM THE PHENOMENON OF INTEREST AND NOT THE RESULT OF MEASU"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DIAGNOSTIC ANALYSIS IN GENERALIZED EXTREME VALUE NONLINEAR REGRESSION MODELS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOSE_VALDENIR_DE_OLIVEIRA_JUNIOR> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1880> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN MANY PRACTICAL SITUATIONS THERE IS A NEED TO MODEL DATA IN THE INTERVAL (0,1), WHICH CAN BE INTERPRETED AS RATES OR PROPORTIONS. THESE DATA, IN GENERAL, PRESENT ASYMMETRY AND HETEROSCEDASTICITY, NOT SATISFYING THE ASSUMPTIONS OF THE CLASSICAL LINEAR REGRESSION MODEL. SEVERAL REGRESSION MODELS ARE BEING STUDIED FOR THIS PURPOSE. FOR EXAMPLE, THE BETA REGRESSION MODEL (FERRARI E CRIBARI-NETO, 2004), KUMARASWAMY REGRESSION MODEL (MITNIK E BAEK, 2013), JOHNSON SB REGRESSION MODEL (LEMONTE E BAZAN"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DIAGNÓSTICO EM MODELOS DE REGRESSÃO SIMPLEX"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUANA_CECILIA_MEIRELES_DA_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1881> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CAUCHY-RAYLEIGH (CR) DISTRIBUTION HAS BEEN SUCCESSFULLY USED TO DESCRIBE ASYMMETRICAL AND HEAVY-TAIL EVENTS FROM RADAR IMAGERY. EMPLOYING SUCH MODEL TO DESCRIBE LIFETIME DATA MAY THEN SEEM ATTRACTIVE, BUT DRAWBACKS ARISE: ITS PROBABILITY DENSITY FUNCTION DOES NOT COVER NON-MODAL BEHAVIOR AS WELL AS ITS HAZARD RATE FUNCTION (HRF) ASSUMES ONLY ONE FORM. TO OUTPERFORM THIS DI¿CULTY, IT IS INVESTIGATED THE EXPONENTIATED CAUCHY-RAYLEIGH (ECR) DISTRIBUTION. THIS BYPARAMETERIC MODEL IS ¿EXIBLE ENOU"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFERENCE, INFORMATION THEORY, AND SEGMENTATION BASED ON THE EXTENDED CAUCHY-RAYLEIGH MODEL: APPLICATIONS TO HEAVY-TAILED DATA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/THIAGO_VEDOVATTO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1882> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN AIDS CLINICAL TRIALS, THE HIV-1 RNA MEASUREMENTS ARE OFTEN SUBJECT TO SOME UPPER AND LOWER DETECTION LIMITS, DEPENDING ON THE QUANTIFICATION ASSAYS. LINEAR AND NONLINEAR MIXEDEFFECTS MODELS, WITH MODIFICATIONS TO ACCOMMODATE CENSORED OBSERVATIONS (LMEC/NLMEC), ARE ROUTINELY USED TO ANALYZE THIS TYPE OF DATA (VAIDA AND LIU, 2009). THIS WORK PRESENTS A LIKELIHOOD BASED APPROACH FOR FITTING LMEC/NLMEC WITH AUTOREGRESSIVE OF ORDER P (AR(P)) DEPENDENCE ON THE ERROR TERM. AN EM-TYPE ALGORITHM IS DE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "27FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFERÊNCIA BASEADA EM VEROSSIMILHANÇA PARA MODELOS AUTORREGRESSIVOS CENSURADOS DE EFEITOS MISTOS, COM APLICAÇÕES AO CONJUNTO DE DADOS DE CARGAS VIRAIS DO HIV"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ROMMY_CAMASCA_OLIVARI> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1883> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CLASS OF ELLIPTICAL MULTILEVEL MODELS HAS BEEN WIDELY USED IN DATA SETS, WHICH PRESENT SOME HIERARCHICAL STRUCTURE. THIS CLASS PROPOSES THE USE OF PROBABILITY DISTRIBUTIONS IN THE ELLIPTICAL CLASS, WHICH INVOLVES ALL SYMMETRIC CONTINUOUS DISTRIBUTIONS, INCLUDING THE NORMAL DISTRIBUTION AS A PARTICULAR CASE. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS DISSERTATION IS THE DEVELOPMENT OF DIAGNOSTIC TECHNIQUES, MORE SPECIFICALLY, THE ANALYSIS OF LOCAL INFLUENCE VIA NORMAL CURVATURE IN THE ELLIPTICAL MULTILEVEL M"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "31JUL2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFLUÊNCIA LOCAL EM MODELOS ELÍPTICOS MULTINÍVEIS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ERICA_VIEIRA_NOGUEIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1884> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "GEOSTATISTICAL IS BASED ON THE STUDY OF RANDOM VARIABLES INDEXED BY THEIR GEOGRAPHIC LOCATION. THE ANALYSIS OF INFLUENTIAL DIAGNOSTICS METHODS IS OFTEN USED TO IDENTIFY THE PRESENCE OF POTENTIALLY INFLUENTIAL OBSERVATIONS IN THE DATA AND/ R THE MODEL AND TO ASSESS THE DISTORTION THAT THESE OBSERVATIONS MAY CAUSE IN THE RESULTS OF THE STATISTICAL ANALYSIS. IN THIS CONTEXT, THE STUDY IS CONSIDERED IN GAUSSIAN SPATIAL LINEAR MODELS, WHICH TAKE INTO ACCOUNT THE SPATIAL VARIABILITY OF THE VARIABLES U"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "29JUL2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INFLUÊNCIA LOCAL EM MODELOS ESPACIAIS LINEARES GAUSSIANOS UTILIZANDO O MÉTODO DE MÁXIMA VEROSSIMILHANÇA RESTRITA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/EDUARDO_LUCAS_ENSSLIN_DOS_SANTOS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/1885> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN SPATIAL DATA ANALYSIS THE DATA ARE INDEXED BY A SET OF LOCATIONS IN SPACE, THE WAY THIS SET IS DEFINED SEPARATES SPATIAL STATISTICS INTO THREE AREAS: GEOSTATISTICAL DATA, AREAL DATA, AND POINT PATTERN DATA. IN THIS WORK WE WILL FOCUS ON THE MODELS FOR AREAL DATA, SPECIFICALLY IN THE SIMULTANEOUS AUTOREGRESSIVE (SAR) MODELS, WHICH HAS APPLICATIONS IN MANY FIELDS SUCH AS ECOLOGY, PUBLIC HEALTH, TEXTURE ANALYSIS AND SPATIAL ECONOMETRICS. IT IS PROPOSED TO IMPLEMENT THE SAR MODELS WITHIN THE GENE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25JUL2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
