<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19317> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DEFECTS IN COMPUTER SYSTEMS OR APPLICATIONS DIRECTLY IMPACT THE QUALITY AND PERFORMANCE OF A FINAL PRODUCT, GENERATING CONSEQUENCES FOR THE USER AND THE SUPPLIER. THEREFORE, IDENTIFYING THE ESCAPED DEFECT NOT DETECTED BY THE TESTER AT THE PROPER STAGE, THUS, INCORPORATING IT INTO THE PRODUCT, IS ONE OF THE SOFTWARE INDUSTRYS PRIMARY ACTIVITIES. TO MITIGATE OR ELIMINATE THE MISSING DEFECTS, COMPANIES USUALLY HAVE A SECTOR RESPONSIBLE FOR ANALYZING AND EVALUATING THE LOST BUGS TO UNDERSTAND THE C"@pt,
        "THE PRODUCTION OF BIOMASS ESTIMATES, DETERMINED BY REMOTE SENSING TECHNIQUES SUCH AS LIDAR, HAS PRESENTED LARGE POTENTIAL FOR MODELING BIOPHYSICAL AND BIOMETRIC PARAMETRIC IN PLANTED AND NATURAL FORESTS. IN THIS SCENARIO, THE PRESENT WORK AIMS TO ESTIMATE ABOVE GROUND BIOMASS (AGB), USING LIDAR DATA, IN A RAINFOREST REMNANT IN AREAS CONSIDERED MATURE VEGETATION, HAVING AS A FIELD OF STUDY THE DOIS IRMÃOS STATE PARK, A LOCATED IN THE URBAN AREA OF RECIFE, PERNAMBUCO STATE. IT WAS USED IN THE CALC"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "11AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "29AUG2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
