    capes:hasAbstract "REMOTE SENSORS HAVE EVOLVED ON A GROWING SCALE, WITH RESPECT TO SPATIAL, SPECTRAL AND TEMPORAL RESOLUTIONS. THE JOINT APPLICATION OF MULTISPECTRAL SYSTEMS/SENSORS OF THE LANDSAT 8 AND SENTINEL-2 SATELLITE PLATFORMS IS VERY IMPORTANT AND EFFECTIVE FOR APPLICATIONS OF ENVIRONMENTAL CHANGES. THUS, THE CROSS-COMPARISON BETWEEN THE TWO SATELLITES BECOMES INDISPENSABLE FOR THE COMPLEMENTARY USE OF THE IMAGES. THE RESEARCH PROPOSES TO ANALYZE THE SPECTRAL AND SPATIAL BEHAVIOR BETWEEN THE SENSORS: OLI/L"@pt,
