    capes:hasAbstract "HE WORKING PROCESS FOR DEALING WITH DATA STREAMS REQUIRES NEW DEMANDS AND CHALLENGING TASKS IN THE AREA OF DATA MINING AND MACHINE LEARNING. A STREAM CAN BE CATEGORIZED AS A SYSTEM THAT GENERATES HUGE AMOUNTS OF DATA. THUS, WHEN THE PROBABILITY DISTRIBUTION WITHIN THIS DATA STREAM VARIES, WE HAVE A PROBLEM COMMONLY KNOWN AS CONCEPT DRIFT. THE PROCESS OF IMPLEMENTATION OF NEW METHODS TO DEAL WITH DATA STREAMS CONTAINING CONCEPT DRIFTS REQUIRES ALGORITHMS THAT CAN ADAPT TO DIFFERENT SITUATIONS TO "@pt,
