    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOAO_ALEXANDRE_DA_SILVA_NETO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_DA_COMPUTAÇÃO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19342> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TIME SERIES ANALYSIS IS A FIELD THAT PRESENTS SEVERAL CHALLENGES, THE MOST COMMON OF WHICH IS THE TIME SERIES FORECASTING ACTIVITY. AMONG THE MOST COMMON MEANS OF IMPROVING FORECASTS, TWO STAND OUT: (I) THE CREATION OF NEW MATHEMATICAL MODELS; (II) THE USE OF HYBRID METHODOLOGIES. THIS WORK IS DEDICATED TO PRESENTING A NEW HYBRID METHODOLOGY FOR TIME SERIES FORECASTING BY APPLYING THE GENERALIZED ADDITIVE MODELS FOR LOCATION, SCALE AND SHAPE (GAMLSS) STATISTICAL MODEL FOR ITS DECOMPOSITION. AFTE"@pt ;
