<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19353> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "A PACKAGE REPOSITORY IS AN ESSENTIAL PIECE OF A SOFTWARE ECOSYSTEM WHERE PACKAGES AND INTERDEPENDENCIES ARE PUBLISHED TOGETHER WITH SECURITY UPDATES. IN FREE AND OPEN-SOURCE SOFTWARE, THE SOFTWARE REPOSITORIES ARE FREQUENTLY HOSTED AND MAINTAINED USING DONATIONS OR CONTRIBUTIONS IN THE FORM OF COMPUTATIONAL POWER OR FINANCIAL AID. THE TECHNICAL SOLUTION ADOPTED TO ABSORB THE COMPUTATIONAL POWER DONATION LIMITS ON ITS DESIGN, PROHIBITING SMALL DONORS FROM PARTICIPATING WITH THEIR CONTRIBUTIONS. T"@pt ;
