<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19354> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "REINFORCEMENT LEARNING (RL) IS AN EMERGENT SUBFIELD OF MACHINE LEARNING IN WHICH AN AGENT INTERACTS WITH AN ENVIRONMENT AND LEVERAGES THEIR EXPERIENCES TO LEARN, BY TRIAL AND ERROR, WHICH ACTIONS ARE THE MOST APPROPRIATE FOR EACH STATE. AT EACH STEP THE AGENT RECEIVES A POSITIVE OR NEGATIVE REWARD SIGNAL, WHICH IS THE MAIN FEEDBACK USED FOR LEARNING. RL FINDS APPLICATIONS IN MANY AREAS, SUCH AS ROBOTICS, STOCK EXCHANGE, AND EVEN IN COOLING SYSTEMS, PRESENTING SUPERHUMAN PERFORMANCE IN LEARNING T"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "07JUN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
