<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19367> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WOUND INFECTIONS ARE ONE OF THE MOST COMMON COMPLICATIONS THAT DELAY WOUND HEALING. THE MAIN BACTERIA THAT CAUSE THIS INFECTION ARE STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS AND PSEUDOMONAS AERUGINOSA, INCREASING THE MORBIDITY AND MORTALITY OF PATIENTS. THE MAIN CURRENT METHODS TO AID IN THE DIAGNOSIS OF WOUND INFECTIONS CAUSED BY THESE BACTERIA ARE THE CULTURE AND THE MOLECULAR METHOD, WHICH HAVE A LONG PERIOD FOR SPECIES IDENTIFICATION AND HIGH FINANCIAL COST, RESPECTIVELY. IN THIS SENSE, AN EXCELLENT TECHNOLOGIC"@pt ;
