<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19369> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PREMATURITY IS WHEN A CHILD IS BORN WITH LESS THAN 37 COMPLETED WEEKS OF GESTATION, BEING CONSIDERED A GLOBAL HEALTH PROBLEM, AND STILL ONE OF THE MAIN CONSEQUENCES OF DEATHS IN NEONATAL AND FIVE-YEAR-OLD CHILDREN. THE PREMATURE BIRTH RATE MAY VARY ACCORDING TO GEOGRAPHIC REGION AND INCOME LEVEL, MAINTAINING A HIGHER FREQUENCY IN UNDERDEVELOPED COUNTRIES. IN THE COUNTRIES INCLUDED, IT IS WIDELY CONSIDERED AS A WAY OF UNDERSTANDING THE CAUSES AND CREATING PREVENTIVE ACTIONS. IN THIS RESEARCH, THE"@pt ;
