<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19406> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DATA SCIENCE IS A FIELD THAT CONCERNS THE ANALYSIS, EXTRACTION OF KNOWLEDGE, AND VALUABLE INFORMATION HELPING THE DECISION-MAKING FROM STRUCTURED (TABLES, DATASETS, ETC) AND UNSTRUCTURED DATA (MUSIC, TEXT, ETC). SYMBOLIC DATA ANALYSIS (SDA) PROVIDES A FRAMEWORK THAT GIVES ANSWERS TO BIG AND COMPLEX DATA. IN SDA A SYMBOLIC DATASET IS BUILT FROM AN AGGREGATION, CONCATENATION, AND FUSION PROCESS, WHERE THE NEW INPUT UNITS ARE SUBSETS OF THE INDIVIDUAL ENTITIES (CLASSES) HAVING A COMMON PROPERTY. TH"@pt ;
