<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19408> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "REAL-WORLD APPLICATIONS HAVE BEEN DEALING WITH LARGE AMOUNTS OF DATA, WHICH COME CONTINUOUSLY AND SEQUENTIALLY OVER TIME, CHARACTERIZED AS DATA STREAMS. THIS TYPE OF DATA CHALLENGES MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHMS DUE TO CONCEPT DRIFT. CONCEPT DRIFT IS A CHANGE IN THE JOINT PROBABILITY DISTRIBUTION OF THE PROBLEM AND HAS TWO VARIATIONS: VIRTUAL DRIFT THAT AFFECTS THE UNCONDITIONAL PROBABILITY DISTRIBUTION ¿(¿); AND REAL DRIFT THAT AFFECTS THE CONDITIONAL PROBABILITY DISTRIBUTION ¿(¿|¿). THESE DRIFTS"@pt ;
