<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19410> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SOLVING RECURSIVE DOMAIN EQUATIONS OVER A CARTESIAN CLOSED 0-CATEGORY IS A WAY TO FIND EXTENSIONAL MODELS OF THE TYPE-FREE ¿¿-CALCULUS. IN THIS WORK WE SEEK TO GENERALIZE THESE EQUATIONS TO HOMOTOPY DOMAIN EQUATIONS; TO BE ABLE TO SET ABOUT A PARTICULAR CARTESIAN CLOSED (0,8)-CATEGORY, WHICH WE CALL THE KLEISLI 8-CATEGORY, AND THUS FIND HIGHER ¿¿-MODELS, WHICH WE CALL ¿¿-HOMOTOPIC MODELS. TO ACHIEVE THIS PURPOSE, WE HAD TO PREVIOUSLY GENERALIZE C.P.OS (COMPLETE PARTIAL ORDERS) TO C.H.P.O"@pt ;
