<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19421> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DEFECT PREDICTION IS A TASK THAT AIMS TO ALLOCATE RESOURCES AND INFORMATION TO PREDICT DEFECTPRONE SOFTWARE MODULES. HOWEVER, DUE TO THE NEED FOR SUFFICIENTLY LARGE AMOUNTS OF DATA REQUIRED BY THE MODELS, RESEARCHERS HAVE FOCUSED ON RESEARCH ON CROSS-PROJECT DEFECT PREDICTION (CPDP). THIS APPROACH INVOLVES BUILDING MODELS USING A TRAINING SET COMPOSED OF INFORMATION FROM MULTIPLE EXTERNAL PROJECTS. SEVERAL CPDP APPROACHES PROPOSED IN THE LITERATURE USE TRADITIONAL APPROACHES SUCH AS LOG NORMALIZ"@pt ;
