<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19422> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SIGN LANGUAGE IS AN ESSENTIAL RESOURCE TO ENSURE THE DEAF TO HAVE ACCESS TO COMMUNICATION, EDUCATION, AS WELL AS TO COGNITIVE AND SOCIO-EMOTIONAL DEVELOPMENT. IN FACT, IT IS THE MAIN FORCE THAT UNITES SUCH COMMUNITY AND THE KEY TRAIT THAT IDENTIFIES ITS MEMBERS. ON THE OTHER HAND, THE NUMBER OF HEARING INDIVIDUALS WHO ARE ABLE TO COMMUNICATE THROUGH THIS LANGUAGE IS CURRENTLY SMALL AND, IN PRACTICE, THIS IMPOSES OBSTACLES TO THE DAILY LIFE OF THE DEAF. SIMPLE TASKS LIKE USING PUBLIC TRANSPORTATI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "05JUL2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "UMA ABORDAGEM LINGUÍSTICA PARA O RECONHECIMENTO DE LÍNGUAS DE SINAIS"@pt ;
