<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19423> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THE LAST DECADE, THE VOLUME OF DATA GENERATED AND STORED BY COMPUTERS HAS INCREASED CONSIDERABLY. THIS DATA IS GENERATED BY VARIOUS SOURCES, INCLUDING AUTONOMOUS SYSTEMS. TO MEET THE DEMAND FOR MANAGING THIS DATA, CONVENTIONAL DATABASE TECHNOLOGIES HAVE LIMITATIONS DUE TO THE INFLEXIBILITY OF THEIR ARCHITECTURES. ADJACENT TO THIS NEED FOR DATA GROWTH, THE DEVELOPMENT OF DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS (DBMS) NOSQL (NOT ONLY SQL) IS POPULAR. NOSQL IS A DATABASE TECHNOLOGY DESIGNED FOR CLOUD APPLIC"@pt ;
