    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_DA_COMPUTAÇÃO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19424> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SOFTWARE ADAPTABILITY GIVES INFORMATION SYSTEMS THE ABILITY TO ADJUST THEIR BEHAVIOUR OR STRUCTURE THROUGH CHANGES IN THEIR EXECUTION ENVIRONMENT AND IN THEIR SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS. THIS ADAPTABILITY IS AN EFFECTIVE APPROACH TO DEAL WITH DYNAMIC AND CHANGING ENVIRONMENTS, SUCH AS THE ENVIRONMENT IN WHICH HEALTH INFORMATION SYSTEMS (HIS), THAT USE ARCHETYPE, ARE INSERTED. AN ARCHETYPE IS AN OPENEHR STANDARD AND CAN BE DEFINED AS A COMPUTATIONAL EXPRESSION REPRESENTED BY DOMAIN CONSTRAINTS, WHICH "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28JUL2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "UMA ARQUITETURA DE SOFTWARE ADAPTATIVA BASEADA EM ARQUÉTIPO OPENEHR PARA SISTEMAS DE INFORMAÇÃO EM SAÚDE"@pt ;
