<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19439> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CHILD DEVELOPMENT IS WITHIN HUMAN DEVELOPMENT, AND CAN BE DEFINED AS A PROCESS OF MATURATION, CONTINUITY, AND CHANGE, OVER TIME, IN WHICH DIFFERENT SKILLS ARE DEVELOPED, FOLLOWING A PROGRESSIVE SEQUENCE FROM THE BEGINNING OF LIFE. PRIMARY CARE HEALTH PROFESSIONALS ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR MONITORING CHILD DEVELOPMENT, INCORPORATING KNOWLEDGE TO SUPPORT FAMILIES AND CAREGIVERS IN THIS PROCESS. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO ANALYZE THE CONTRIBUTIONS OF A CONTINUING EDUCATION PROCESS WITH PRIMARY C"@pt ;
