<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19448> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "HEALTH LITERACY REPRESENTS THE KNOWLEDGE AND PERSONAL SKILLS THAT ACCUMULATE OVER GENERATIONS, THROUGH DAILY ACTIVITIES AND SOCIAL INTERACTIONS. INDIVIDUALS WITH A LOW LEVEL OF HEALTH LITERACY MAY HAVE DIFFICULTIES UNDERSTANDING THE HEALTH TEAM'S GUIDELINES, WHICH MAY RESULT IN NON-ADHERENCE TO MEDICATION AND THE ADOPTION OF RISKY BEHAVIOR, SUCH AS ADDING SELF-CARE MANAGEMENT. THE STUDY AIMED TO ANALYZE THE ASSOCIATION OF ADHERENCE TO ANTIRETROVIRAL THERAPY WITH THE HEALTH LITERACY OF ADULTS LIV"@pt ;
