<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19450> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE ACTIVE PARTICIPATION OF MAN IN THE PREGNANT-PUERPERAL CYCLE CONTRIBUTES TO THE SUCCESS OF BREASTFEEDING. THIS RESEARCH AIMS TO EVALUATE THE SUPPORT PRACTICES OF THE FATHER/PARTNER IN THE MAINTENANCE OF EXCLUSIVE BREASTFEEDING (EUS) FROM THE PERSPECTIVE OF THE WOMAN. A SINGLE-GROUP PROSPECTIVE AND OPEN-END EXPOSURE COHORT STUDY WHOSE OUTCOME WAS ESA. THE SAMPLE CONSISTED OF 195 PUERPERAS, INTERVIEWED FACE-TO-FACE IN THE JOINT ACCOMMODATION OF A HOSPITAL UNIVERSITY/EP. IN CONTINUITY, THE DATA "@pt ;
