<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19455> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CARE OF CHILDREN IN VULNERABLE SITUATIONS SUCH AS THOSE EXPERIENCED ON THE STREETS REQUIRES THE SUPPORT OF SOCIAL NETWORKS. THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC CHANGED RELATIONAL DYNAMICS AS WELL AS THE ACCESS TO SOCIAL ASSISTANCE SERVICES, INFLUENCING THIS CARE. FROM THE INTERACTION WITH THE ENVIRONMENT, THE SOCIAL REPRESENTATIONS OF THESE CHILDREN ABOUT CARE EMERGE, WHICH INFLUENCE INDIVIDUAL AND COLLECTIVE ATTITUDES THAT INTERFERE WITH THEIR WELL-BEING. THE ACTORS OF THE CHILD'S SOCIAL NETWORK CAN ACT "@pt ;
