<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19526> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DURING A RADIOTHERAPY TREATMENT PLANNING WITH A LINEAR ACCELERATOR, A DOSE OF RADIATION IS APPLIED TO A CERTAIN VOLUME OF TISSUE THAT ENCOMPASSES THE TUMOR TO ERADICATE ALL TUMOR CELLS, BUT AT THE SAME TIME, SPARING HEALTHY CELLS. WITH THIS OBJECTIVE, ALGORITHMS ARE USED TO CALCULATE ACCURATELY THE DOSE DISTRIBUTION AT THE MEDIUM. HOWEVER, THESE ALGORITHMS ARE LESS EFFECTIVE WHEN IT IS USED HETEROGENEOUS TISSUES. THE PURPOSE OF THIS WORK IS TO EVALUATE THE ACUROS XB ALGORITHM'S IN HETEROGENEOUS "@pt ;
