<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19527> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WEEDS ACCOUNT FOR UP TO 80% OF THE LOST PRODUCTIVITY OF SUGARCANE. THUS, THE USE OF HERBICIDES IS NECESSARY IN ORDER TO CONTROL THE INFESTATION OF THESE SPECIES AND TO MINIMIZE THEIR EFFECTS ON CROPS. ONE OF THE HERBICIDES COMMONLY USED IN SUGARCANE IS IMAZAPIC. STUDIES HAVE SHOWN THAT THIS MOLECULE CAN BE LEACHED INTO ENVIRONMENTAL COMPARTMENTS, MAKING IT A CONTAMINANT. THE APPLICATION OF BIO-BIO TO THE SOIL IS CAPABLE OF REDUCING THE LEACHING OF HERBICIDES. THEREFORE, THE PRESENT WORK HAD THE "@pt ;
