<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19544> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ESTIMATING BIOMASS POSES A CHALLENGE IN HARD-TO-REACH AREAS OR LARGE AREAS. THE NEED FOR STUDIES CAPABLE OF DESCRIBING THE NATURAL VARIABILITY AND IMPACTS CAUSED BY CHANGES IN LAND USE IS EVIDENT. HOWEVER, DETAILED BIOMASS ACCOUNTING WITHIN A HIGHLY VARIABLE REGION REQUIRES A LARGE AMOUNT OF DATA TO BE PROCESSED WITH AGILITY. THIS REQUIRES SYSTEMATIZING DATA ON RESPONSE VARIABLES AND ACCOUNTING FOR BALANCES OVER TIME AND GENERATING SPATIALLY EXPLICIT DATA ON LAND USE AND ITS CHANGES. THE AVAILAB"@pt ;
