<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19545> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE SPREAD OF ANTHROPOGENIC RADIOISOTOPES IN THE ENVIRONMENT COMES FROM NUCLEAR TESTS AND ACCIDENTS THAT OCCURRED IN THE PAST, WHICH JUSTIFIES CONSTANT MONITORING, TO GUARANTEE THE SAFETY AND CONTROL OF THE ACTIVITIES THAT INVOLVE THESE APPLICATIONS. BRAZIL, WHEN EXPORTING SOME FOOD PRODUCTS, DEPENDING ON THE COUNTRY OF ORIGIN, A RADIOMETRIC REPORT IS REQUIRED, ESPECIALLY FOR SUGAR THAT HAS HIGH WORLD CONSUMPTION AND THE POSSIBILITY OF CONTAMINATION OF THE POPULATION, WHEN RADIOISOTOPE IS PRESEN"@pt ;
