<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19555> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CONCENTRATORS USED IN THERMAL APPLICATIONS, SUCH AS CYLINDRICAL PARABOLIC, REACH TEMPERATURES UP TO 400°C AT EFFECTIVE CONCENTRATIONS OF 23 TO 26 SUNS. THIS WORK PRESENTS THE APLANATIC AS A DOUBLE REFLECTION THERMAL SOLAR CONCENTRATOR WITH CYLINDRICAL ABSORBER, WITH EFFECTIVE CONCENTRATION OF 66 SUNS FOR A TOTAL INTERCEPT FACTOR OF 0.72. BY ADOPTING THE TOTAL INTERCEPTION FACTOR OF 0.98, SIMILAR TO THE OBTAINED IN CYLINDRICAL PARABOLIC, WE OBTAIN AN EFFECTIVE CONCENTRATION OF 36 SUNS, WHICH REPR"@pt ;
