<http://example.com/capes#thesis/19556> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ATMOSPHERIC PARTICULATE IS THE SET OF SMALL PARTICLES SUSPENDED IN THE ATMOSPHERE, WITH A HIGH DEGREE OF PHYSICAL, CHEMICAL AND SOMETIMES RADIOMETRIC HETEROGENEITY. IT IS ONE OF THE MOST HARMFUL POLLUTANTS TO HEALTH, BEING A POTENTIAL CAUSE OF HEART DISEASES AND CANCER. HOWEVER, THE MONITORING OF ATMOSPHERIC PARTICLES IS POORLY STUDIED IN THE BRAZILIAN TERRITORY. IN THIS SENSE, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO ESTIMATE THE DISTRIBUTION OF THE CONCENTRATION OF TOTAL SUSPENDED PARTICLES - PTS - N"@pt ;
