    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOCIÊNCIAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21615> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "GROUNDWATER MANAGEMENT IS A COMPLEX TASK, GIVEN THE LARGE NUMBER OF VARIABLES INVOLVED IN ITS FORMULATION. IN BRAZIL, THE MANAGEMENT TOOLS USED BY MANAGERS ARE STILL TIMID. IN PERNAMBUCO, THE REGULATORY AGENCY USES THE SO-CALLED AQUIFER EXPLOITATION ZONES, WHEN AVAILABLE, TO ESTABLISH THE FLOWS GRANTED. THESE ZONES ARE BASICALLY ESTABLISHED BASED ON THE DEPTH OF THE STATIC LEVELS, WHICH IS A VERY LIMITED WAY TO ESTABLISH THE GRANT. AN EFFICIENT MANAGEMENT TOOL HAS TO CONSIDER THE COMPLEXITY OF T"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "16NOV2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "GESTÃO DAS ÁGUAS SUBTERRÂNEAS DA BACIA SEDIMENTAR DE SÃO JOSÉ DO BELMONTE - PE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ANA_GABRIELLA_DOS_SANTOS_BATISTA_DE_MENEZES> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOCIÊNCIAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21616> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MOST OF WHAT WE KNOW ABOUT OCEANIC PLATEAUS COMES FROM FRAGMENTS ACCRETED ONTO ACTIVE MARGINS. ALTHOUGH, NUMERIC MODELS SUGGEST THAT UNDER CERTAIN CIRCUMSTANCES THEY MAY SUBDUCT, REPORTS OF ECLOGITES OR BLUESCHISTS WHICH PROTOLITH WAS ORIGINATED FROM OCEANIC PLATEAUS ARE LACKING. HERE ARE PRESENTED GEOCHEMICAL, GEOCHRONOLOGICAL, AND METAMORPHIC CONSTRAINTS OF BLUESCHISTS AND ECLOGITES FROM A HIGH-PRESSURE (HP) OPHIOLITE THAT EVIDENCES THEIR OCEANIC PLATEAU ORIGIN DEBATING THE METAMORPHIC SIGNATU"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "05DEC2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "HISTÓRIA METAMÓRFICA DE UM PLATÔ OCEÂNICO: O EXEMPLO DO COMPLEXO RASPAS, EQUADOR"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/SALVIANO_PEREIRA_DA_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOCIÊNCIAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21617> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FOSSIL VERTEBRATES FROM ANTARCTICA ARE CONSIDERABLY RARE, PRESENTING A FRAGMENTED AND DISJOINTED ASPECT, WHICH MAKES IT DIFFICULT TO UNDERSTAND THE EVOLUTIONARY HISTORY OF THE FOSSIL BIOTA OF THAT CONTINENT. IN THIS SENSE, OSTEOHISTOLOGICAL ANALYZES CONSTITUTE AN IMPORTANT TOOL IN THE IDENTIFICATION OF THESE RECORDS, SINCE THE PRESERVATION OF THE BONE MICROSTRUCTURE KEEPS INFORMATION ABOUT THE LIFE HISTORY OF ORGANISMS. DESPITE THIS, FEW STUDIES HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT INVOLVING THE OSTEOHISTOLOGY"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "11FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "IDENTIFICAÇÃO TAXONÔMICA DE VERTEBRADOS CRETÁCICOS DA SUB-BACIA JAMES ROSS (PENÍNSULA ANTÁRTICA) POR MEIO DA ANÁLISE OSTEOHISTOLÓGICA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUCIA_HELENA_DE_SOUZA_ELEUTERIO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOCIÊNCIAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21618> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE WESTERN END OF TRANSVERSAL ZONE IN BORBOREMA PROVINCE ENCOMPASSES SUPPOSED ALLOCHTHONOUS TERRAIN LODGED IN THE PIANCÓ-ALTO BRÍGIDA BELT, INCLUDING THE ICAIÇARA TERRANE. IN THIS WORK REGIONAL AND LOCAL AEROGEOPHYSICAL DATA WERE INTEGRATED IN ORDER TO SUPPORT THE STRUCTURAL UNDESTANDING OF THIS SUPPOSED EXOTIC TERRAIN. THE GAMMA-SPECTROMETRIC MAPS ALLOW MAPPING OF SHALLOW STRUCTURES AND THE GENERAL DELINEATION OF THE GEOLOGICAL DOMAINS, WHILE THE MAGNETIC AND GRAVIMETRIC DATA ALLOW THE ESTIMUL"@pt ;
