<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21619> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE TAMBABA FORMATION IS EOCENE AGE AND OCCURS IN SURFACE RESTRICTED WAY IN THE NORTHERN COASTAL REGION OF THE PARAÍBA BASIN. PREVIOUSLY, THE CARBONACEOUS DEPOSITS CONSTITUENT OF THIS UNIT WERE FREQUENTLY CITED AS UPPER MARIA FARINHA FORMATION, ASSUMING A STRATIGRAPHIC FORMATION DISTINCT FROM THE MARIA FARINHA FORMATION (PALEOCENIC AGE). THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS THE CONSTRUCTION OF A PALEOENVIRONMENTAL MODEL OF REEF LIMESTONES OF THIS FORMATION THROUGH SEDIMENTOLOGICAL, STRATIGRAPHICAL AND"@pt ;
