<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21620> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PARNAMIRIM BATHOLITH GRANITIC (PP) REPRESENTS A TYPICAL CRUSTAL MELT IN PULSES, LOCATED IN THE CENTRAL SUB-PROVINCE OF BORBOREMA PROVINCE, NORTHEASTERN BRAZIL. THE PP (~210 KM²) CAN BE DIVIDED INTO THREE MAIN PULSES THAT INTRUDE THE SALGUEIRO COMPLEX, VERTICALLY (SHEETS), PRESENTING AN ELONGATED ENE-WSW SHAPE, APPROXIMATELY EN CORNU, CONDITIONED BY THE PERNAMBUCO SHEAR ZONES (TO THE SOUTH) AND PARNAMIRIM (TO THE WEST). ALONG THE BODY THERE ARE MAGMATIC FOLIATIONS THAT PROGRESS TO S-C FOLIATI"@pt ;
