<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21625> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE ALIANÇA FORMATION FROM THE BROTAS GROUP, JATOBÁ BASIN, REPRESENTS THE FIRST LACUSTRINE PULSE THAT OCCURRED DURING THE EARLY RIFT PHASE IN THE FIRST EFFORTS TO SEPARATE WESTERN GONDWANA, DURING THE NEO-JURASSIC. IN THIS CONTEXT, AN IMPORTANT VERTEBRATE FAUNA IS FOUND IN SEVERAL STRATA OF THIS UNIT, MAINLY IN THE REGION OF IBIMIRIM, STATE OF PERNAMBUCO. THE TWO MAIN OBJECTIVES OF THIS WORK INCLUDE: (1) TO DESCRIBE THE VERTEBRATE TAPHOFACIES AND (2) TO CARRY OUT A TAXONOMIC STUDY OF THE FIRST D"@pt ;
