<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21673> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE 1980 VIENNA CONVENTION EMBODIES AN INTERNATIONAL STANDARD OF UNIFORM LAW THAT ADDRESSES SUBSTANTIVE RULES ON INTERNATIONAL CONTRACTS FOR THE PURCHASE AND SALE OF GOODS, COMMONLY REFERRED TO BY ITS ACRONYM IN ENGLISH CISG. THE CURRENT WORK AIMS TO STUDY THE SCOPE OF THIS CONVENTION IN RELATION TO THE HARDSHIP CLAUSES PRESENT IN INTERNATIONAL CONTRACTS, ESPECIALLY IN THE FACE OF THE PANDEMIC SCENARIO DERIVED FROM COVID-19. THE CLAUSE IN QUESTION REFERS TO THE PRIOR DETERMINATION BY THE PARTI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20SEP2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
