<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21680> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENT WORK IS AIMED AT IDENTIFYING THE POSSESSION OF A SOCIO-AFFECTIVE AFFILIATION STATE IN THE RECOGNITION. IT IS KNOWN THAT CURRENTLY, CONSIDERING THE EXPRESSION OR OTHER ORIGIN PRESENT IN ARTICLE 1593 OF THE CIVIL CODE, IT HAS BEEN UNDERSTOOD BY THE POSSIBILITY OF SOCIO-AFFECTIVE AFFILIATION, WHICH WAS REINFORCED BY THE JURISPRUDENCE OF THE SUPERIOR COURT OF JUSTICE (STJ) AND BY THESIS 622 OF THE FEDERAL SUPREME COURT THAT DEALT WITH MULTIPARENTHOOD. IN TURN, DOCTRINAL STUDIES HAVE PO"@pt ;
