<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21690> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS WORK SEEKS TO CRITICALLY RESIZE AND EXPATIATE ON THE ROLE PLAYED BY EDUCATION IN HUMAN RIGHTS IN GUINEA-BISSAU AS AN EFFECTIVE AND CONFIRMING ELEMENT OF DEMOCRACY, AS WELL AS FOR SOCIAL CONTROL AND CITIZEN PARTICIPATION, BOTH AT LOCAL AND UNIVERSITY LEVELS. IT ADOPTS AN ANALYTICAL VERSION THAT SEES HUMAN RIGHTS AS PRINCIPLES OF AFFIRMATION OF THE CONDITION OF MAN IN RELATION TO HIS FELLOW MAN AND THE STATE, AIMED AT BUILDING A REAL VALUE OF THIS CONDITION INHERENT TO THE HUMAN BEING IN ANY "@pt ;
