<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21704> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE MAIN GOAL OF THIS DISSERTATION IS TO THINK CRITICALLY ABOUT THE CONCEPT OF PARITY OF PARTICIPATION IN NANCY FRASER, OBSERVING ITS POTENTIALS AND LIMITS, AS WELL AS ITS POSSIBLE ROLE FOR A REFLECTION ON BRAZILIAN LAW. TO DO SO, IT SOUGHT TO EXAMINE THE GENESIS OF THE CONCEPT, WITH ATTENTION TO THE MAIN DEBATES HELD BY THE PHILOSOPHER (MAINLY WITH JÜRGEN HABERMAS) IN THE 1990S UNTIL HER MOST RECENT WRITINGS. IT IS WORTH POINTING OUT THAT PARITY OF PARTICIPATION IS THE NORMATIVE CENTER THROUGH "@pt ;
