<http://example.com/capes#thesis/21935> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "GRAPHENE IS ONE OF THE ALLOTROPES OF CARBON AND WAS DISCOVERED IN 2004. WITH ITS DIFFERENT ELECTRONIC PROPERTIES COMPARED TO OTHER MATERIALS, THE SCIENTI C COMMUNITY TURNED ITS EYES TO GRAPHENE, WHERE SEVERAL STUDIES HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT UNTIL THE PRESENT DAY. IN THIS MATERIAL, THE QUASIPARTICLES (ELECTRONS AND HOLES) BEHAVE LIKE MASSLESS RELATIVISTIC FERMIONS. A SYSTEM THAT HAS ATTRACTED GREAT ATTENTION IS THE GRAPHENE SUPERLATTICE, AS IT IS POSSIBLE TO CONTROL THE ELECTRONIC PROPERTIES OF GRA"@pt ;
