<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22323> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE VARIABILITY OF RAINFALL AND HIGH EVAPOTRANSPIRATION, CHARACTERISTIC OF THE BRAZILIAN SEMI-ARID REGION, RESULT OVER TIME, IN PRODUCTION AND VARIABLE QUALITY OF FORAGE. FOR A FEW MONTHS, THE ABUNDANT PRODUCTION MAY EXCEED THE CAPACITY OF CONSUMPTION BY THE ANIMALS AND DECREASES WITH THE ADVANCE OF THE DROUGHT PERIOD. AT THAT TIME, EXOTIC FORAGES ADAPTED TO THE EDAPHOCLIMATIC CONDITIONS OF THE REGION HAVE BEEN CULTIVATED AND CONSERVED AS A STRATEGY TO REDUCE THE FOOD DEFICIT OF RUMINANTS. AMONG"@pt ;
