<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22686> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE IMPACTS CAUSED BY IMPROPERLY DISPOSING OF TIRES ON THE ENVIRONMENT GENERATE PROBLEMS NOT ONLY AT THE DISPOSAL SITE, BUT RATHER, IT BECOMES A WORLDWIDE PROBLEM DUE TO THE HIGH POTENTIAL FOR ENVIRONMENTAL RISKS AND RISKS TO HUMAN HEALTH. THEREFORE, ALTERNATIVES ARE SOUGHT FOR THE REUSE OF THIS MATERIAL, AND CIVIL CONSTRUCTION IS ONE OF THE AREAS WITH THE GREATEST POSSIBILITY OF INSERTING THESE ALTERNATIVE MATERIALS, WHICH AIM TO OPTIMIZE THE PROPERTIES OF THE USUAL MATERIALS, SUCH AS PLASTER. "@pt ;
