<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22696> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE HIGH POST-HARVEST LOSSES OF FRUIT AND VEGETABLES IN OUR COUNTRY AFFECT THE PROFITABILITY OF PRODUCERS AND TRADERS, AND DUE TO THE RAPID LOSS OF POST-HARVEST QUALITY, THERE IS A GREAT LIMITATION IN TERMS OF SERVING THE FRESH FRUIT MARKET. AMONG THE FRUITS WITH THE HIGHEST LOSS RATE IS ACEROLA, A FRUIT THAT HAS A HIGH PERCENTAGE OF VITAMIN C, BUT WHOSE POST-HARVEST LIFE IS REDUCED DUE TO ITS HIGH RESPIRATORY RATE. IN THIS SENSE, THE USE OF EDIBLE COATINGS HAS BEEN EXPLORED TO REDUCE POST-HARVE"@pt ;
