<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22704> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CASSAVA PRUNING IS A COMMON PRACTICE AMONG FARMERS WITH THE OBJECTIVE OF PROVIDING MATERIAL FOR NEW PLANTINGS, CONTROL OF DISEASE INFESTATION OR FORAGE FOR ANIMALS. THE WORK WAS DEVELOPED WITH THE OBJECTIVE OF EVALUATING THE DOSE OF GLYPHOSATE IN THE PRESENCE AND ABSENCE OF PRUNING APPLIED IN LATE POST-EMERGENCE, ON PRODUCTIVITY AND OTHER BIOMETRIC CHARACTERISTICS OF THE CROP. THE EXPERIMENT WAS CONDUCTED IN THE FARM OF VÁRZEA DO BARRO, MUNICIPALITY OF SÃO JOÃO - PE, BEING THE TREATMENTS DISTRIB"@pt ;
