<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22710> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BIOCHAR CAN BE A GREAT ALLY IN THE RECOVERY OF SOILS AFFECTED BY SALTS, BECAUSE IT REGULATES THE CHEMICAL AND PHYSICAL PROPERTIES, BESIDES PROVIDING RECALCITRANT ORGANIC MATTER. HOWEVER, HIGH DOSES OF BIOCHAR CAN BE HARMFUL TO THE SOIL, RELEASING LARGE AMOUNTS OF SALTS INTO THE SOIL, AND BIOCHARS ARE USUALLY ALKALINE, WHICH MAKES THEIR APPLICATION IN SALINE SOILS UNFEASIBLE, AND CHEMICAL MODIFICATION CAN BE AN ALTERNATIVE TO REDUCE THIS ALKALINITY. THE SALINITY OF THE SOIL OCCURS DUE TO LOW PREC"@pt ;
