<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22962> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MAIZE IS ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT CROPS AND OCCUPIES THE FIRST PLACE IN DEVELOPING ECONOMIES. IN THIS SCENARIO, PLANT STRESS IS AN EXTERNAL CONDITION THAT EXERTS PRESSURE ON THEIR BIOLOGICAL SYSTEM, RESULTING IN GROWTH AND YIELD REDUCTION. DROUGHT AND SALINITY ARE TWO IMPORTANT ABIOTIC STRESS FACTORS THAT NEGATIVELY AFFECT PLANT GROWTH AND YIELD IN THE MAIN CROPS WORLDWIDE. HOWEVER, PLANT GROWTH-PROMOTING BACTERIA (PGPB) CAN AFFECT PLANT METABOLISM THROUGH DIFFERENT PHYSIOLOGICAL, BIOCHEMICAL, "@pt ;
