<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22964> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PITHECELLOBIUM DIVERSIFOLIUM BENTH., IS AN ENDEMIC PLANT FROM CAATINGA, TRADITIONALLY USED TO TREAT DISEASES SUCH AS DIABETES, COUGHS, BRONCHITIS AND INFLAMMATIONS. THIS WORK AIMED TO CONDUCT A PHYTOCHEMICAL STUDY OF THE LEAVES AND STEM BARK OF P. DIVERSIFOLIUM AND TO ANALYZE ITS CYTOTOXICITY. THE CRUDE ETHANOLIC EXTRACTS WERE PARTITIONED TO OBTAIN THE HEXANIC, DICHLOROMETHANE, ETHYL ACETATE AND METHANOLIC FRACTIONS. PHYTOCHEMICAL PROFILING WAS PERFORMED, IN ADDITION TO ANTIOXIDANT ACTIVITY TEST"@pt ;
