<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22965> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CAATINGA IS CHARACTERIZED BY A SEMI-ARID CLIMATE WITH VEGETATION ADAPTED TO CONDITIONS OF HIGH TEMPERATURES AND IRREGULAR RAINFALL. IT IS AN ECOSYSTEM RICH IN BIODIVERSITY, WITH BIOPROSPECTIVE POTENTIAL FOR THE STUDY OF BIOACTIVE SUBSTANCES. CENOSTIGMA MICROPHYLLUM AND CENOSTIGMA PYRAMIDALE ARE ENDEMIC SPECIES OF THE CAATINGA, POPULARLY KNOWN AS CATINGUEIRA AND CATINGA-DE-PORCO, RESPECTIVELY. STUDIES IN LIPID CHEMISTRY HAVE BEEN DEDICATED TO THE EVALUATION OF VEGETABLE OILS EXTRACTED FRO"@pt ;
