<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22967> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COVID-19 IS AN INFECTIOUS RESPIRATORY DISEASE CAUSED BY SARS-COV-2, WHICH CAN RANGE FROM ASYMPTOMATIC PATIENTS TO FATAL. THE MORBIDITY AND MORTALITY OF THE DISEASE CAN BE ATTRIBUTED TO A DYSREGULATED IMMUNE RESPONSE. AN IMPORTANT COMPONENT OF THIS IMMUNE RESPONSE IS PENTRAXIN 3 (PTX3), WHICH IS INVOLVED IN RESISTANCE TO SELECTED PATHOGENS AND IN THE REGULATION OF COMPONENTS OF INNATE IMMUNITY. SINGLE NUCLEOTIDE POLYMORPHISMS (SNPS) IN THE PTX3 GENE HAVE BEEN ASSOCIATED WITH CHANGES IN PROTEIN LE"@pt ;
