<http://example.com/capes#thesis/22968> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN NATURE THERE ARE PRIMARY METABOLITES SUCH AS LECTINS AND SECONDARY METABOLITES SUCH AS SAPONINS, BOTH IN FAUNA AND FLORA. IN VEGETABLES, LECTINS AND SAPONINS ARE COMMONLY ISOLATED AND PURIFIED FROM SEEDS, BUT THEY CAN ALSO BE FOUND IN OTHER PARTS OF PLANTS, SUCH AS LEAVES AND ROOTS IN THE MOST DIVERSE BOTANICAL FAMILIES. THE ALBIZIA SPECIES FLOOD POPULARLY KNOWN AS CANAFÍSTULA, MUQUÉM AND BIGUAZEIRO, IT HAS POTENTIAL IN ITS BIOLOGICAL ACTIVITIES. IN THIS WAY, STUDIES WERE CARRIED OUT WI"@pt ;
