<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23054> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CYANOBACTERIA CAN DEVELOP IN ALMOST ALL ECOSYSTEMS AND DOMINATE THE ENVIRONMENT, FORM BLOOMS AND HAVE A NEGATIVE ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT, COMPROMISING WATER QUALITY AND PUTTING HUMAN AND ANIMAL POPULATIONS AT RISK. THIS IS ONLY POSSIBLE BECAUSE CYANOBACTERIA ARE PART OF A GROUP IN WHICH SOME SPECIES ARE POTENTIALLY TOXIN PRODUCERS (CYANOTOXINS). THE OBJECTIVE OF THE PRESENT RESEARCH WAS TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE KNOWLEDGE OF THE IMPACT ON THE GROWTH OF THE ITEP-A1 STRAIN OF R. RACIBORSKII IN THE PRESENC"@pt ;
