    capes:hasAbstract "CYANOBACTERIA ARE PHOTOSYNTHETIC PROKARYOTIC MICROORGANISMS AND HAVE CHLOROPHYLL-A. ALTHOUGH THEY OCCUR NATURALLY IN THE MOST DIVERSE TYPES OF ENVIRONMENTS, THE HIGH LOAD OF NUTRIENTS FROM HUMAN EUTROPHICATION HAS CONTRIBUTED TO THE FORMATION OF SO-CALLED BLOOMS, THAT IS, EXCESSIVE GROWTH OF CYANOBACTERIA IN SUPPLY RESERVOIRS. ATTENTION TO FLOWERING STEMS FROM THE FACT THAT MANY SPECIES ARE POTENTIALLY CYANOTOXIN PRODUCERS, WHICH PUTS EVERYONE WHO USES THE WATER AT RISK. THE MOST SERIOUS EPISODE"@pt ;
