<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23568> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ANTHROPOGENIC ACTIVITIES WITH POLLUTING POTENTIAL, INCLUDING MINING, FOUNDRY, FERTILIZER APPLICATION, PESTICIDES, WASTE DISPOSAL FROM ELECTRONIC INDUSTRIES, SEWAGE SLUDGE, WASTE WATER IRRIGATION, COAL COMBUSTION RESIDUES AND PETROCHEMICAL SPILLAGE, ARE A PROBLEM OF GREAT RELEVANCE, AS THEY LEAD TO SOIL CONTAMINATION BY TOXIC METALS IN MANY PARTS OF THE WORLD. THE ACCUMULATION OF THESE TOXIC METALS IS A CAUSE OF CONCERN IN AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTION, BECAUSE IT IS A GROUP OF CONTAMINANT METALS WITH "@pt ;
