<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23569> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CHEMICAL FERTILIZATION CAN HAVE NEGATIVE EFFECTS ON THE ENVIRONMENT AND THE FINANCIAL SUSTAINABILITY OF CROPS, WHICH IS WHY IT IS IMPORTANT TO SEEK ALTERNATIVE WAYS OF PROVIDING NUTRIENTS, WITH EMPHASIS ON BIOLOGICAL NITROGEN FIXATION (FBN). THUS, THIS WORK AIMS TO EVALUATE THE DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCTIVITY OF COWPEA (VIGNA UNGUICULATA (L.) WALP.) INOCULATED WITH ALPHA AND BETA-RHIZOBIA STRAINS NATIVE TO SEMIARID SOILS. THE STUDY WAS CARRIED OUT IN THE EXPERIMENTAL AREA AND LABORATORIES OF THE SE"@pt ;
