    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/PRODUÇÃO_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23573> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SOIL RESPIRATION IS A BIOLOGICAL METABOLIC PROCESS THAT RESULTS IN THE EMISSION OF CO 2 INTO THE ATMOSPHERE. QUANTIFYING RESPIRATION HELPS TO ASSESS SOIL HEALTH, ESPECIALLY OF FORAGE SPECIES FOR AGRICULTURAL PURPOSES. COMBINING DIFFERENT PLANT GROUPS AND STUDYING THEIR INFLUENCE ON SOIL RESPIRATION CAN HELP TO DEVELOP STRATEGIES FOR COEXISTENCE WITH THE SEMIARID REGION. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO EVALUATE THE INFLUENCE OF FORAGE CONSORTIA ON THE MAINTENANCE OF SOIL RESPIRATION IN A SEMI-A"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
