<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23736> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ION CHANNELS ARE INTEGRAL PROTEINS PRESENT IN CELL MEMBRANES RESPONSIBLE FOR IONIC FLUX BETWEEN INTRA AND EXTRACELLULAR ENVIRONMENT AND BETWEEN ORGANELLES AND THE CYTOPLASM. THEY ARE INVOLVED IN MANY PHYSIOLOGICAL PROCESSES, SUCH AS THE GENERATION OF NERVE IMPULSES, HORMONE SECRETION, HEARTBEAT, AMONG COUNTLESS OTHER PROCESSES. THE KINETICS OF ION CHANNELS IS CLASSICALLY TREATED AS A RANDOM PROCESS, KNOWN AS THE MARKOV PROCESS. MORE RECENTLY, HOWEVER, SEVERAL STUDIES HAVE SHOWN THAT THIS PROCESS"@pt ;
