<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23740> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "HYPERLIPIDEMIA IS CHARACTERIZED BY ABNORMAL CONCENTRATIONS OF LIPOPROTEINS IN PLASMA, THE MAIN CAUSE OF WHICH IS THE CONSUMPTION OF HIGH-FAT DIETS AND A SEDENTARY LIFESTYLE. ELEVATED PLASMA LIPOPROTEINS INCREASE THE RISK OF DEVELOPING CHRONIC KIDNEY DISEASE AND NONALCOHOLIC FATTY LIVER DISEASE, THUS BECOMING A PUBLIC HEALTH PROBLEM. LIPID PEROXIDATION LEADS TO THE FORMATION OF REACTIVE OXYGEN SPECIES, WHICH WHEN IN EXCESS CAN LEAD TO THE ACTIVATION OF GENES FOR THE PRODUCTION OF INFLAMMATORY MED"@pt ;
