<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23741> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE LEGALITY OF ALCOHOL, CULTURAL AND SOCIAL FACTORS HAVE INCREASINGLY NORMALIZED ALCOHOL 185 CONSUMPTION BY ADOLESCENTS. MALES ARE THE MAJORITY AMONG ACTIVE DRINKERS, ALMOST TWICE 186 AS MANY AS WOMEN WHO CONSUME ALCOHOL IN BRAZIL. ALCOHOLISM IS A MULTIFACTORIAL CHRONIC 187 DISEASE CHARACTERIZED BY THE CONTINUOUS CONSUMPTION OF ALCOHOL. THIS DISEASE HAS SEVERAL 188 EFFECTS ON PHYSICAL AND MENTAL HEALTH, ESPECIALLY DURING ADOLESCENCE, WHERE SEVERAL 189 PHYSIOLOGICAL PROCESSES OF MATURATION TAKE "@pt ;
