<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23743> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE IMMUNODIAGNOSIS APPLIED TO THE IDENTIFICATION OF CAPRINE ARTHRITIS ENCEPHALITIS (CAE) IS CONSIDERED THE BEST ALTERNATIVE FOR THE PREVENTION AND CONTROL OF INFECTIONS, ENABLING THE DETECTION OF INFECTED ANIMALS AT AN EARLY STAGE. THE PRODUCTION PROCESS OF THE ANTIGENS IS FUNDAMENTAL FOR THE PERFORMANCE OF THIS TEST, WHICH MAKES THE DEVELOPMENT OF RESEARCH CONTRIBUTING TO OBTAINING IT, EXTREMELY IMPORTANT. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH WAS TO PRODUCE VIRAL ANTIGEN THROUGH BOVINE FIBROBLASTIC "@pt ;
