    capes:hasAbstract "SLOTHS ARE MAMMALS BELONGING TO THE PILOSA ORDER, AND HAVE BEEN SUFFERING FROM DEVASTATING ANTHROPIC ACTIONS. THESE ANIMALS HAVE ARBOREAL HABITS AND A DIET BASED ON LEAVES AND SPROUT, WHICH MAY CONTAIN TOXIC CONTENT IN THEIR COMPOSITION, HIGHLIGHTING THE IMPORTANCE OF A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF THE ORGANIC SYSTEMS, EMPHASIZING THE HEPATIC ACTIVITY IN THESE ANIMALS. IN THIS CONTEXT, IT WAS PROPOSED TO CARRY OUT A MORPHOLOGICAL AND VENOUS DESCRIPTION OF THE LIVER, IN ORDER TO COLLABORATE WITH THE L"@pt ;
