<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23772> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "EPIDEMIOLOGICAL STUDIES OF EMERGING AND REEMERGING DISEASES MUST CONSIDER THE COMPONENTS OF THE EPIDEMIOLOGICAL TRIAD IN AN INTEGRATED MANNER AND CONSIDER THE HEALTH EMERGENCY AS A SHARED PROBLEM OF ONE HEALTH. IN THIS CONTEXT, THE INFECTIOUS AGENTS TOXOPLASMA GONDII AND SPOROTHRIX SPP. ARE INSERTED, WHERE HUMANS AND SUSCEPTIBLE ANIMALS CAN BECOME INFECTED THROUGH CONTACT WITH A CONTAMINATED ENVIRONMENT AND/OR INFECTED ANIMALS. THEREFORE, THE OBJECTIVE WAS TO EVALUATE THE CONTAMINATION BY OOCYST"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "29JUL2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
