<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23781> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CONTAMINATION OF SURFACE WATER BY PESTICIDES IS COMMONLY ASSOCIATED WITH A COMBINATION OF SUBSTANCES RATHER THAN A SINGLE COMPOUND, AS MULTIPLE ACTIVE INGREDIENTS ARE COMMONLY APPLIED SIMULTANEOUSLY TO CROPS AND/OR A VARIETY OF CROPS UTILIZE THE SAME WATER SOURCES. BUT THE CURRENT EVALUATION OF THE EFFECTS OF THESE PESTICIDES IS PREDOMINANTLY BASED ON THE ISOLATED SUBSTANCES, SO THE ECOLOGICAL RELEVANCE MAY BE UNDERESTIMATED. THEREFORE, THIS STUDY AIMED TO INVESTIGATE THE EFFECTS OF THE COMBINED"@pt ;
