<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23875> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"PHENOLOGY IS THE STUDY OF EVENTS THAT INVOLVE THE LIFE CYCLE OF SPECIES, WITH INDICATORS OF IMPORTANT ENVIRONMENTAL VARIATIONS DUE TO THE HIGH SENSITIVITY OF VEGETATION. THE ENVIRONMENTAL TRIGGERS THAT REGULATE THE SEPARATION OF PLANT COMMUNITIES ARE THEREFORE CRUCIAL. IN THE CONTEXT OF CLIMATE CHANGE, AND THE NEAR-SURFACE IMAGE WITH SIGNIFICANT PHENOMENA REPRESENTS A GAIN IN INCREASING THIS UNDERSTANDING. THIS STUDY IS PART OF A SYSTEMATIC REVIEW (CHAPTER 1) THAT DEALS WITH THE EVOLUTION OF PH"@pt ;
