    capes:hasAbstract "\"SPINA ET AL. (2015) CONDUCTED A STUDY ON THE POTENTIAL FOR LACCASE DEGRADATION OF TRAMETES PUBESCENS AGAINST SEVERAL COMPOUNDS CHARACTERIZED AS ENDOCRINE DISRUPTORS. THESE SUBSTANCES ARE CAPABLE OF ALTERING HORMONAL HOMEOSTASIS CAUSING SERIOUS DAMAGE TO HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ECOSYSTEM, SO THE DEVELOPMENT OF METHODS THAT QUICKLY, ECONOMICALLY AND WITH GOOD ACCURACY THE ABILITY OF LACCASE TO DEGRADE THESE COMPOUNDS IS OF GREAT IMPORTANCE. THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO BUILD A MODEL THAT PREDICTS WH"@pt ;
