<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23877> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"THE DEVELOPMENT OF DRUG RESISTANCE BY PATHOGENS IS A WORRYING REALITY; THIS PROBLEM ALSO OCCURS WITH CANDIDA SPECIES THAT CAUSE INFECTIONS AND FORM BIOFILMS, INCREASING THE NUMBER OF COMPLICATIONS AND EVEN DEATHS OF MORE SUSCEPTIBLE PATIENTS. THE SEARCH FOR ALTERNATIVE TREATMENTS HAS BEEN WIDELY ENCOURAGED, AND VEGETABLES ARE CONSTANTLY CITED IN THE LITERATURE AS SOURCES OF NATURAL PRODUCTS THAT CAN BE USED ALONE OR TOGETHER WITH THE ANTIFUNGALS ALREADY USED. CROTON BLANCHETIANUS IS POPULARLY K"@pt ;
