<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23878> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"EUPHORBIACEAE IS THE SECOND MOST DIVERSE FAMILY IN NUMBER OF SPECIES IN THE CAATINGA DOMAIN, AND IT IS MENTIONED IN MOST OF FLORISTIC-PHYTOSOCIOLOGICAL SURVEYS. THE FAMILY IS PRESENT IN ALL PHYTOGEOGRAPHIC DOMAINS IN BRAZIL, WITH REPRESENTATIVES IN THE MOST DIFFERENT VEGETATION TYPES. DESPITE BEING ONE OF THE FAMILIES WITH THE HIGHEST VOLUME OF STUDIES IN BRAZIL, THERE ARE STILL GAPS IN TAXONOMIC KNOWLEDGE, ESPECIALLY DUE TO THE LACK OF LOCAL RESEARCH AND THE LOW NUMBER OF COLLECTIONS IN CERTAI"@pt ;
