<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23879> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WHILE CLIMATE CHANGE HAS ALREADY PROFOUNDLY INFLUENCED BIODIVERSITY THROUGH SHIFTS OF SHIFTS AND SHIFTS OF SHIFTS, CHANGES OF EVOLUTION ITS EFFECTS ON FUTURE HISTORY ARE STILL OR ENHANCED. DIVERSITY CAN PHYLETIC AS A BRIDGE TO THE DIVERSITY OF FUNCTIONAL STRATEGIES THAT CAN HELP SUSTAIN THE ECOLOGICAL SYSTEMS THAT SERVED AS A GLOBAL REFERENCE. THIS EVOLUTIONARY HISTORY MAY BE ESPECIALLY VULNERABLE TO THE DECLINE OF PLANT COMMUNITIES IN WARM, WATER-LIMITED REGIONS SUCH AS THE CAATINGA, INTENSIFYI"@pt ;
