<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23881> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MYRCIA S.L. PRESENTS ABOUT 800 SPECIES, BEING ONE OF THE MOST NUMEROUS EXCLUSIVELY NEOTROPICAL GENERA. IT CONSISTS OF A MONOPHYLETIC GROUP, WITH THE RECENT INCLUSION OF CALYPTRANTHES, GOMIDESIA AND MARLIEREA IN ITS CIRCUMSCRIPTION, AND IS DIVIDED INTO NINE SECTIONS. IN BRAZIL, IT IS FOUND IN ALL PHYTOGEOGRAPHIC DOMAINS, HAS APPROXIMATELY 397 SPECIES, 77% OF WHICH ARE ENDEMIC. IT IS CHARACTERIZED MAINLY BY FOLIACEOUS COTYLEDONS, SEEDS WITH MEMBRANOUS TEGUMENT, BI- OR TRILOCULAR OVARY, WITH TWO OV"@pt ;
