<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23882> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"UNDERSTANDING THE RELATIONSHIPS BETWEEN TRADITIONAL POPULATIONS AND FAUNA ELEMENTS IS ONE OF THE ATTRIBUTES OF ETHNOCONSERVATION AND CONTRIBUTES TO STRATEGIES FOR THE MANAGEMENT AND MAINTENANCE OF NATURAL RESOURCES IN THE TERRITORIES. REPTILES CONSTITUTE A GROUP NOT SO ESTEEMED BY HUMAN SOCIETY IN GENERAL, DESPITE BEING ONE OF THE MOST DIVERSE GROUPS OF VERTEBRATES IN BRAZIL, AN IMPORTANT ELEMENT IN THE MAINTENANCE OF ECOSYSTEMS. SO, IS THERE A DIFFERENCE REGARDING THE WEALTH OF THESE ANIMALS"@pt ;
