<http://example.com/capes#thesis/23883> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"THE ADVANCEMENT OF INDUSTRIAL ACTIVITIES INCREASINGLY RESULTS IN ENVIRONMENTAL CONTAMINATION CAUSED BY THE DISPOSAL OF INDUSTRIAL WASTE TOXIC TO HUMAN HEALTH AND THE ENVIRONMENT. SEEKING TO CARRY OUT THE BIOREMEDIATION OF THE IMPACTS CAUSED, ENZYMES SUCH AS LACCASES ARE USED BY EFFICIENCY IN THE DEGRADATION OF VARIOUS SUBSTRATES. THE MAIN OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH WAS TO PURIFY A TAILINGS LACCASE FROM THE SHRIMP LITOPENAEUS VANNAMEI, AS WELL AS TO CHARACTERIZE IT IN TERMS OF ITS PROPERTIES AND"@pt ;
