<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24035> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE HAZARD ANALYSIS AND CRITICAL CONTROL POINTS (HACCP) SYSTEM IS A PREVENTIVE APPROACH TO RISK MANAGEMENT, DESIGNED TO INCREASE LEVELS OF FOOD SAFETY ASSURANCE BY ADAPTING TO ALL STAGES OF THE FOOD CHAIN. HENCE, THE OBJECTIVE OF THE PRESENT STUDY WAS TO APPLY THE HACCP SYSTEM IN SEVEN DAIRY HERDS LOCATED IN THE MUNICIPALITIES OF BOM CONSELHO AND IATI, MICROREGION OF GARANHUNS, PE - BRAZIL. THE STUDY WAS CARRIED OUT IN THREE STAGES, WHERE IN THE FIRST (DIAGNOSTIC STAGE), DATA RELATED TO THE PROD"@pt ;
