<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24036> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DIETS CONSISTING OF 100% GRAINS ARE BECOMING MORE AND MORE COMMON IN CONFINEMENT SYSTEMS FOR BEEF CATTLE IN BRAZIL. TO SUPPLY NATIONAL AND WORLDWIDE DEMANDS FOR BEEF, CATTLE BREEDERS ARE INVESTING IN WAYS TO CUT SHORT THE TIME FOR FINISHING PHASE. HOWEVER THIS DIET REQUIRES A PREVIOUS ADAPTATION FROM THE ANIMALS, FOLLOWED BY EFFECTIVE METODOLOGIES IN PREVENTING AND REDUCING RUMINAL AND METABOLIC DISORDERS CAUSED BY INGESTA FERMENTATION AND ACCUMULATION OF VFAS. TRYING TO UNDERSTAND THE MODIFICAT"@pt ;
