<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24037> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE PROBIOTIC POTENTIAL OF LACTIC ACID BACTERIA FROM THE BOVINE AND GOAT MILK MICROBIOTA IN THE MICROREGION OF GARANHUNS-PE. FROM 42 SAMPLES, 20 CAME FROM RAW COWS MILK AND 22 FROM RAW GOATS MILK. AFTER ISOLATION AND INITIAL IDENTIFICATION, THE LAB WERE SUBMITTED TO PHENOTYPIC TESTS, ANTIMICROBIAL SUSCEPTIBILITY AND ANTAGONISM TESTS USING THE PATHOGENIC BACTERIA STRAINS OF LISTERIA MONOCYTOGENES, STAPHYLOCOCCUS AUREUS, ESCHERICHIA COLI AND SALMONELLA"@pt ;
