<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24041> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CONTAMINATION OF MEAT BY PATHOGENIC BACTERIA IS A RISK TO PUBLIC HEALTH AND CAN OCCUR IN SEVERAL STAGES OF PRODUCTION, STARTING WITH THE SHIPMENT OF FARM ANIMALS, WHICH CAN INCREASE THE STRESS LEVEL AND MODIFY THE MICROBIOTA, UNTIL THE MOMENT OF SLAUGHTER, DURING EACH STEP TO THE FINAL PRODUCT. AMONG THE MAIN PATHOGENS THAT CONTAMINATE MEAT, BACTERIA BELONGING TO THE GENUS SALMONELLA STAND OUT DUE TO THEIR FREQUENCY IN OUTBREAKS OF FOODBORNE DISEASES. TAKING INTO ACCOUNT THE ECONOMIC AND PUBLIC "@pt ;
