<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24212> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ART AND SCIENCE ARE FIELDS OF KNOWLEDGE AND HUMAN PRODUCTION THAT GO HAND IN HAND OVER TIME, ALTHOUGH THEY ARE SEEN MORE FOR THEIR DIFFERENCES THAN FOR THE POSSIBILITIES OF INTERACTIONS. THUS, THE INTERDISCIPLINARY RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN ART AND BIOLOGY WAS ESTABLISHED AS AN OBJECT OF STUDY  CONFIGURING THE TERM BIOART, AS A FACTOR THAT PROMOTES BIOLOGICAL AND ARTISTIC KNOWLEDGE. IN THIS CONTEXT, THE OBJECTIVE WAS TO ANALYZE THE CONTRIBUTIONS OF BIOARTE TO THE TEACHING AND LEARNING PROCESS OF SCI"@pt ;
