<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24747> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MANGO (MANGIFERA INDICA L.) IS A FRUIT TREE OF GREAT IMPORTANCE IN THE WORLD, KNOWN AS THE QUEEN OF FRUITS FOR ITS EXCELLENT ORGANOLEPTIC CHARACTERISTICS, IT PRESENTS GREAT PHENOTYPIC DIVERSITY IN RELATION TO FRUIT QUALITY. THE OBJECTIVE OF THE PRESENT STUDY WAS TO CHARACTERIZE MANGO GENOTYPES IN TERMS OF FRUIT QUALITY, ESTIMATE GENETIC PARAMETERS AND SELECT PROMISING GENOTYPES FOR CULTIVATION IN SEMI-ARID CONDITIONS. IN CHAPTER II, TWO HUNDRED AND NINETY-TWO PLANTS WERE EVALUATED IN TWO CONSECU"@pt ;
