<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24748> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SYAGRUS CORONATA (MART.) BECC., POPULARLY KNOWN AS OURICURI AND LICURI, IS A MEMBER OF ARECACEAE AND HAS GREAT SOCIOECONOMIC AND ECOLOGICAL IMPORTANCE. DESPITE BEING A SPECIES WIDELY DISTRIBUTED IN THE CAATINGA AND ATLANTIC FOREST, THE URBAN EXPANSION AND INTENSIFICATION OF AGRICULTURAL PRACTICES HAVE CONTRIBUTED TO THE ACCENTUATED POPULATION DECLINE, REQUIRING MEASURES THAT CAN HELP THE CONSERVATION OF ITS GENETIC RESOURCES. GENOMIC STUDIES INVOLVING THE CHARACTERIZATION OF THE REPETITIVE FRACT"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "30JUN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
