<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24752> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COTTON IS ONE OF THE MAIN GLOBALLY COMMODITIES, AND BRAZIL IS THE FOURTH-LARGEST PRODUCER IN THE WORLD. THE PRODUCTIVITY OF BRAZILIAN CULTIVARS HAS INCREASED CONSIDERABLY; HOWEVER, THERE IS CONCERN ABOUT THE NARROWING OF THE GENETIC BASE, WHICH CAN REDUCE GENETIC GAINS IN THE SELECTION AND EXPOSE THE CROP TO VULNERABILITY TO PESTS AND DISEASES. THE GENETIC IMPROVEMENT OF COTTON IN BRAZIL BEGAN IN 1924, AT THE INSTITUTO AGRONÔMICO DE CAMPINAS (IAC). SUBSEQUENTLY, WERE CREATED OTHER GENETIC IMPROV"@pt ;
