<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24753> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TOMATO (SOLANUM LYCOPERSICUM L.) IS ONE OF THE MOST ECONOMICALLY IMPORTANT VEGETABLES IN THE WORLD. RALSTONIA PSEUDOSOLANACEARUM (RP) IS A PHYTOPATHOGENIC BACTERIUM THAT INFECTS THE XYLEM OF PLANTS, CAUSING THE DEVASTATING DISEASE KNOWN AS BACTERIAL WILT (MB), WHICH ATTACKS MORE THAN 200 PLANT SPECIES WORLDWIDE. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO CLARIFY THE MECHANISMS OF RESISTANCE AND SUSCEPTIBILITY, AT THE PROTEOMIC LEVEL, OF TWO CULTIVARS RESISTANT TO RP: HAWAII 7996 AND YOSHIMATSU AND A SUSC"@pt ;
