<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24798> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BACTERIA OF THE GENUS BORRELIA ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR SEVERAL DISEASES, INCLUDING RECURRENT FEVER, WHICH IS AN INFECTIOUS DISEASE THAT AFFECTS MAMMALS AND HUMANS, AND IS TRANSMITTED BY ARGASID TICKS OF THE GENUS ORNITHODOROS. THIS DISEASE IS CHARACTERIZED BY INTERVALS OF PYREXIA, WHICH CAN OFTEN BE CONFUSED WITH FEBRILE ILLNESSES SUCH AS DENGUE AND MALARIA. THE PRESENT STUDY AIMED TO RESEARCH BORRELIA SPP. IN BLOOD SAMPLES OF WILD MAMMALS AND DOMESTIC ANIMALS PRESENT IN CATIMBAU NATIONAL PARK, PE. "@pt ;
