<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24800> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE DEMAND FOR SHEEP MEAT IS INCREASINGLY IN DEMAND IN THE NORTHEAST, WHETHER FOR CULTURAL, ECONOMIC OR NUTRITIONAL REASONS. HOWEVER, THIS MEAT IS CONSIDERED A POTENTIAL SOURCE OF FOODBORNE ILLNESS CAUSED BY PATHOGENIC BACTERIA SUCH AS SALMONELLA AND ESCHERICHIA COLI, WHICH ARE COMMONLY FOUND IN FOOD-BORNE INFECTIONS IN HUMANS, POSING A PUBLIC HEALTH CHALLENGE. GOOD PRACTICES MUST BE IMPLEMENTED AT ALL STAGES OF THE PRODUCTION CHAIN AND IN ITS COMMERCIALIZATION, IN ORDER TO OBTAIN FOOD WITH SATI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "11FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
