    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_VETERINÁRIAS_NO_SEMIÁRIDO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24801> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE INDISCRIMINATE USE OF ANTIMICROBIALS IN BOTH HUMAN AND ANIMAL AREAS HAS ACCELERATED THE SELECTION OF RESISTANT BACTERIA, WHICH IS COMPLEX AND MULTIFACTORIAL AND REPRESENTS A GLOBAL PUBLIC HEALTH PROBLEM. IN THE VETERINARY MEDICAL ROUTINE, BACTERIAL DERMATOLOGICAL INFECTIONS ARE THE MOST COMMON, WHICH, DUE TO THE PROLONGED USE OF ANTIMICROBIALS, BECOMES AN AGGRAVATING FACTOR AND REINFORCES THE NEED TO SEARCH FOR NEW ANTIMICROBIAL DRUGS AGAINST MULTIDRUG-RESISTANT ISOLATES. IN THIS CONTEXT, US"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20JUN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "USNATO DE POTÁSSIO: NOVA ALTERNATIVA NO TRATAMENTO DE FERIDAS CIRÚRGICAS E POTENCIAL TERAPÊUTICO NA OTITE CANINA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JUSCIENE_BAGAGI_MOURA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_VETERINÁRIAS_NO_SEMIÁRIDO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24802> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRODUCTION OF TILAPIA HAS BEEN GAINING MORE AND MORE SPACE ON THE WORLD STAGE, HOWEVER, THIS GROWTH IS DIRECTLY RELATED TO HIGH PRODUCTIVITY, WHICH, IF NOT ASSOCIATED WITH ADEQUATE MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES, POSES RISKS TO ANIMAL HEALTH. IN THIS CONTEXT, BACTERIA SUCH AS AEROMONAS SPP. GAIN SPACE, CAUSING GREAT DAMAGE NOT ONLY TO ANIMAL HEALTH, BUT ALSO TO HUMAN HEALTH, GENERATING GREAT DISTURBANCES IN THE PRODUCTIVE SECTOR. IN THIS SENSE, SEQUENCING TECHNOLOGIES CAN BECOME GREAT ALLIES, SUPPORT"@pt ;
