    capes:hasAbstract "PERCEPTION HAS BEEN A KEY FACTOR FOR HUMAN SURVIVAL; UNDERSTANDING HOW THE HUMAN BEING PERCEIVES THE ENVIRONMENT AND CONSEQUENTLY THEIR ACTIONS AS A REFLECTION OF THIS VIEW, MAY PROVIDE A PERCEPTIVE, BEHAVIORAL, ENVIRONMENTAL AND SOCIAL ANALYSIS, ESPECIALLY DURING THE DEVASTATING NEW CORONAVIRUS PANDEMIC, PROBABLY CAUSED BY HUMAN INFLUENCE ON THE ENVIRONMENT, WITH DRASTIC CONSEQUENCES FOR HUMANITY. THIS WORK PRESENTS A QUALITATIVE AND QUANTITATIVE RESEARCH OF SOCIAL INDIVIDUALS IN THEIR VARIOUS "@pt,
        "THE DISTANCE EDUCATION MODEL POTENTIALLY OFFERS SEVERAL BENEFITS TO THE EDUCATIONAL ENVIRONMENT, SUCH AS DEMOCRATIZING EDUCATION. HOWEVER, SEVERAL CHALLENGES ARISE IN PROVIDING DISTANCE LEARNING STUDENTS AN EDUCATIONAL EXPERIENCE EQUIVALENT TO FACE-TO-FACE LEARNING. THUS, SEVERAL TOOLS AND THEORETICAL FRAMEWORKS HAVE BEEN DEVELOPED. ONE OF THEM IS THE COI MODEL. IN THIS DISSERTATION, A COMPUTATIONAL APPROACH WAS DEVELOPED TO ANALYZE ONLINE STUDENT DISCUSSIONS HELD IN EDUCATIONAL FORUMS. TECHNIQU"@pt ;
