<http://example.com/capes#thesis/24893> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN TODAY'S WORLD, WHERE TECHNOLOGY REDUCES DISTANCES, AVIATION IS SEEN AS A STRATEGIC ELEMENT FOR CONNECTING DIFFERENT PLACES. THE SIGNIFICANT INCREASE IN AIRPLANES AND AIRPORTS INFLUENCES THE DEVELOPMENT OF REGIONS IN SEVERAL ASPECTS. WHEN REFLECTING ON THE IMPACT OF AIR ACTIVITY, OVERLAPPING THE ENVIRONMENT AND QUALITY OF LIFE, THE STUDY HIGHLIGHTED THE NEED FOR AIRPORT MANAGEMENT WITH SOCIO-ENVIRONMENTAL RESPONSIBILITY, THUS RELATING RISK FACTORS, PREVENTIVE MEASURES, A SET OF LAWS AND NORMS "@pt ;
