    capes:hasAbstract "TEMPOROMANDIBULAR JOINT DISORDERS (TMDS) ENCOMPASS A GROUP OF HETEROGENEOUS CONDITIONS THAT CAN INVOLVE PAIN AND DYSFUNCTION AND CONTRIBUTE TO POOR QUALITY OF LIFE. IN ADVANCED JOINT DEGENERATION, ANKYLOSIS, OR TUMORS, JOINT RECONSTRUCTION IS USUALLY REQUIRED USING ALLOPLASTIC MATERIALS OR GRAFTS. THESE PROCEDURES HAVE DISADVANTAGES SUCH AS ALLERGY TO IMPLANTS, NEED FOR REVISION SURGERY, INFECTION AND MORBIDITY IN THE DONOR AREA. RECENTLY, AN EFFORT HAS BEEN MADE TO DEVELOP TISSUE ENGINEERING ST"@pt ;
