<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25160> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PESTS CAUSE THE LOSS OF PRODUCTION OF THE MAIN CROPS IN THE WORLD. PEST BIOLOGICAL CONTROL BY NATURAL ENEMIES IN CROPS CAN MITIGATE THESE DAMAGES. SEVERAL FACTORS MAY INFLUENCE BIOLOGICAL CONTROL, SUCH AS THE IDENTITY AND DIVERSITY OF PREDATORS. HOWEVER, CLIMATE AND CROP STABILITY ARE NEGLECTED. HERE, WE AIM TO UNDERSTAND THE EFFECT SIZE OF BIOLOGICAL CONTROL ON PEST SUPPRESSION AND PRODUCTIVITY. WE ALSO AIM TO UNDERSTAND IF CLIMATE AND CROP STABILITY AFFECT THE EFFECT SIZE. IN THIS WAY, WE DID "@pt ;
