<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25553> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COHERENTLY PREPARED ATOMIC SYSTEMS CAN GIVE RISE TO INTERESTING AND UNEXPECTED PHENOMENA SUCH AS, FOR EXAMPLE, ELECTROMAGNETICALLY INDUCED TRANSPARENCY (EIT). IN SUCH PHENOMENON, AN ABSORBING MEDIUM CAN BE RENDERED TRANSPARENT UPON COHERENT INTERACTION WITH OPTICAL LASER FIELDS. THIS EFFECT CAN BE INTERPRETED AS THE CREATION OF A COHERENT ATOMIC GROUND LEVELS SUPERPOSITION WHICH IS NOT COUPLED TO THE EXCITED STATE BY THE INCIDENT FIELDS. IN A RECENT PUBLICATION, IT WAS INVESTIGATED THE EIT PHENO"@pt ;
