    capes:hasAbstract "THE WORLD FACES GREAT TRANSFORMATIONS IN A SPEED THAT MAY CAUSE ASTONISHMENT, BUT ABOVE ALL, IT MUST BE AN APPEAL TO THE MISSION AND A TASK FOR THEOLOGY AS IT WAS ALWAYS PLACED IN CHALLENGING HISTORICAL CONTEXTS. IN ORDER TO RESPOND TO THE CHALLENGES OF THE MISSION IN THE 1970S, THE THEOLOGY OF INTEGRAL MISSION (IMT) EMERGED. IN THAT HISTORICAL MOMENT OF CONTEXTUAL THEOLOGIES, IT WAS NECESSARY TO TURN TO THE LATIN AMERICAN REALITY AND WITHIN A VISION OF THE HUMAN BEING IN ITS ENTIRETY, IN ORDER "@pt ;
