    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/SHAYRA_ANNY_MOURA_BARBOSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/REABILITAÇÃO_E_DESEMPENHO_FUNCIONAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25982> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: SEDENTARY WORK IS A POTENTIAL HEALTH RISK FACTOR AND MAY AGGRAVATE PAINFUL COMPLAINTS, WHILE PHYSICAL ACTIVITY MAY BE A PREVENTIVE FACTOR FOR THE ONSET AND WORSENING OF MUSCULOSKELETAL DISORDERS. HOWEVER, EVIDENCE ON HOW SEDENTARY BEHAVIOR AND THE PERFORMANCE OF LEISURE-TIME PHYSICAL ACTIVITY MAY INFLUENCE THE REPORT OF TEMPOROMANDIBULAR DYSFUNCTION (TMD) SYMPTOMS IS SCARCE. OBJECTIVE: TO EVALUATE THE ASSOCIATION BETWEEN THE LEVEL OF LEISURETIME PHYSICAL ACTIVITY AND TEMPOROMANDIBU"@pt ;
