<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25987> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BACKGROUND: STROKE IS ONE OF THE MAIN CAUSES OF DISABILITY IN THE WORLD. ABOUT HALF OF STROKES ARE ASSOCIATED WITH AN INCREASE IN BLOOD PRESSURE (BP). PHYSICAL ACTIVITY HAS A FAVORABLE EFFECT ON BP REDUCTION, A FACT THAT REDUCES THE RISK OF STROKE SINCE A 10MMHG REDUCTION IN MEAN BP IS ASSOCIATED WITH A 33% LOWER RISK OF STROKE. OBJECTIVES: A) TO VERIFY THE ACUTE EFFECTS OF EXPLOSIVE RESISTANCE EXERCISE (ERTE) WITH ELASTIC BANDS ON THE BP OF ELDERLY STROKE SURVIVORS; B) TO COMPARE THE PHYSICAL F"@pt ;
