<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25988> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: RESISTANCE TRAINING PERFORMED ON UNSTABLE BASES (TRBI) HAS BEEN A STRATEGY WIDELY ADOPTED IN THE TRAINING AND REHABILITATION OF ATHLETES. IN THE CONTEXT OF AGING, THE ELDERLY TEND TO AVOID DAILY SITUATIONS WITH SOME DEGREE OF INSTABILITY. HOWEVER, TRBI HAS EMERGED AS A PROMISING AND BENEFICIAL ALTERNATIVE FOR THE ELDERLY, AIMING TO COUNTERACT CHANGES INHERENT TO THE AGING PROCESS, ESPECIALLY WITH REGARD TO MOTOR, FUNCTIONAL AND COGNITIVE PERFORMANCE VARIABLES. OBJECTIVE: TO EXAMINE"@pt ;
