<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25989> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: COMMONLY TEMPORARY NEUROPHRAGMATIC RESISTANCES OF RESTRICTION TO THE INTENSIVE CARE UNIT (ICU) AND CHANGES IN MAJOR DAILY FUNCTION DUE TO INVASIVE MECHANICAL VENTILATION (IMV). THE SUM OF FACTORS CAN CULMINATE IN SHORTENING OF THE RIB CAGE, ATROPHY OF THE EXERCISES, MAKING THE PROCESS OF REMOVAL OF THE V DIFFICULT. REINFORCED, OPTIMIZING THE RECOVERY CAPACITY. SO FAR NOT STUDIED PATIENTS DO NOT CONTROL THE EFFECTS OF NEUROCRITICS. OBJECTIVE TO EVALUATE THE IMMEDIATE EFFECTS OF TLMD"@pt ;
