<http://example.com/capes#thesis/25990> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SHOULDER PAIN IS ONE OF THE MOST COMMON CAUSES OF MUSCULOSKELETAL COMPLAINTS FOUND IN PRIMARY CARE, SECOND ONLY TO BACK PAIN. OF ALL CONDITIONS INVOLVING THIS JOINT, SUBACROMIAL PAIN SYNDROME ACCOUNTS FOR 44 TO 65% OF CASES. EVIDENCE RECOMMENDS THERAPEUTIC EXERCISES ASSOCIATED WITH MANUAL THERAPY, AS THEY PRESENT BETTER RESULTS IN SHORT-TERM PAIN REDUCTION. IN ADDITION TO THESE TREATMENTS, PAIN EDUCATION HAS BEEN GAINING RECOGNITION, DUE TO ITS APPROACH TO CONSIDERING PAIN AS A TRULY BIOPSYCHOSO"@pt ;
