<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2620> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE INCOMPARABLE EFFIGY OF FRANCISCO SUÁREZ (1548-1617) IS UNMISTAKABLY CELEBRATED IN THE HISTORY OF THE PHILOSOPHY OF HIS TIME. INDEED, HIS POSITION ON THE STAUNCH QUESTION OF THE DISTINCTION BETWEEN ESSENCE AND EXISTENCE IN CREATURES, WHICH IS THE FUNDAMENTAL THEME OF THIS WORK, IS ESPECIALLY STRIKING, AND IS PERHAPS ONE OF HIS MOST ACCLAIMED REFLECTIONS. HOWEVER, ALTHOUGH HIS FINAL POSITION ON THIS ISSUE IS RELATIVELY WELL KNOWN, THE RELATIONSHIP WITH THE PHILOSOPHICAL ENVIRONMENT SURROUNDING"@pt ;
