<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2642> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DENTAL ERUPTION IS THE PROCESS WHICH THE TOOTH MOVES FROM THE DENTAL CRYPT (SITE OF FORMATION) TO THE EMERGENCE IN THE ORAL CAVITY WHERE PERFORM ITS FUNCTION. HOWEVER IT IS USUALLY USED AS A SYNONYM FOR IRRUPTION, INDICATING THE MOMENT WHEN THE DENTAL CROWN CROSSES THE GUMAND INTEGRATING THE ORAL ENVIRONMENT. DENTAL ERUPTION IS AN INTEGRAL PART OF THE CHILD'S DEVELOPMENT, AND SHOULD BE CONSIDERED IN ITS FOLLOW-UP, INCLUDING IN INTRODUCTION OF COMPLEMENTARY FEEDING. THIS STUDY AIMS TO DETERMINE T"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "13JUN2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "A CRONOLOGIA E SEQUÊNCIA DA ERUPÇÃO DENTÁRIA EM UM GRUPO DE CRIANÇAS DAS CRECHES MUNICIPAIS DE RECIFE"@pt ;
