    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/SAÚDE_DA_CRIANÇA_E_DO_ADOLESCENTE> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2644> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MOST OF THE CHILDREN WITH CEREBRAL PALSY (CP) PRESENT ALTERATIONS IN ORAL FUNCTIONS, WHICH MAKES FEEDING DIFFICULT AND CAN HAVE SERIOUS CONSEQUENCES FOR THEIR HEALTH SUCH AS MALNUTRITION AND PNEUMONIA. THE CAREGIVER IS ESSENTIAL IN THE FEEDING PROCESS OF THESE CHILDREN, SO THAT IT NEEDS TO KNOW AND PRACTICE THE RECOMMENDATIONS FOR SAFE FEEDING. IN ORDER TO AVOID COMPLICATIONS AND REDUCE STRESS OF THE CAREGIVER AND THE CHILD, ORIENTATIONS OF ALIMENTARY PRACTICES ARE ESSENTIAL AND NEED TO BE SATIS"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "23FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ALIMENTAÇÃO DE CRIANÇAS COM PARALISIA CEREBRAL: DO SABER AO FAZER"@pt ;
