<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2649> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: THE INFLAMMATORY PROCESS IN INFLAMMATORY BOWEL DISEASES (IBD) IS A RESULT OF A DISORDER IN THE MODULATION OF THE INTESTINAL IMMUNE SYSTEM INVOLVING DIFFERENT FACTORS INCLUDING GENETIC POLYMORPHISMS, ENVIRONMENT AND INTESTINAL MICROBIOTA. GIVEN THE PHENOTYPIC DIVERSITY OF DISEASE AND THE PATHOGENIC MECHANISMS INVOLVED, IT IS CHALLENGING TO INTERPRET THE CLINICAL FINDINGS AND THE COMPLEMENTARY TESTS. OBJECTIVES: TO DESCRIBE THE CLINICAL ASPECTS OF CHILDREN AND ADOLESCENTS DIAGNOSED W"@pt ;
