<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2659> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CHILDREN WITH CEREBRAL PALSY (CP) SUFFER DAMAGE TO THE DEVELOPING CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM, WHICH CAUSES CHANGES IN MOVEMENT AND POSTURE. THESE IMPAIRMENTS CAUSE REPERCUSSIONS ON THE ACQUISITION OF SKILLS THAT IS ESSENTIAL FOR THE PERFORMANCE OF FUNCTIONAL ACTIVITIES. FUNCTIONALITY IS A COMPLEX CONDITION RESULTING FROM THE COMBINATION OF PERSONAL AND CONTEXTUAL ASPECTS, AND MAY BE RELATED TO NUTRITIONAL STATUS. FOR THIS REASON, UNDERSTANDING HOW THE FUNCTIONALITY IS RELATED TO NUTRITIONAL STATUS I"@pt ;
