<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2666> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE USE OF PLANT GROWTH PROMOTING BACTERIA (PGPR) IN GRASSES HAS THE POTENTIAL TO OPTIMIZE THE USE OF NITROGEN FERTILIZERS AND SOLUBILIZE PHOSPHATE. THE CONSOLIDATION OF PGPR USE IN MAIZE PRODUCTION SYSTEMS, HOWEVER, DEPENDS ON NATIVE STRAINS ADAPTED TO THE GROWING REGIONS. THUS, THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE EFFECT OF INOCULATION OF REGIONAL / LOCAL STRAINS ON MAIZE GROWTH PROMOTION. A FIELD TRIAL WAS CONDUCTED ON MAIZE-GROWN VERTISOL IN PASSIRA-PE, BRAZIL. THE EXPERIMENTAL DESIGN W"@pt ;
