<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2673> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "POROSITY CAN BE CONSIDERED AS THE VOLUMETRIC FRACTION OF THE SOIL FILLED BY AIR OR WATER, OR BY A FRACTION OF BOTH, REPRESENTING THE PLACE WHERE THE SOIL SOLUTION (WATER AND NUTRIENTS) AND AIR CIRCULATE; THEREFORE, IT IS THE SPACE WHERE DYNAMIC PROCESSES INVOLVING THE THREE PHASES OF THE SOIL OCCUR. DESPITE THE IMPORTANCE OF SOIL POROSITY, ITS DISTRIBUTION BY PORE SIZE IS MORE ILLUMINATING IN THE STUDY OF PROCESSES SUCH AS THE DYNAMICS OF AIR, WATER AND NUTRIENTS, AS IT PROVIDES INFORMATION ON T"@pt ;
