<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2677> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DESERTIFICATION IS A PROBLEM OF CONTINENTAL DIMENSIONS THAT OCCURS IN REGIONS WITH ARID, SEMI-ARID AND DRY SUB-HUMID CLIMATES AND IS CHARACTERIZED BY THE DEGRADATION OF NATURAL RESOURCES. APPROXIMATELY 57% OF NORTHEAST BRAZIL HAS A SEMI-ARID CLIMATE AND IS EXPERIENCING INTENSE CHANGES IN LAND USE THAT HAVE RESULTED IN SEVERE SOIL DEGRADATION DUE TO WATER EROSION. ONE OF THE MAIN STRATEGIES ADOPTED TO STUDY THIS PROBLEM AT THE LOCAL LEVEL WAS THE ESTABLISHMENT OF DESERTIFICATION CENTERS. SIX NUCL"@pt ;
