<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27339> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BIORIENTED POLY(ETHYLENE TEREPHTHALATE) (PET) FILMS ARE COMMONLY SUBJECTED TO METALLIZATION PROCESSES TO OPTIMIZE SOME OF THEIR PROPERTIES, SUCH AS BARRIER TO MOISTURE AND GASES. WHEN EMPLOYED IN A PACKAGE, THE METALLIZED LAYER CAN DELAMINATE BECAUSE OF POOR ADHESION OF THE METAL TO THE POLYMER SURFACE. AS A PROPOSAL TO IMPROVE THE ADHESION OF THIS INTERFACE, HYBRID METALLIZATION ARISES, A VACUUM COATING PROCESS, CHARACTERIZED IN THIS STUDY BY THE CONTROLLED INJECTION OF O2 GAS INTO THE DEPOSITI"@pt ;
