<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27552> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ABASTRACTVOLUMETRIC QUANTIFICATION IS AN IMPORTANT PARAMETER TO BE EVALUATED IN FAST GROWING FORESTS. AND THE MODELING IS A TOOL THAT ALLOWS CHARACTERIZING THE FOREST STRUCTURE AND REPRESENTS GROWTH OVER TIME. THE PRESENT WORK DEALS WITH THE CHARACTERISTICS OF THE GENERALIZED ADDITIVE MODELS FOR LOCATION, SCALE AND SHAPE (GAMLSS), EXPOSING THE ESTIMATION TECHNIQUES THAT INSERT THE ITERATIVE ALGORITHMS, THE INFERENCE AND PREDICTION TECHNIQUES, THE DISTRIBUTIONS, THE ADDITIVE TERMS, THE MODEL SELE"@pt ;
