<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27553> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CLASSIFICATION TECHNIQUES ARE OFTEN USED TO SOLVE DIFFERENT BIOINFORMATICS PROBLEMS. MOST GENES IN THE DNA SEQUENCE ARE TRANSCRIBED BY MESSENGER RNA AND TRANSLATED INTO PROTEIN. THE DNA CONTAINS REGIONS THAT ENCODE PROTEINS (EXONS) AND REGIONS THAT DO NOT ENCODE PROTEINS (INTRONS), THE BOUNDARIES BETWEEN EXONS AND INTRONS ARE CALLED THE SPLICE SITE. DURING THE TRANSCRIPTION PROCESS, THE INTRONS ARE \"CUT\", THIS IS KNOWN AS SPLICING THAT PUTS THE EXONS OF A GENE CONSECUTIVELY, READY TO BE TRANSLAT"@pt ;
