<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27554> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "NATURAL FIRES ARE RARE IN DAMP FORESTS AND ARE CAUSED, FOR THE MOST PART, BY HUMAN PRACTICES, SUCH AS THE CLEANING OF FOREST AREAS FOR AGRICULTURE AND LIVESTOCK. HOWEVER, SOME FACTORS MAY INCREASE ITS CHANCE OF OCCURRENCE BY FAVORING ITS PROPAGATION. STUDIES OF THE TIME SERIES OF HOT PIXELS (AS A PROXY FOR VEGETATION FIRES) CAN BE USED TO PROVIDE ADDITIONAL INFORMATION ON THE TEMPORAL DYNAMICS OF FOREST FIRES AND THE FACTORS THAT INFLUENCE THEM. IN THIS WORK WE STUDIED THE BEHAVIOR OF THE SERIES"@pt ;
