<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27808> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SYSTEMIC LUPUS ERYTHEMATOSUS IS AN AUTOIMMUNE DISEASE WITH PERIODS OF EXACERBATION AND REMISSION THAT CAN AFFECT MULTIPLE ORGANS OR SYSTEMS, LEADING TO A WIDE SPECTRUM OF CLINICAL MANIFESTATIONS. BACTERIAL AND VIRAL INFECTIONS ARE COMMON OPPORTUNITIES IN SLE AND REPRESENT THE CAUSE OF DEATH IN THIS GROUP IN DEVELOPED COUNTRIES, RANGING FROM 25% OF MORTALITY CASES TO 50% TO 50% OF MORTALITY CASES. EVIDENCES FACTOR THAT COVID-19 HAS A SENSIBLE EFFECT IN CAUSING DAMAGE TO ORGANS AND OTHER CIRCUMSTA"@pt ;
