<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27810> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SEVERE ACUTE RESPIRATORY SYNDROME CORONAVIRUS-2 (SARS-COV-2) IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE CORONAVIRUS DISEASE PANDEMIC-2019 (COVID-19), WHICH LED TO THE REPORTING OF MORE THAN 200 MILLION CASES WORLDWIDE. SINCE THEN, GENOMIC SURVEILLANCE HAS BEEN A KEY TOOL TO TRACK VIRAL SPREAD. IN THIS STUDY WE PROVIDE A DETAILED ANALYSIS OF THE TEMPORAL DYNAMICS OF SARS-COV-2 MUTATIONS AND STRAINS DURING THE FIRST WAVE OF THE PANDEMIC IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO, BRAZIL. TO THIS END, WE PERFORMED THE CHARACTERIZATIO"@pt ;
