<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27816> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TRANSCRIPTION FACTORS (FTS) ARE PROTEINS THAT REGULATE GENE EXPRESSION BY BINDING TO SPECIFIC DNA SEQUENCES IN PROMOTER REGIONS OF TARGET GENES. SUCH PROTEINS ASSIST IN THE TRANSCRIPTION PROCESS THROUGH THEIR INTERACTION WITH RNA POLYMERASE, AN ENZYME RESPONSIBLE FOR THE SYNTHESIS OF MESSENGER RNAS. IN THIS WAY, THE FTS POSITION THE RNA POLYMERASE AND ACTIVATE IT TO INITIATE ITS POLYMERIZING ACTION. AMONG THE MAIN FT FAMILIES, WE HAVE THE GENES OF THE NAC FAMILY (NAM, ATAF1 / 2, CUC2) AND TIFY C"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "24FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
