<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27819> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SPHEROID IS A THREE-DIMENSIONAL BIOLOGICAL MODEL THAT HAS SHOWN POTENTIAL FOR THE STUDY OF INTERACTION WITH NANOPARTICLES (NPS) BY MIMICKING THE TUMOR ENVIRONMENT. QUANTUM DOTS (QDS) ARE SEMICONDUCTOR NANOCRYSTALS THAT HAVE A PHOTOSTABLE FLUORESCENT EMISSION AND AN ACTIVE SURFACE FOR CONJUGATION WITH MOLECULES OF BIOLOGICAL INTEREST. THESE ADVANTAGES HAVE BECOME QDS AS VERSATILE NANOPROBES FOR CANCER CELL BIOLOGY STUDY. THE WARBURG EFFECT REPORTS THAT CANCER CELLS CAN PRESENT A GREATER GLUCOSE U"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INTERAÇÃO DE ESFEROIDES E MONOCAMADAS DE CÉLULAS DE CÂNCER COM CONJUGADOS DE PONTOS QUÂNTICOS E GLICOSE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/RAFAELLA_BEZERRA_DE_LIMA_HENRIQUE> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27820> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC TWO YEARS AGO HAS CAUSED A LOT OF GLOBAL UPHEAVAL IN TERMS OF PUBLIC HEALTH, ECONOMICS, AND POLITICS. THE NUMBER OF CASES AND DEATHS HAS INCREASED IN OSCILLATIONS CALLED WAVES AND EVEN AFTER THE VACCINATION PROCESS HAS STARTED, THERE IS STILL NO MEDICINE AIMED AT FIGHTING THE VIRUS. THIS STUDY AIMS TO PROVIDE MORE KNOWLEDGE ABOUT THE PATHOGENESIS OF COVID-19, IN LABORATORY AND CLINICAL ASPECTS, CONFRONTING THE EVOLUTION OF THE DISEASE IN WARD AND ICU PATIENTS. BIOLOGICAL SA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "INVESTIGAÇÃO HEMATOLÓGICA, BIOQUÍMICA, MICROBIOLÓGICA E CLÍNICA DE PACIENTES COM COVID-19 INTERNADOS NA ENFERMARIA E UTI DE UM HOSPITAL UNIVERSITÁRIO EM PERNAMBUCO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/GEORON_FERREIRA_DE_SOUSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27821> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO ENCAPSULATE CEFTAZIDIME AND TOBRAMYCIN SEPARATELY AND IN CO-ENCAPSULATION IN ZEIN NANOPARTICLES WITH AND WITHOUT CHITOSAN COATING, TO CHARACTERIZE AND EVALUATE THE ANTIBACTERIAL AND ANTIBIOFILM ACTIVITY. THE NANOPARTICLES WERE PREPARED BY THE NANOPRECIPITATION METHOD AND COATED WITH CHITOSAN BY ELECTROSTATIC INTERACTION. THEN, THEY WERE CHARACTERIZED AND ANALYZED DURING STORAGE BY PARTICLE SIZE (Ø), POLYDISPERSITY INDEX (PDI), ZETA POTENTIAL (¿), PH AND ENCAPSULATION"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "30MAR2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "NANOPARTÍCULAS DE ZEÍNA REVESTIDAS COM QUITOSANA CONTENDO CEFTAZIDIMA E TOBRAMICINA COMO ESTRATÉGIA TERAPÊUTICA PARA INFECÇÕES BACTERIANAS RESISTENTES"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUIS_ANDRE_DE_ALMEIDA_CAMPOS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27822> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "QUANTUM DOTS (QDS) ARE FLUORESCENT SEMICONDUCTOR NANOCRYSTALS WITH UNIQUE OPTICAL PROPERTIES. GADOLINIUM [GD(III)] CHELATES HAVE BEEN USED AS CONTRAST AGENTS (CAS) IN THE TECHNIQUE OF NUCLEAR MAGNETIC RESONANCE IMAGING (MRI). COMBINING QDS WITH GD(III) CHELATES, IT IS POSSIBLE TO JOIN THE SPECIFICITY AND SENSITIVITY OF FLUORESCENCE-BASED METHODS AND PROVIDE A MORE EFFECTIVE PARAMAGNETIC SIGNAL FOR MRI. THUS, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS DISSERTATION WAS TO DEVELOP A MULTIMODAL NANOPLATFORM FORMED BY CA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "27JAN2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "NANOPLATAFORMAS ÓPTICO-MAGNÉTICAS MULTIMODAIS PARA INTERAÇÃO COM RECEPTORES DE TRANSFERRINA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/RENNAN_RIBEIRO_MANO_DE_LIMA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27823> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE WORLDWIDE DEMAND FOR PROTEIN SOURCES IS RISING DUE TO ITS NUTRITIONAL USE, BESIDES ITS BROAD BIOTECHNOLOGICAL, MEDICAL AND PHARMACEUTICAL APPLICATION. AMONG THE APPLICATIONS OF PROTEINS IS THE PRODUCTION OF BIOACTIVE PEPTIDES WITH ANTI-INFLAMMATORY, ANTIOXIDANT, AND ANTICANCER ACTIVITIES AND ACTING IN THE INHIBITION OF ANGIOTENSIN-CONVERTING ENZYME, HELPING TO CONTROL HYPERTENSION, ONE OF THE MAIN CAUSES OF DEATH IN THE WORLD. HOWEVER, THE USE OF PROTEIN SOURCES EXCLUSIVELY OF ANIMAL ORIGIN "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "OBTENÇÃO DE PEPTÍDEOS INIBIDORES DE ENZIMA CONVERSORA DE ANGIOTENSINA PROVENIENTES DE MICROALGAS CULTIVADAS EM MEIO SUPLEMENTADO COM MILHOCINA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
