    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27824> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PLAGUE IS A FLEA TRANSMITTED ZOONOSIS OF WILD RODENTS, WHICH CAN ATTAIN OTHER MAMMALS, INCLUDING HUMANS. DUE TO THE SEVERITY OF THE DISEASE AND ITS RAPID EVOLUTION, THE PLAGUE CAN GENERATE PUBLIC HEALTH EMERGENCIES OF INTERNATIONAL INTEREST. TECHNOLOGICAL AND SCIENTIFIC ADVANCES STILL DO NOT ALLOW TO ELIMINATE THE INFECTION FROM NATURAL FOCI THAT PERSIST IN MANY COUNTRIES ALTERNATING PERIODS OF ACTIVITY AND QUIESCENCE. IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO, THE ZOONOSIS INTRODUCED IN 1902 HAS BEEN SILENT S"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
