    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_BIOLÓGICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27829> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE GROWING INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT AND RAPID URBANIZATION IN REGIONS CLOSE TO WATER RESOURCES HAVE CONTRIBUTED ALARMINGLY TO THE INTRODUCTION OF CHEMICAL COMPOUNDS HARMFUL TO ENVIRONMENTAL AND SPECIES HEALTH. IN RECENT DECADES, AQUATIC ECOSYSTEMS HAVE BEEN SIGNIFICANTLY ALTERED DUE TO MULTIPLE ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS ARISING FROM THE RELEASE OF LARGE AMOUNTS OF EFFLUENTS WITHOUT ADEQUATE TREATMENT AND/OR WITH INTENSITY, IN CONCENTRATION AND CHARACTERISTICS THAT DISAGREE WITH THE STANDARDS ESTABLIS"@pt ;
