<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27830> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "A POSSIBLE METHODOLOGICAL BIAS HAS BEEN IDENTIFIED IN STUDIES THAT HAVE BEEN CONDUCTED TO TEST THE ECOLOGICAL APPEARANCE HYPOTHESIS (EAH), WHICH AIM TO COMPARE THE HIGH USE VALUE (UV) OF PLANT SPECIES MENTIONED BY POPULATIONS THROUGH PHYTOSOCIOLOGY. SINCE LOCAL ECOLOGICAL KNOWLEDGE (LEK), DESPITE ITS PREDICTIVE CAPACITY, IS SUBJECT TO THE INFLUENCE OF SOCIOECONOMIC FACTORS SUCH AS AGE, GENDER, INCOME, LENGTH OF RESIDENCE, AS WELL AS THE INTERACTION OR LOSS OF INTERACTION WITH NATURAL ENVIRONMENT"@pt,
        "SHARKS ARE POPULARLY KNOWN FOR HUMAN INCIDENT RECORDS AROUND THE WORLD. ALTHOUGH RARE, THESE CASES GENERATE FEAR ABOUT THESE ANIMALS. THIS HAS BEEN MAGNIFIED BY THE MEDIA, AT LEAST BY THE JAWS EFFECT. HOWEVER, MOST SPECIES OF TUBERS ARE NOT AGGRESSIVE AND ARE NOT ABLE TO SUBMIT TO HUMANS. IN BRAZIL, CASES OF SHARK INCIDENTS WERE CONCENTRATED IN PERNAMBUCO, TOTALING 66 AS OF 1992. OF THIS TOTAL, 62 OCCURRING IN BEACHES OF THE METROPOLITAN REGION OF RECIFE - RMR AND 4 IN THE FERNANDO DE NORONHA AR"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "30AUG2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "30AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "A PERCEPÇÃO DE DISPONIBILIDADE COMO FERRAMENTA PARA TESTAR A HIPÓTESE DA APARÊNCIA ECOLÓGICA E PARA ANALISAR A CAPACIDADE PREDITIVA SOBRE A DISPONIBILIDADE DE PLANTAS ÚTEIS"@pt,
        "A PROBLEMÁTICA DE INCIDENTES COM TUBARÕES EM PERNAMBUCO, BRASIL"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JONAS_EUGENIO_RODRIGUES_DA_SILVA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/THIAGO_BRAZ_BARBOSA_DE_SOUSA> ;
