<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27831> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INFORMATION ON THE TEMPORAL DYNAMICS OF THE FISHING FLEETS HAS BEEN WIDELY USED TO INFER MANY ASPECTS OF FISHERIES SCIENCE, SUCH AS THE EVALUATION OF SPECIES DISTRIBUTION PATTERNS, INVESTIGATE IMPACTS ON HABITATS DUE TO FISHING EFFORT, IN DISTRIBUTION OF FISHING VESSELS, AMONG OTHERS. IN THIS WORK WE DESCRIBED THE SPATIAL DISTRIBUTION AND CATCH COMPOSITION OF THE ARTISANAL AND RECREATIONAL FLEETS OF THE FERNANDO DE NORONHA ARCHIPELAGO, BASED ON GPS DATA. FOR THE DESCRIPTION OF THE SPATIAL DISTRI"@pt,
        "THE MAIN MOTIVATION FOR THE CULTIVATION OF THE PLANT SPECIES MALPIGHIA EMARGINATA D.C IS IN THE COMMERCIALIZATION OF THE FRUITS FOR THE AGRO-INDUSTRIES THAT EXPLOIT THE RIPE PULP AND THE HIGH CONTENT OF VITAMIN C OF THE UNRIPE FRUIT. INTERESTINGLY, THIRTY-ONE POPULAR NAMES FOR THE SPECIES ARE REPORTED IN THE LITERATURE. IN BRAZIL, THE TYPICAL CULTIVATION OF THE CROP IS IMPORTANT TO GENERATE INCOME IN FAMILY FARMING. THEREFORE, THE PURPOSE OF THIS STUDY IS TO EXPAND KNOWLEDGE ABOUT THE SPECIES M."@pt ;
