<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27834> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENTE STUDY AIM TO CHARACTERIZE ABUNDANCE, DISTRIBUTION AND SOME BIOECOLOGICAL ASPECTS OF CRUSTACEAN FAUNA OFF PERNAMBUCO STATE, NORTHEASTERN BRAZIL, BASED ON DEEP-SEA FISHING SURVEYS CONDUCTED BETWEEN 2014 AND 2018 USING AS FISHING GEAR BAITED BOTTON TRAPS (COVO) AT DEPTHS RANGING FROM 218 TO 600 M. A TOTAL OF 690 INDIVIDUALS WERE COLLECTED REPRESENTED BY TWELVE SPECIES, DISTRIBUTED IN TWO ORDENS: DECAPODA AND ISOPODA. DECAPODS COMPRISED 9 ESPECIES: STENOCIONOPS SPINOSISSIMUS, ROCHINIA C"@pt,
        "TO DEAL WITH HEALTH PROBLEMS, HUMANS USE HERBAL MEDICINES. ACCORDING TO THE LITERATURE, THE SELECTION OF PLANTS IS INFLUENCED BY THEIR ORGANOLEPTIC PROPERTIES, SUCH AS SMELL. THE SMELL OF A PLANT CONSISTS OF A MIXTURE OF VOLATILE ORGANIC COMPOUNDS (VOCS) THAT HAVE BIOLOGICAL AND PHARMACOLOGICAL ACTIVITIES. HOWEVER, STUDIES THAT AIM TO UNDERSTAND THE INFLUENCE OF SMELL FOR THE SELECTION OF MEDICINAL PLANTS ARE BASED ONLY ON HUMAN OLFACTORY PERCEPTION, WITHOUT A DETAILED AND INTEGRATED QUANTITATIV"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "29AUG2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
