<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27838> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "COUNTRIES ARE INCREASINGLY CONCERNED ABOUT REDUCING EMISSIONS OF CO2 AND OTHER GREENHOUSE GASES. WITH THIS, THE NEED ARISES TO MEET THE WORLD DEMAND FOR ENERGY, ENSURING THE SUSTAINABLE USE OF NATURAL RESOURCES, LEADING TO A GROWING INTEREST IN ALTERNATIVE ENERGY SOURCES. SOLAR ENERGY IS AN IMPORTANT SOURCE OF RENEWABLE ENERGY, IN ADDITION TO BEING A CLEAN AND ABUNDANT SOURCE, AND IN TROPICAL COUNTRIES, SUCH AS BRAZIL, THE USE OF THIS ENERGY SOURCE IS VIABLE IN PRACTICALLY THE ENTIRE TERRITORY D"@pt,
        "THIS WORK DEALS WITH THE REPRODUCTIVE STRATEGIES OF THREAD HERRING, OPISTHONEMA OGLINUM, A TELEOST FISH BELONGING TO THE CLUPEIDAE FAMILY, ABUNDANT IN THE BRAZILIAN NORTHEAST COAST. SAMPLING WAS CARRIED OUT IN THE NORTHERN COAST OF THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO BETWEEN MAY 2016 AND APRIL 2018. A TOTAL OF 497 SPECIMENS WERE COLLECTED AND SEXED, 304 GONADS SECTIONED FOR MATURATIONAL EVALUATION. FEMALES WERE MORE FREQUENT THAN MALES, WITH A SEX RATIO OF 1.5 FEMALES: 1 MALE. THE TOTAL LENGTH OF THE FEMALE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "18JUN2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "28FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DINÂMICA REPRODUTIVA DA SARDINHA-LAJE OPISTHONEMA OGLINUM, LESUEUR, 1818 CAPTURADA NO LITORAL NORTE DE PERNAMBUCO, BRASIL"@pt,
        "GERAÇÃO DE ENERGIA FOTOVOLTAICA FLUTUANTE EM LAGO ARTIFICIAL E SUAS LIMITAÇÕES AMBIENTAIS E SOCIAIS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2022"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JESSICA_GOUVEIA_LIRA>,
        <http://example.com/capes#author/MARIA_ESTER_RIBEIRO_SIMONI> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIA_E_TECNOLOGIA_AMBIENTAL>,
        <http://example.com/capes#program/RECURSOS_PESQUEIROS_E_AQUICULTURA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/27839> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE AIM OF THIS THESIS IS TO DESCRIBE THE VULNERABILITY TO FISHING GEAR (BOTTOM GILLNET), TO KNOW THE TEMPORAL DISTRIBUTION OF THE CAPTURES OF THESE ELASMOBRANCHS AND TO IDENTIFY THE HABITAT USE OF THE MOST ABUNDANT ELASMOBRANCH SPECIES IN THE BOTTOM GILLNET BYCATCH (RHIZOPRIONODON POROSUS AND CARCHARHINUS ACRONOTUS) ON THE COAST OF PERNAMBUCO. BETWEEN 2010 AND 2015, A TOTAL OF 176 SPECIMENS OF ELASMOBRANCHS WERE CAPTURED, 6 SPECIES (RHIZOPRIONODON POROSUS, CARCHARHINUS ACRONOTUS, CARCHARHINUS L"@pt,
        "UNDERSTAND THE STRUCTURE AND DYNAMICS OF THE VEGETATION COVER OF THE CAATINGAS, IN THE LAST 30 YEARS, ON THE STUDY MICROBASIN AND THE POSSIBILITY OF OFFERING SUBSIDIES FOR IN-DEPTH STUDIES AIMED AT LAND USE PROJECTIONS, INCLUDING THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN DEFORESTATION PRACTICES AND/OR CONSERVATION OF THE CAATINGAS WERE THE MAIN SCIENTIFIC QUESTIONS FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF THIS MASTER'S THESIS. INITIALLY, A SYSTEMATIC REVIEW WAS DEVELOPED, BASED ON THE INVESTIGATION OF SCIENTIFIC ARTICLES PUBLISHE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "02MAY2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "26FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
