<http://example.com/capes#thesis/28482> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "OBESITY IS A DISEASE THAT AFFECTS A LARGE PART OF THE WORLD'S POPULATION. EPIDEMIOLOGICAL STUDIES REPORT THAT OBESITY GROWS EVERY YEAR, CAUSING A SERIES OF OTHER DISEASES, SUCH AS DIABETES AND CARDIOVASCULAR DISEASES. RESEARCH ON PHYSICAL EXERCISE SEEKS TO UNDERSTAND THE BENEFITS OF THIS PRACTICE, WHICH SHOULD BE PART OF A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE TO REDUCE THE OCCURRENCE OF DISEASES. AMONG THE BIOCHEMICAL MODIFICATIONS CAUSED BY EXERCISE ARE THE INCREASE IN THE LEVEL OF CIRCULATING ACETATE AND THE POS"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "19DEC2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "EFEITOS DO EXERCÍCIO FÍSICO SOBRE OS RECEPTORES GPR-41 E GPR-43 NA INFLAMAÇÃO E RESISTÊNCIA À INSULINA EM CAMUNDONGOS"@pt ;
