<http://example.com/capes#thesis/28484> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BIOACTIVE COMPOUNDS FROM FUNGI AND FILAMENTOUS BACTERIA CAN BE USED BY PHARMACEUTICAL, AGRICULTURAL, OR FOOD INDUSTRIES, AND THEIR DISCOVERY, IDENTIFICATION, AND PRODUCTION ARE CLOSELY LINKED TO THE METHODOLOGIES APPLIED IN THE PROCESS. CURRENT KNOWLEDGE OF GENOME MINING HAS SHOWN THAT MANY GENES ENCODING BIOSYNTHETIC PATHWAYS OF THESE MICROORGANISMS ARE SILENCED, THUS LIMITING THEIR ABILITY TO PRODUCE METABOLITES UNDER LABORATORY CONDITIONS, WITHOUT ADEQUATE ENVIRONMENTAL STIMULI. THE USE OF DN"@pt ;
