<http://example.com/capes#thesis/28485> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ACUTE PROMYELOCYTIC LEUKEMIA (APL) IS A RARE SUBTYPE OF ACUTE MYELOID LEUKEMIA. DESPITE HAVING A GREATER POTENTIAL FOR CURE WITH ADEQUATE THERAPEUTIC AND TRANSFUSIONAL SUPPORT, EARLY MORTALITY FROM HEMOSTASIS DISORDERS IS STILL THE MAIN CAUSE OF THE LOW OVERALL SURVIVAL RATE. THE STUDY AIMED TO DEFINE THE IMPACT OF FACTORS ASSOCIATED WITH TRANSFUSION NEEDS IN PATIENTS WITH APL AND ASSESS THE HEMOTHERAPY COSTS IN TREATING THE DISEASE. BLOOD TRANSFUSION DATA WERE COLLECTED FROM THE BLOOD BANK SYST"@pt ;
