<http://example.com/capes#thesis/28486> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE BEETLE EUCHROMA GIGANTEA (LINNAEUS, 1758), (COLEOPTERA: BUPRESTIDAE) IS A PEST SPECIES WITH HIGH CHROMOSOMAL POLYMORPHISM IN NUMBER AND MORPHOLOGY. RECENTLY, THREE EVOLUTIONARY LINEAGES WERE DESCRIBED FOR BRAZIL, WHICH WERE IDENTIFIED THROUGH PHYLOGENETIC ANALYSIS OF A FRAGMENT OF THE CYTOCHROME OXIDASE GENE SUBUNIT I. IT ALSO HAS A MULTIPLE SEXUAL SYSTEM (WITH FIVE, SIX OR EIGHT CHROMOSOMES), BEING A POSSIBLE MODEL FOR ANALYZING THE EVOLUTION OF SEX CHROMOSOMES. IN THESE CHROMOSOMES, THE AC"@pt ;
