<http://example.com/capes#thesis/28487> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE APPLICATION OF ORGANIC SUBSTRATES AND EFFICIENT ARBUSCULAR MYCORRHIZAL FUNGI (AMF) IS A PROMISING ALTERNATIVE TO COMPOSE LOW-COST PROTOCOLS IN ORDER TO ENHANCE THE ANTIOXIDANT ACTIVITY AND THE BIOSYNTHESIS OF PLANT SECONDARY COMPOUNDS. SUCH BIOMOLECULES ARE ATTAINED TO THE ANXIOLYTIC, ANTIDEPRESSANT AND ANTIOXIDANT EFFECTS OF PASSIFLORA ALATA CURTIS EXTRACTS, A SPECIES USED BY THE HERBAL MEDICINES INDUSTRIES OF ANXIOLYTICS. HOWEVER, SUCH COMPOUNDS ARE SYNTHESIZED AT LOW CONCENTRATIONS IN THE"@pt ;
