    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GESTÃO_EMPRESARIAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2914> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PERIODONTITIS IS A CHRONIC INFLAMMATORY DISEASE CAUSED BY THE PRESENCE OF A BACTERIAL BIOFILM COMPOSED OF SEVERAL SPECIES OF MICROORGANISMS. IN THE PRESENT STUDY, THE ANTI-INFLAMMATORY PROPERTIES ATTRIBUTED TO CYSTEINE PROTEASES (LPP2) OBTAINED FROM CALOTROPIS PROCERA LATEX WAS INVESTIGATED IN A MODEL OF CHRONIC PERIODONTITIS IN RATS. FOR THE INDUCTION OF PERIODONTAL DISEASE, THE LIGATURE MODEL WAS USED IN WHICH A SURGICAL THREAD WAS ATTACHED TO THE DENTITION TO FORM A BACTERIAL BIOFILM. NEXT, T"@pt ;
