<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2917> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "YELLOW FEVER (YF) HAS BEEN ENDEMIC AND ENZOOTIC DISEASE IN 47 COUNTRIES OF AMERICA AND AFRICA. EARLY VIRUS DETECTION IN SENTINELS NON-HUMAN PRIMATES (NHP) IS ESSENTIAL TO IMPLEMENT PREVENTIVE MEASURES TO AVOID THE HUMAN DISEASE, THUS THIS STUDY AIMED TO EVALUATE THE SYLVATIC YELLOW FEVER SURVEILLANCE PROGRAM IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO. CURRENTLY, FOUR SENTINEL UNITS (SU) ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR RECEIVING, PREPARING AND DELIVERING THE ORGAN SAMPLES FROM DECEASED NHP TO THE REFERENCE LABORATORY. FROM "@pt ;
