<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2918> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO CHARACTERIZE THE VIRULENCE AND ANTIMICROBIAL RESISTANCE OF CAMPYLOBACTER SPP. FROM CATTLE AND SHEEP FROM NORTHEASTERN BRAZIL. THE PRESENCE OF VIRULENCE GENES (CDTA, CDTB, CDTC, CADF, RACR, DNAJ, CIAB, PLDA, WLAN E VIRB11) WAS INVESTIGATED BY POLYMERASE CHAIN REACTION. THE GENETIC POTENTIAL OF ANTIMICROBIAL RESISTANCE IN SHEEP SAMPLES WAS INVESTIGATED BY 23S RDNA SEQUENCING TO IDENTIFY MUTATIONS A2074G AND A2075G AND FRAGMENTS OF THE GYRA GENE TO IDENTIFY MUTATI"@pt ;
