<http://example.com/capes#thesis/2920> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "LEISHMANIASIS ARE ANTHROPOZOONOSIS CAUSED BY OBLIGATE INTRACELLULAR PARASITES BELONGING TO THE GENUS LEISHMANIA AND SUBGENUS LEISHMANIA, VIANIA AND MUNDINIA THAT AFFECT AROUND 350 MILLION PEOPLE AROUND THE WORLD. THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO IS HISTORICALLY ENDEMIC FOR THE TWO MAIN CLINICAL PRESENTATIONS OF THE DISEASE: VISCERAL LEISHMANIASIS (LV) AND TEGUMENTARY LEISHMANIASIS (LT). THE DOMESTIC DOG IS STILL CONSIDERED THE MAIN URBAN HOST FOR LEISHMANIA INFANTUM AND SIGNIFICANT IN THE TRANSMISSION OF"@pt ;
