<http://example.com/capes#thesis/29417> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH AIMS TO INVESTIGATE THE WAY LANGUAGE IS CONCEIVED IN THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE (EL) TEXTBOOKS OF THE LANGUAGE AND INFORMATICS PROGRAM (PROLINFO), FOCUSING ON THE RELATIONSHIP OF THIS CONCEPTION WITH THE WAY SOCIAL ACTORS ARE REPRESENTED. THEREFORE, WE STARTED OUR WORK TRYING TO DESCRIBE THE FOUR VOLUMES THAT MAKE UP THE EL COLLECTION, CONSIDERING THE PARAMETERS OF THE COMMON EUROPEAN FRAMEWORK OF REFERENCE FOR LANGUAGES (QCERL) AND THEIR RELATIONSHIP TO THE FIVE LANGUAGE SKILLS: READING"@pt ;
