<http://example.com/capes#thesis/29421> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FROM THE CRADLE OF ITS PHILOSOPHICAL ORIGINS TO CONTEMPORANEITY, GRAMMAR HAS HISTORICALLY BEEN THE MAIN TARGET OF LINGUISTIC STUDIES DISCUSSED IN SEVERAL THEORIES. LIKEWISE, IN THE HISTORY OF FOREIGN LANGUAGE TEACHING METHODOLOGIES, GRAMMAR WAS A PROTAGONIST IN THE FIRST METHODS OF TEACHING A FOREIGN LANGUAGE. AFTER THE EMERGENCE OF THE COMMUNICATIVE METHOD WHICH BECAME A GENERAL THEORETICAL PRINCIPLE AND A DOMINANT PRESENCE IN SPANISH AS A FOREIGN LANGUAGE MANUALS (SFL), SEVERAL OTHER METHODOLO"@pt ;
