    capes:hasAbstract "\"INTRODUCTION: FAMILY FUNCTIONING MAY BE INVOLVED IN BEHAVIORS AND DECISION MAKING RELATED TO ADOLESCENT HEALTH. OBJECTIVE: TO INVESTIGATE PERCEIVED FAMILY COHESION AND ADAPTABILITY AND ITS ASSOCIATION WITH ORAL HEALTH, SOCIODEMOGRAPHIC FACTORS, USE OF DENTAL SERVICES AND ANTHROPOMETRIC DATA IN ADOLESCENTS. METHODS: CROSS-SECTIONAL STUDY WITH A CALCULATED AND RANDOMIZED SAMPLE OF 790 ADOLESCENTS FROM STATE PUBLIC SCHOOLS IN CAMARAGIBE-PE. THE ADOLESCENTS WERE CLINICALLY EXAMINED FOR CARIES PREVA"@pt ;
