<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3453> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CRACKED TEETH ARE CONSIDERED A DIAGNOSTIC CHALLENGE TO CLINICIANS DUE TO THE VARIABLE SIGNS AND SYMPTOMS THAT THEY CAN PRESENT. IN ADDITION, THE CURRENTLY AVAILABLE DIAGNOSTIC METHODS HAVE SEVERAL LIMITATIONS IN PROVIDING A DEFINITIVE DIAGNOSIS FOR THESE CASES. SEVERAL FACTORS, INCLUDING ROOT CANAL INSTRUMENTATION, HAVE BEEN ASSOCIATED WITH THE INDUCTION OF DENTINAL MICROCRACKS. REPORTS FROM RESEARCH DATA, HOWEVER, HAVE BEEN INCONSISTENT CONCERNING THE INCIDENCE OF MICROCRACKS AFTER ROOT CANAL P"@pt ;
