<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3653> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY (CSR) IS POINTED IN THE KNOWN LITERATURE AS A BEHAVIOUR THAT A COMPANY MUST HAVE TO DEVELOP AND SUSTAIN COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGES IN A LONG TERM PERIOD. IN THE BUSINESS WORLD THERE IS A RANGE OF NORMATIVE TO GUARANTEE THE LEGALITY OF THE RELATION BETWEEN EMPLOYERS AND WORKERS. THE PURPOSE OF THIS WORK IS TO RESPOND THE FOLLOW QUESTION: WHICH ASPECT OF THE CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY HAS CONTRIBUTED TO BRING JUDICIAL PROCESS TO COURT? IN ORDER TO ANSWER THIS Q"@pt ;
