    capes:hasAbstract "THE USE OF LEGUMES IN THE PRODUCTION SYSTEM CAN BE AN ALTERNATIVE TO INCREASE THE PRODUCTION AND THE QUALITY OF THE FORAGE RESULTING FROM THE PARTICIPATION OF THE LEGUME IN THE DIET OF THE ANIMAL AND THE EFFECTS RELATED TO THE BIOLOGICAL FIXATION OF NITROGEN. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS THE CHARACTERIZATION, EVALUATION AND QUANTIFICATION OF THE GENETIC DIVERGENCE OF MACROPTILIUM ACCESSES, FOR USE IN ANIMAL FEED, BY MEANS OF MORPHOAGRONOMIC AND CHEMICAL-BROMATOLOGICAL CHARACTERS. FOR THIS, 64 "@pt ;
