<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3713> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FISH FARMING IS ONE OF THE FASTEST GROWING PRODUCTION ACTIVITIES IN THE WORLD IN THE LAST 50 YEARS. IN BRAZIL IT IS THE FASTEST GROWING ANIMAL PRODUCTION ACTIVITY DUE TO THE GREAT AMOUNT OF FRESH WATER, FAVORABLE CLIMATE AND QUANTITY OF NATIVE SPECIES WITH EXCELLENT POTENTIAL FOR AQUACULTURE. IN THIS SENSE, THE SÃO FRANCISCO VALLEY PRESENTS AN EXCELLENT ECONOMIC POTENTIAL IN WHICH BOTH COMMERCIAL AND SUBSISTENCE FISHING IS PRACTICED, ALLOWING SPACE FOR BOTH NATIVE AND EXOTIC SPECIES, SUCH AS NIL"@pt ;
