<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3716> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE AEROMONAS GENUS IS ONE OF THE MAIN CAUSER AGENT OF ECONOMIC LOSSES IN FISH FARMING. AS AN OPPORTUNISTIC PATHOGEN, IT MAY CAUSE TISSUE NECROSIS AND SEPTICEMIA IN IMMUNOSUPPRESSED AQUATIC ANIMALS. THE PATHOGENICITY OF THIS BACTERIUM IS LINKED TO SOME VIRULENCE FACTORS, SUCH AS BIOFILM FORMATION. SALINE STRESS IS ONE OF THE FACTORS THAT FAVORS THE FORMATION OF THESE COLONIES IN THE AQUATIC ENVIRONMENT AND, CONSEQUENTLY, THE INCREASE OF INFECTIONS. WHEN THESE INFECTIONS ARE ASSOCIATED WITH BIOFI"@pt ;
