<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3723> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THE 21ST CENTURY, COUNTRIES ARE INCREASINGLY SEEKING CLEANER RENEWABLE SOURCES TO REPLACE FOSSIL FUEL CONSUMPTION, DUE TO THE PHENOMENON CALLED GLOBAL WARMING. THEREFORE, BIODIESEL IS ONE OF THE OUTPUTS FOR THE MITIGATION OF GREENHOUSE GASES, MAINLY CO2. BECAUSE THIS BIOFUEL IS CONSIDERED ZERO CARBON. BRAZIL HAS A VERY FAVORABLE CLIMATE FOR THE CREATION OF FISH SUCH AS TILAPIA. TILAPIA BIODIESEL IS PRODUCED THROUGH THE FISH'S RESIDUAL OIL. THIS OIL WAS REMOVED BY THE PRESSING AND MACERATION M"@pt ;
