<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3730> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE GROWTH OF THE RESIDENTIAL AUTOMATION MARKET EVIDENCES THE INCREASING NEED OF THE HUMAN BEING TO OPTIMIZE TIME AND EFFORT SPENT ON MECHANICAL AND REPETITIVE TASKS. IN ADDITION, THE SEARCH FOR SECURITY AND ECONOMY OF RESOURCES, SUCH AS ELECTRIC POWER AND POTABLE WATER, BOOSTED THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE AUTOMATION SECTOR. CURRENTLY, AUTONOMOUS MECHANISMS ARE USED THAT PERFORM TASKS ALONE AND THE GREAT CHALLENGE IS THE INTEGRATION OF THESE INTO A SINGLE SYSTEM THAT ALLOWS GREATER EASE OF CONTROL AN"@pt ;
