<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3785> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TUBERCULOSIS (TB) IS CAUSED BY MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS (MTB) OF MEDICAL IMPORTANCE. THE CURRENT TREATMENT OF THE DISEASE IS EFFECTIVE, BUT HAS ADVERSE EFFECTS. CHITOSAN (CS) IS A BIOPOLYMER AND HAS BEEN TESTED AS ADJUTANT TO MINIMIZE THE EFFECTS OF TOXICITY OF DIFFERENT DRUGS. IN THIS WORK, WE STUDIED THE ADJUTANT EFFECT OF CS ON THE DRUGS ISONIAZID (INH) AND ETHAMBUTOL (ETH), IN ORDER TO MINIMIZE ITS TOXIC ACTION AND POTENTIATE THE ANTIMYCOBACTERIN ACTIVITY. IN THE PRESENT STUDY, CONJUGATES "@pt ;
