<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3890> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AMONG THE REPRESENTATIVES OF THE MEGAFAUNA OF THE PLEISTOCENE, THE TOXODONTÍDEOS CONSTITUTE \"NATIVE UNGULATE\" EXTINCT MAMMALS, THAT INHABITED ALL AMERICA UNTIL THE END OF THE PLEISTOCENE AND BEGINNING OF THE HOLOCENE. ALTHOUGH TOXODONTID REMAINS ARE VERY FREQUENT IN THE BRAZILIAN PLEISTOCENE FOSSIL RECORD, THERE IS NO CONSENSUS ON THE TAXONOMY INVOLVING REMAINS DESCRIBED AS PIAUHYTHERIUM AND TRIGODONOPS. TOXODON IS CONSIDERED TO BE REPRESENTED ONLY BY T. PLATENSIS, WHICH IS WIDELY FOUND IN SOUTH"@pt ;
