<http://example.com/capes#thesis/3892> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PALEOICTIOFAUNA OF THE ARARIPE IS KNOWN WORLDWIDE FOR THE EXCEPTIONAL PRESERVATION AND DIVERSITY OF FOSSILS. A LARGE NUMBER OF RESEARCHERS HAVE ALREADY CONDUCTED STUDIES ADDRESSING THE TAXONOMY, HOWEVER, FEW PUBLICATIONS ADDRESS THE PALEOECOLOGY OF FISH. STUDIES PERFORMED IN THE N-NE PORTION OF THE BASIN IN THE STATE OF CEARÁ ARE MUCH MORE EXPRESSIVE THAN THOSE PERFORMED IN ARARIPE PERNAMBUCANO (S-SW OF THE BASIN). THEREFORE, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY IS TO PERFORM A SURVEY OF THE DIVERSIT"@pt ;
