<http://example.com/capes#thesis/390> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SURVIVAL DATA COME FROM SEVERAL APPLICATIONS; SUCH AS, EQUIPMENT FAILURES, RELIABILITY, PATIENT LIFETIME AFTER A MEDICAL DIAGNOSIS AND ADVANCEMENT OF CANCER CELLS. THE RESULTING DATA ARE POSITIVE-VALUED AND ARE OFTEN CENSORED OF HEAVY TAILS. THIS LATTER FACT SUGGESTS THAT TAILORED TOOLS ARE NECESSARY FOR MODELLING SURVIVAL DATA BEHAVIOR. IN PARTICULAR, THERE IS A NEED FOR FLEXIBLE MODELS; INFERENTIAL METHODS, SUCH AS ESTIMATION AND GOODNESS-OF-FIT (GOF); AND CONDITIONAL REPRESENTATION (E.G., REG"@pt ;
