<http://example.com/capes#thesis/391> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CIRCULAR STATISTIC IS AN IMPORTANT BRANCH OF THE STATISTIC WHICH HAS BEEN DEMANDED BY SEVERAL APPLICATIONS. PROVIDING NEW MODELS DEFINED ON CIRCULAR SUPPORT TO DESCRIBE ASYMMETRIC BEHAVIORS ALONG WITH THEIR INFERENCE AND REGRESSION MODELS ARE ALSO REQUIRED. THIS THESIS ADVANCES IN THIS SENSE. CHAPTER 2 ADRESSES THE PROPOSAL OF A NEW CIRCULAR DISTRIBUTION, CALLED EXPONENTIATED CARDIOID (EC). SOME OF ITS MATHEMATICAL PROPERTIES ARE ALSO PROPOSED, SUCH AS TRIGONOMETRIC MOMENTS, KURTOSIS AND SKEWNES"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "14MAR2018:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
