<http://example.com/capes#thesis/392> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AUTOREGRESSIVE (AR) MODELS PROVIDE A MEANS TO APPROXIMATE THE SPECTRUM OF A SIGNAL. THE GREATER THE ORDER OF THE MODEL, THE BETTER THE APPROXIMATION. IN THIS WORK, WE FACE THE PROBLEM OF DESIGNING COMPUTATIONALLY EFFICIENT METHODS FOR PARAMETER ESTIMATION IN 1ST AND 2ND ORDER AR PROCESSES. FIRST, WE REVIEW HOW THE SPECTRAL DISTRIBUTION PROVIDES AN ANALYSIS OF THE VARIANCE OF A TIME SERIES BY REVEALING ITS FREQUENCY COMPONENTS. THEN, WE TACKLE THE LOW-COMPLEXITY ESTIMATION PROBLEM IN THE AR(1) CA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20JUL2018:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "LOW-COMPLEXITY METHODS FOR AUTOREGRESSIVE SIGNAL MODELING"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2018"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ABEL_PEREIRA_DE_MACEDO_BORGES_JUNIOR> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/393> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THIS THESIS WE GENERALIZE THE BETA REGRESSION MODEL WITH MEASUREMENT ERRORS (CARRASCO, 2014) PROPOSING A MODEL WITH NON-LINEAR FUNCTIONAL FORMS. THREE ESTIMATION METHODS DENOTED BY APPROXIMATE MAXIMUM LIKELIHOOD, APPROXIMATE MAXIMUM PSEUDO-LIKELIHOOD, AND REGRESSION CALIBRATION WERE EVALUATED. TO EVALUATE THE ESTIMATION METHODOLOGIES, WE PERFORMED A MONTE CARLO SIMULATION STUDY WITH DIFFERENT SCENARIOS. IT WAS POSSIBLE TO SHOW THAT THE APPROXIMATE MAXIMUM LIKELIHOOD AND APPROXIMATE MAXIMUM PS"@pt ;
