<http://example.com/capes#thesis/394> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE BETA REGRESSION MODEL INTRODUCED BY FERRARI AND CRIBARI (2004) IS USEFUL FOR SITUATIONS WHERE THE RESPONSE IS RESTRICTED TO THE INTERVAL (0,1) AND OSPINA AND FERRARI (2012) CONSIDERS THE ISSUE OF MODELING FRACTIONAL DATA OBSERVED ON [0,1), (0,1] E [0,1]. OUR GOAL IN THIS THESIS IS TO INTRODUCE INFLATED KUMARASWAMY DISTRIBUTIONS, IN ADDITION TO PROPOSING INFLATED KUMARASWAMY REGRESSION MODELS THAT ALLOW MODELING DATA IN THE INTERVALS [0,1), (0,1] AND [0,1], AS WELL AS TO APPROACH THE RESPECTI"@pt ;
