<http://example.com/capes#thesis/395> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "STATISTICAL TOOLS FOR MODELING COVARIANCE STRUCTURES HAVE BEEN SHOWN USEFUL IN MEDICINE FOR STUDIES IN GENETICS. IN THAT CONTEXT, FACTOR ANALYSIS MODELS STAND OUT FOR ITS ABILITY IN IDENTI- FYING LATENT FACTORS CAPABLE OF REDUCING DATA DIMENSIONALITY AND EXPLAINING OBSERVED VARIABILITY. USUALLY, LATENT FACTORS ARE INTERPRETED AS UNOBSERVED PHYSIOLOGICAL MECHANISMS UNDERLYING THE STUDIED PHENOMENON. CONFIRMATORY FACTOR ANALYSIS MODELS ARE CHARACTERIZED BY ALLOWING THE RESEARCHER TO PRE-SPECIFY MO"@pt ;
