<http://example.com/capes#thesis/396> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTEGER-VALUED TIME SERIES IS A TOPIC THAT HAS RECEIVED MUCH ATTENTION IN THE LAST THREE DECADES. THE REASON FOR THIS IS THE NEED OF APPROPRIATE MODELS FOR THE STATISTICAL ANALYSIS OF COUNT TIME SERIES. COUNT TIME SERIES OCCUR NATURALLY IN SEVERAL FIELDS. IN MEDICINE, THE NUMBER OF PATIENTS IN A HOSPITAL AT SPECIFIC POINT OF TIME OR THE NUMBER OF EPILEPTIC SEIZURES A PATIENT SUFFERS EACH DAY. IN ECONOMICS, THE NUMBER OF INSURANCE CLAIMS A COMPANY RECEIVES DURING EACH DAY, DISCRETE TRANSACTION PR"@pt ;
