<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4010> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FACED WITH UNFAVORABLE CONDITIONS SUCH AS DROUGHT AND SALINITY, PLANTS CAN PRESENT STRATEGIES AT THEIR SEVERAL LEVELS OF THE ORGANIZATION TO TOLERATE STRESS. AMONG SUCH STRATEGIES, LEAF ANATOMICAL FEATURES STAND OUT SINCE THE PHYSIOLOGICAL PERFORMANCE IS RELATED TO THE ANATOMY OF THE LEAF, MAINLY BECAUSE IT IS THE ORGAN DIRECTLY INVOLVED WITH PHOTOSYNTHESIS. ALSO BEING THE ORGAN WITH THE GREATEST PLASTICITY OF RESPONSES, ANATOMICAL ADJUSTMENTS CAN BE AN IMPORTANT TRAIT OF SPECIES TOLERANT TO ADV"@pt ;
