    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4011> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "UNDERSTANDING THE ADAPTIVE PROCESSES OF SPECIES IN RESTRICTIVE ENVIRONMENTS, SUCH AS THE CAATINGA, WHICH HAVE A LONG DRY SEASON, IS ESSENTIAL TO UNDERSTAND BIOGEOGRAPHIC PATTERNS OF THIS DRY FOREST AND TO ELABORATE CONSERVATION STRATEGIES IN THESE ENVIRONMENTS. INTEGRATIVE STUDIES, AS REPRODUCTIVE ECOLOGY AND POPULATION GENETICS ARE NEEDED TO COMPREHEND HOW BIOTIC AND ABIOTIC FACTORS SHAPE SPECIES DISTRIBUTION. THUS, THIS THESIS AIMED TO ANALYZE HOW THE BIOTIC AND ABIOTIC ENVIRONMENT INFLUENCES "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AMBIENTE E RELAÇÕES ECOLÓGICAS MOLDANDO TRAÇOS FLORAIS E GENÉTICOS DE BIONIA PEDICELLATA, UMA FABACEAE ENDÊMICA DA CAATINGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/CAMILA_MIRANDA_BARBOSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4012> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CAESALPINIA GROUP IS FORMED BY 27 GENERA AND 225 SPECIES WITH PANTROPICAL DISTRIBUTION IN SEASONALLY DRY TROPICAL FORESTS (SDTF), MAINLY IN THE AMERICAN CONTINENT. KARYOTYPICALLY THE GROUP IS CHARACTERIZED BY NUMERICAL STABILITY (2N = 24), BUT WAS OBSERVED A HIGH DIVERSITY IN THE AMOUNT AND DISTRIBUTION OF HETEROCHROMATIN BANDS. IN THIS WORK, A NEW CHARACTERIZATION OF THE GROUP WAS MADE FOR 12 NEW SPECIES, WHICH SHOWED CMA+ / DAPI- AND CMA0 / DAPIPERICENTROMERIC BANDS, ASSOCIATED WITH THEIR "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "18FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ANÁLISE DA DIVERSIFICAÇÃO DA HETEROCROMATINA DO GRUPO CAESALPINIA (LEGUMINOSAE) BASEADO EM DADOS CITOMOLECULARES"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/YENNIFER_CAROLINA_MATA_SUCRE> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4013> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE ANATOMY OF SPECIES MAY VARY IN RESPONSE TO ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITIONS, ESPECIALLY THOSE THAT OCCUR IN CAATINGA SUBJECT TO SEMI-ARID CLIMATE. THUS, THE SPECIES CAN ADJUST MORPHOLOGICALLY TO SURVIVE IN THIS ENVIRONMENT. IN THE FIRST CHAPTER OF THIS DISSERTATION, THE LEAF AND STEM ANATOMY OF TWO MALVACEAE SPECIES OCCURRING IN THE CAATINGA WAS COMPARED FOR TAXONOMIC AND ECOLOGICAL PURPOSES. IN THE SECOND CHAPTER, IT WAS VERIFIED WHETHER THE ENVIRONMENTAL CONDITIONS OF TWO DIFFERENT AREAS OF CAATIN"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28AUG2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ANATOMIA E HISTOQUÍMICA DE FOLHA E CAULE DE HERISSANTIA CRISPA (L.) BRIZICKY E HERISSANTIA TIUBAE (K.SCHUM.) BRIZICKY (MALVACEAE) EM DIFERENTES ÁREAS DA CAATINGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/PAMELA_CLEMENTE_DE_MENESES_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4014> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE HERBIVORY IS ONE OF THE MOST DOMINANT ECOLOGICAL INTERACTIONS IN NATURE, WITH EFFECTS ON THE FUNCTIONING AND STRUCTURING OF FOREST ECOSYSTEMS. PLANTS ARE NOT INERT TO HERBIVORE ATTACKS AND HAVE MECHANISMS TO RESIST OR TOLERATE HERBIVORY, ESPECIALLY IN THEIR LEAF TRAITS. SPECIFICALLY, THESE TRAITS CAN BE MODIFIED ACCORDING TO ENVIRONMENTAL VARIATIONS, SUCH AS FORESTS IN DIFFERENT STAGES OF ECOLOGICAL SUCCESSION, GENERATING IMPLICATIONS FOR THE INCIDENCE AND ATTACK OF HERBIVORES, AND THE HERBI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "19FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ATRIBUTOS ANTI-HERBIVORIA DE DIFERENTES GRUPOS FUNCIONAIS EM FLORESTA TROPICAL SAZONAL SECA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/FERNANDO_HENRIQUE_DE_SENA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4015> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FLOWERING PLANTS WITH SIMILAR FLORAL ATTRIBUTES OFTEN ATTRACT THE SAME GROUPS OF POLLINATORS AND, IN SYNCHRONOPATRIC SPECIES, SHARING POLLINATORS CAN RESULT IN COMPETITION, FACILITATION, OR HAVE NEUTRAL EFFECTS. WE, THEREFORE, ANALYZED THE EFFECTS OF POLLINATOR SHARING BETWEEN TWO SPECIES OF EUPHORBIACEAE (CNIDOSCOLUS INFESTUS AND C. URENS) WITH POPULATIONS IN ISOLATION AND COOCCURRENCE IN SERRA DO JATOBÁ, A ROCKY OUTCROP IN THE CAATINGA LOCATED IN THE MUNICIPALITY OF SERRA BRANCA-PB. WE USED FL"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "25AUG2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "CONSEQUÊNCIAS DA PARTILHA DE POLINIZADORES USANDO DUAS ESPÉCIES CO-OCORRENTES DE CNIDOSCOLUS (EUPHORBIACEAE) COMO MODELO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/EDITO_ROMAO_DA_SILVA_NETO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4016> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE REGENERATION OF TROPICAL FORESTS IN THE CONTEXT OF SLASH-AND-BURN AGRICULTURE HAS RECEIVED MUCH ATTENTION CONSIDERING THAT THIS TYPE OF ACTIVITY, OR LAND USE, CAN REDUCE THE FOREST'S RESILIENCE; I.E. SPEED OF REGENERATION. IN SEASONALLY DRY TROPICAL FORESTS, THE AVAILABILITY OF NUTRIENTS AND THEIR ACCUMULATION IN BIOMASS CAN BE CRITICAL, LIMITING THE NATURAL REGENERATION PROCESS, IN ADDITION TO SEASONAL WATER LIMITATION. HOWEVER, THE RECOVERY / ACCUMULATION OF NUTRIENTS THROUGHOUT THE REGENE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "12JUN2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DINÂMICA DE NUTRIENTES DURANTE A REGENERAÇÃO DE UMA FLORESTA DE CAATINGA APÓS AGRICULTURA DE SUBSISTÊNCIA"@pt ;
