<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4020> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PASSIFLORA L. (PASSIFLORACEAE) HAS MORE THAN 575 SPECIES DISTRIBUTED ESPECIALLY IN THE NEOTROPICS. PASSIFLORAS, ALSO KNOWN AS PASSION FRUIT, ARE GROWN AS FRUIT PLANTS, ORNAMENTAL OR EXPLOITED FOR THEIR MEDICINAL PROPERTIES. A GREAT VARIATION IN THE GENOME SIZE AND CHROMOSOMES NUMBER IS OBSERVED IN THE GENUS, CONGRUENT WITH ITS MAIN SUBGENERA. HOWEVER, ITS BASIC CHROMOSOMES NUMBER (X) AND THE EVENTS RESPONSIBLE FOR THESE KARYOTYPE VARIATIONS REMAIN CONTROVERSIAL. THE AIM OF THIS WORK WAS TO UNDER"@pt ;
