<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4021> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "GENOME SIZE (GS) DISPLAYS A BROAD VARIATION ACROSS PLANTS INCREASING BY THREE ORDERS OF 3 MAGNITUDE ACROSS ANGIOSPERMS, SO THAT IT IS POSSIBLE TO FIND ORGANISMS WITH TINY GENOMES OF 4 1C = 0.07 PG LIKE GENLISEA TUBEROSA, TO ORGANISMS WITH GIANT GENOMES 2200 TIMES LARGER AS IN 5 PARIS JAPONICA. AMONG THE PROCESSES THAT GENERATE AN INCREASE IN DNA CONTENT, POLYPLOIDY IS 6 ONE OF THE MOST FREQUENT, FOLLOWED BY THE VARIATION OF REPETITIVE NON-CODING DNA, SUCH AS 7 TRANSPOSABLE ELEMENTS, SATELLITE DN"@pt ;
