    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUCIA_MARIN_PEREZ> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4030> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CONDITIONS OF AN ENVIRONMENT CAN BE CONSIDERED AS FILTERS, WHICH SELECT INDIVIDUALS WITH SPECIFIC RESPONSES ON REQUIRED KEY ATTRIBUTES TO SETTLE AND SURVIVE IN THE COMMUNITY. THE ABILITY OF PLANTS TO CHANGE PHENOTYPIC CHARACTERS AS A RESULT OF INTERACTION WITH THE ENVIRONMENT IS KNOWN AS PHENOTYPIC PLASTICITY, AND CAN CONTRIBUTE TO THEIR FUNCTIONAL STABILITY, MAKING THEM A VERY IMPORTANT TOOL FOR THEIR ADAPTATION. THESE ADJUSTMENTS MAY BE DUE TO CHANGES IN SOLAR IRRADIATION, IN THE AMOUNT OF"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PLASTICIDADE FENOTÍPICA E DIVERSIDADE FUNCIONAL DE PLANTAS ARBÓREAS EM UMA CRONOSEQUÊNCIA EM UMA FLORESTA TROPICAL SAZONAL SECA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/BRUNO_MELO_LUSTOSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4031> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FOREST CONVERSION IN URBANIZED REGIONS HAS OCCURRED RAPIDLY THROUGHOUT THE WORLD IN RECENT DECADES AND CONSEQUENTLY AFFECTS BIODIVERSITY THAT HAS BEEN WIDELY REPORTED. URBAN GREEN AREAS ARE IMPORTANT FOR PROMOTING HUMAN WELL-BEING BY MAINTAINING BIODIVERSITY AND ECOSYSTEMS SERVICES, SUCH AS POLLINATION. THIS STUDY AIMS TO UNDERSTAND HOW URBAN GREEN SPACES CONTRIBUTE TO THE MAINTENANCE OF REPRODUCTIVE STRATEGIES OF TREE PLANTS OCCURRING IN URBAN ECOSYSTEM BY ANALYZING DIFFERENT ASPECTS OS POLLINA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "17JAN2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "POLINIZAÇÃO EM ECOSSISTEMAS URBANOS: REVISÃO, CIENTOMETRIA, DIVERSIDADE FUNCIONAL DE ATRIBUTOS REPRODUTIVOS E FENOLOGIA REPRODUTIVA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/MARCELA_TOMAZ_PONTES_DE_OLIVEIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4032> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE GENUS SIDA SHOWS TO BE A PROMISING GENUS IN THE DISCOVERY OF NEW SUBSTANCES THAT CAN COMBAT MICROBIAL AND PARASITIC RESISTANCE, COUNTING ON SEVERAL SPECIES IN WHICH THIS POTENTIAL HAS BEEN ELUCIDATED. THE GENERAL HYPOTHESIS OF THE WORK IS THAT SIDA GALHEIRENSIS ULBR., AN ENDEMIC SPECIES IN NORTHEASTERN BRAZIL, HAS BIOACTIVE POTENTIAL DUE TO THE CHEMOTAXONOMY OF THE GENUS. THE FIRST CHAPTER PROVIDES AN UPDATE ON THE BIOLOGICAL, PHARMACOLOGICAL, ETHNOMEDICINAL AND PHYTOCHEMICAL ACTIVITIES OF T"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "19FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PROSPECÇÃO FITOQUÍMICA E BIOATIVIDADE DE SIDA GALHEIRENSIS ULBR. (MALVACEAE)"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/FELICIDADE_CAROLINE_RODRIGUES> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4033> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MOST OF THE WORLD'S REMAINING NATURAL ECOSYSTEMS ARE SUBJECTED TO HIGH LEVELS OF CHRONIC AND ACUTE ANTHROPOGENIC DISTURBANCES, POSING A MAJOR THREAT TO NATURAL ECOSYSTEMS. ESPECIALLY IN DRY SEASONAL TROPICAL FORESTS (FTSS), A HIGH RISK BIOME, THERE IS AN INCREASING INTEREST IN UNDERSTANDING HOW THE IMPACTS OF THESE DISTURBANCE REGIMES MIGHT INTERACT WITH CLIMATE CHANGE SINCE THESE TWO FACTORS CAN CAUSE THE DEGRADATION OF LARGE AREAS OF FOREST, DECREASE THEIR PRODUCTIVITY AND MAKE REGENERATION DI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "18FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "RELAÇÃO PLANTA-FUNGOS MICORRÍZICOS EM ÁREAS DE CAATINGA: RESPOSTAS À DISPONIBILIDADE HÍDRICA E PERTURBAÇÕES ANTRÓPICAS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/SILVIA_CAROLINE_FARIAS_PEREIRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4034> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THE CAATINGA THERE IS A CLEAR DISTINCTION BETWEEN SEASONS, CAUSING NOTABLE CHANGES IN THE COLOR OF THE LANDSCAPE. AS POLLINATORS' PERCEPTION OF FLOWER COLORS IS PARTLY MODULATED BY THE BACKGROUND, THESE VARIATIONS COULD INFLUENCE HOW FLOWERS ARE PERCEIVED BY THESE ANIMALS. THAT IS, THE BACKGROUND OF THE FLOWERS CAN MAKE THEM MORE OR LESS CONSPICUOUS DEPENDING ON THE CONTRAST. IN THIS CONTEXT, WE POINT TO THE CASE OF JATROPHA MUTABILIS L. (EUPOHORBIACEAE), A GENERALIST SPECIES VISITED BY DIFFE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "18FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "SAZONALIDADE DE CORES E CONTRASTES DE FLORES NA CAATINGA: UM ESTUDO DE CASO COM JATROPHA MUTABILIS (POHL) (EUPHORBIACEAE)"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/SOFIA_LUCAS_CHALEGRE> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4035> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AS IN MANY TROPICAL ECOSYSTEMS, DUE TO ANTHROPOGENIC DISTURBANCES, AREAS OF CAATINGA WERE REPLACED BY ANOTHER KIND OF LAND USE AND THEN ABANDONED, CURRENTLY IN THE PROCESS OF SECONDARY SUCCESSION. HOWEVER, LITTLE IS KNOWN ABOUT THE SUCCESSION OF CAATINGA VEGETATION. IN ADDITION, IT ALSO DOES NOT KNOW WHETHER ECOSYSTEM SERVICES LOST DUE TO ANTHROPOGENIC DISTURBANCES ARE RECOVERED DURING A SUCCESSION, NOT EVEN IN RAINFORESTS WHERE SUCCESSION STUDIES ARE COMMON. THUS, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK IS "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "17FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "SERVIÇOS DE PROTEÇÃO ANTI-HERBIVORIA PRESTADOS POR FORMIGAS EM UM GRADIENTE DE SUCESSÃO SECUNDÁRIA EM ÁREAS DE CAATINGA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JONATAS_LEVI_GOMES_DA_SILVA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/BIOLOGIA_VEGETAL> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4036> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE FAMILY ERIOCAULACEAE BELONGS TO THE ORDER POALES EXHIBITS TRAITS ASSOCIATED WITH BOTH INSECT POLLINATION, SUCH AS PRESENCE OF NECTAR AND WIND POLLINATION, SUCH AS SMALL FLOWERS, EXPOSED SEXUAL ORGANS AND SMALL POLLEN GRAINS. THIS STUDY AIMED TO ELUCIDATE ISSUES RELATED TO FLORAL SIGNALING, OBSERVATIONS OF INSECT VISITS AND POLLINATION BEHAVIOR, FLORAL VOLATILES, AND THE CONTRIBUTION OF THE INSECTS, WIND AND SELF-POLLINATION TO FRUIT SET IN THREE SPECIES OF PAEPALANTHUS (P. BIFIDUS, P. SUBTIL"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "19FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "SINALIZAÇÃO FLORAL, POLINIZAÇÃO POR FORMIGAS E GEITONOGAMIA EM PAEPALANTHUS (ERIOCAULACEAE - POALES)"@pt ;
