<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4143> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THE NEW WORLD, LEISHMANIA INFANTUM IS THE AGENT OF VISCERAL LEISHMANIASIS AND CANL, WHICH ARE SPREAD BY THE BITE OF INFECTED SAND FLIES. THE DOG IS CONSIDERED THE MAIN RESERVOIR IN URBAN AREAS OF BRAZIL AND THE TREATMENT OF CANL STILL REPRESENTS A CHALLENGE. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO EVALUATE THE CLINICAL AND LABORATORY ASPECTS OF DOGS NATURALLY INFECTED WITH L. INFANTUM SUBMITTED TO THERAPY WITH MARBOFLOXACIN ASSOCIATED WITH ALLOPURINOL. TO EVALUATE THE EFFICACY OF MARBOFLOXACIN 12 "@pt ;
