<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4147> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BREAST NEOPLASMS ARE PROLIFERATIVE CHANGES THAT AFFECT WOMEN, BITCHES AND CATS THE MOST, AND ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE DEATHS OF HUNDREDS OF INDIVIDUALS AROUND THE WORLD. AMONG THE FORMS OF DIAGNOSIS, THE HISTOPATHOLOGICAL EXAMINATION IS CONSIDERED THE GOLD STANDARD, AND IT IS POSSIBLE TO APPRECIATE BESIDES THE HISTOLOGICAL ARCHITECTURE, THE DEGREE OF INVASIVENESS OF THE NEOPLASIA, THE MITOTIC INDEX AND OTHER FACTORS SUCH AS THE PRESENCE OF NECROSIS. BIOLOGICAL MARKERS IN THE NEOPLASTIC TISSUE AND"@pt ;
