    capes:hasAbstract "THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO DETECT MOLECULARLY THE PRESENCE OF LEISHMANIA SPP. IN THE BLOOD OF COMMERCIAL LAYING HENS AND TO DIAGNOSE AND EPIDEMIOLOGICALLY EVALUATE MYCOPLASMA SPP. IN COMMERCIAL LAYING HENS AND BROILER CHICKENS FROM POULTRY FARMS IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO. SAMPLES WERE OBTAINED FROM 22 LOTS FROM NINE FARMS, THREE FROM BROILER CHICKENS AND SIX FROM COMMERCIAL LAYING HENS. FROM EACH FLOCK, BLOOD SAMPLES WERE OBTAINED FOR SEROLOGICAL TESTS (N = 344) SEROLOGICAL SUCH AS, RAPI"@pt ;
