    capes:hasAbstract "SPHAGNETICOLA TRILOBATA (L.) PRUSKI (VEDELIA) IS A PLANT WIDELY USED IN FOLK MEDICINE. IT IS AN HERBACEOUS BELONGING TO THE FAMILY OF THE ASTERACEAE WITH ANTIOXIDANT, ANTI-INFLAMMATORY, ANTIMICROBIAL AND CICATRIZANTE ACTION, CHARACTERISTICS THAT PROPELLED THE REALIZATION OF THIS RESEARCH. THIS STUDY AIMED TO TEST THE ANTIMICROBIAL AND CICATRIZANT ACTIVITY OF THE CRUDE HYDROALCOHOLIC EXTRACT OF THE LEAVES OF SPHAGNETICOLA TRILOBATA. FOR THE PRODUCTION OF THE CRUDE HYDROALCOHOLIC EXTRACT, THE PLAN"@pt ;
