<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4158> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DIABETES MELLITUS IS A HYPERGLYCAEMIC DISORDER CONSIDERED A PUBLIC HEALTH CASE. IT CAN AFFECT SEVERAL ORGANS INCLUDING THE MALE REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM SUCH AS THE TESTICLES, IN THIS ONE CAN CAUSE DIVERSE DISORDERS LIKE LOW HORMONAL PRODUCTION, SPERMATOZOA, WEIGHT LOSS AND TISSUE MORPHOMETRIC ABNORMALITIES. LEADING TO DAMAGE TO THE HEALTH OF MAN. THIS DISEASE IS ASSOCIATED IN ITS HISTOPATHOLOGY WITH THE INCREASE OF INFLAMMATION AND OXIDATIVE STRESS. NOWADAYS, THE USE OF ANTIOXIDANT AND ANTI-INFLAMMA"@pt ;
