<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4166> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "OVER THE DECADES, NEUROSCIENCE HAS SOUGHT TO CORRELATE NEURAL ACTIVITY WITH BEHAVIORAL STATES. WITH THE EVOLUTION OF THE METHODS OF RECORDING THE NEURAL ACTIVITY, IT BECAME MORE PRACTICAL TO PERFORM EXPERIMENTS THAT ALLOWED THE SIMULTANEOUS RECORDING OF MULTIPLE ELECTRODES IN DIFFERENT BRAIN REGIONS, AT THE SAME TIME THAT THE ANIMAL PERFORMS A BEHAVIORAL TASK. THROUGH THESE EXPERIMENTS, IT WAS POSSIBLE TO IDENTIFY THAT CORTICAL OSCILLATIONS HAS AN IMPORTANT ROLE IN COGNITION, ESPECIALLY THE OSCI"@pt ;
