    capes:hasAbstract "TOXOPLASMA GONDII IS AN OBLIGATE INTRACELLULAR PROTOZOAN PARASITE THAT PRESENTS A LYTIC CYCLE CONSISTED OF STAGES OF RECOGNITION, PENETRATION, MULTIPLICATION, AND CAN LEAVE THE HOST CELL OR EVADE THE IMMUNE RESPONSE FROM A MECHANISM OF ENCYSTATION, REMAINING IN THE INTRACELLULAR SPACE. THESE STAGES INFLUENCE THE INFECTION CAPACITY OF THE PARASITE, RELATING TO ITS INFECTIVITY AND, CONSEQUENTLY, ITS VIRULENCE. THIS WORK'S PURPOSE IS TO CHARACTERIZE PHENOTYPICALLY ISOLATED T. GONDII FROM TISSUES OF"@pt ;
