    capes:hasAbstract "CONTAMINATION OF AQUATIC ENVIRONMENTS IS BECOMING MORE FREQUENT AND THESE ECOSYSTEMS ARE THE MAIN DISPOSAL SITES FOR DIFFERENT TYPES OF WASTE PRODUCED BY MAN. AMONG THESE PROCESSES, THE TEXTILE SECTOR IS CONSIDERED ONE OF THE MOST POLLUTED INDUSTRIAL SEGMENTS OF SURFACE WATER. THE CITY OF TORITAMA HAS DEVELOPED ALONG THE BANKS OF THE CAPIBARIBE RIVER AND IS A MAJOR TEXTILE GARMENT CENTER IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK WAS TO ANALYZE THE WATER QUALITY OF THE CAPIBARIBE RIV"@pt ;
