    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/SAÚDE_HUMANA_E_MEIO_AMBIENTE> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/4611> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FILAMENTOUS FUNGI PRODUCE A WIDE DIVERSITY OF SECONDARY METABOLITES THAT HAVE SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON SOCIETY. SOME METABOLITES ARE EXPLOITED FOR THEIR ACTIVITY AS ANTIBIOTICS AND OTHERS ARE INVOLVED IN DISEASES, FUNGAL INTERACTION WITH A WIDE RANGE OF SUBSTRATES. IN THIS CONTEXT, THE AIM OF THIS STUDY WAS TO ISOLATE, IDENTIFY AND TEST FOR ANTIMICROBIAL ACTIVITY OF FILAMENTOUS FUNGI ASSOCIATED WITH CORALS. WERE COLLECTED FRAGMENTS OF SEVEN CORAL SPECIES: FAVIA GRAVIDA, PALYTHOA CARIBAEORUM, PROTOP"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "AVALIAÇÃO DA ATIVIDADE ANTIMICROBIANA DE EXTRATOS METABÓLICOS DE FUNGOS ISOLADOS DE CORAIS"@pt ;
