    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/SAÚDE_DA_CRIANÇA_E_DO_ADOLESCENTE> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5007> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "DEVELOPMENTAL MEASUREMENTS - ANTHROPOMETRY - ARE IMPORTANT TOOLS FOR ASSESSING MUSCLE DEVELOPMENT AND MONITORING OF MUSCLE-RELATED DISEASES. THE MULTIFIDUS ARE DEEP MUSCLES THAT ARE LOCATED IN THE POSTERIOR AND MEDIAL PART OF THE VERTEBRAL COLUMN, BETWEEN THE SPINAL AND TRANSVERSE PROCESSES OF THE VERTEBRAE. THROUGH THE CROSS-SECTIONAL AREA OF THE LUMBAR MULTIFIDUS MUSCLE, IT IS POSSIBLE TO EVALUATE IF THERE IS A FUNCTION OR DYSFUNCTION OF THE SPINE, SINCE THERE IS A RELATION BETWEEN THIS AREA A"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22JAN2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
