<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5008> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE OCCURRENCE OF INFANT REGURGITATION (IR) CAN BE EXPLAINED BY BIOLOGICAL FACTORS RELATED TO THE INFANT, SUCH AS DYSREGULATION OF THE DIGESTIVE SYSTEM; AND BIOPSYCHOSOCIAL FACTORS ASSOCIATED WITH THE FAMILY-BABY RELATIONSHIP. THE BIOMEDICAL MODEL OF IR TREATMENT DOES NOT BRING THE EXPECTED RESOLUTION TO INFANTS AND FAMILIES. THE NON-MEDICATED APPROACH BY MANUAL THERAPY (TM) AND ITS POSSIBLE EFFECT ON THE AUTONOMIC NERVOUS SYSTEM (ANS), AS WELL AS STRATEGIES TO STRENGTHEN THE MOTHER-BABY RELATIO"@pt ;
