<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5009> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CARDIAC CATHETERIZATION IS A VALUABLE METHOD FOR TREATMENT AND DIAGNOSIS OF CONGENITAL HEART DISEASE. THIS PROCEDURE CAN BE A VERY STRESSFUL SITUATION FOR CHILDREN AND MAY HAVE EFFECTS ON THEM AND THEIR PARENTS SUCH AS, FOR EXAMPLE, ANXIETY. CHILDREN THAT ARE MORE ANXIOUS IN THE PREOPERATIVE PERIOD ARE LESS COOPERATIVE. THERAPEUTIC PLAY (TP) IS AN IMPORTANT TECHNIQUE TO PREPARE CHILDREN THAT WILL BE SUBMITTED TO CARDIAC CATHETERIZATION BECAUSE IT IS BASED IN ITS POTENTIAL TO EXPOSE A PROBLEM TO "@pt ;
