<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5012> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ASTHMA IS A DISEASE THAT CAN BE DESCRIBED AS CHRONIC INFLAMMATION OF THE LOWER AIRWAYS, LEADING TO REDUCED BRONCHIAL CALIBER AND AIRFLOW LIMITATION, PRESENTING RESPIRATORY SYMPTOMS SUCH AS WHEEZING, DIFFICULTY BREATHING AND COUGHING, VARYING IN FREQUENCY AND INTENSITY OVER TIME. OF TIME, SUBDIVIDED INTO SEVERAL PHENOTYPES AND ENDOTYPES. AMONG THE CHARACTERISTICS OF THESE PHENOTYPES AND ENDOTYPES ARE ASTHMATICS THAT ARE AFFECTED BY EXERCISE-INDUCED BRONCHOSPASM (EIB), DESCRIBED IN THE LITERATURE "@pt ;
