<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5019> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "FOOD INTOLERANCE (FI) INTERFERES WITH THE ADEQUATE NUTRIENT INTAKE AND IT IS FREQUENT IN CHILDREN WITH NEUROLOGIC DAMAGE. THE CONGENITAL ZIKA SYNDROME (CZS) IS AN EXAMPLE OF AN EARLY AND EXTREME BRAIN INJURY. IN THE HEALTH CARE OF CHILDREN WITH THIS SYNDROME, IT IS OBSERVED THAT FI ESPECIALLY PRESENTS AS VOMITING AND REGURGITATION, EVEN IN THOSE WITH TUBE FEEDING, WHICH COULD IMPLY THE GASTRIC MOTILITY IN THIS PHENOMENON. AS A SYNDROME OF RECENT DESCRIPTION, STUDIES RELATED TO THESE CHILDREN´S F"@pt ;
