    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/SAÚDE_DA_CRIANÇA_E_DO_ADOLESCENTE> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5025> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CHILD SOCIAL-EMOTIONAL DEVELOPMENT CAN BE UNDERSTOOD AS A PROCESS OF INTERDEPENDENCE BETWEEN SOCIAL SKILLS AND EMOTIONAL COMPETENCIES. IN THE EMOTIONAL REALM, SELF-REGULATION IS PARAMOUNT IN THIS DEVELOPMENT, AND IS DEFINED AS THE ABILITY TO MODIFY BEHAVIOR ACCORDING TO NEED OR IN PARTICULAR SITUATIONS. SOCIAL COMPETENCE IS CONCEPTUALIZED AS THE ABILITY TO ARTICULATE FEELINGS, ACTIONS AND THOUGHTS IN THE RELATIONSHIP WITH ADULTS AND OTHER CHILDREN. FAMILIES LIVING IN SITUATIONS OF VULNERABILITY "@pt ;
