<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5047> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE EPIDEMIOLOGICAL SURVEILLANCE (ES) CONTRIBUTES TO THE PREVENTION AND CONTROL OF DISEASES AND HEALTH PUBLIC PROBLEMS. THE TESTING AND COUNSELING CENTERS (TCC) ARE HEALTH SERVICES THAT PERFORM DIAGNOSTIC TESTS FREE OF CHARGE FOR SEXUALLY TRANSMITTED INFECTIONS (STI), ESPECIALLY FOR HIV, SYPHILIS AND VIRAL HEPATITIS (HV) B AND C, COLLABORATING AS DATA SOURCE, RESEARCH AND DESCRIPTION OF THE EPIDEMIOLOGICAL PROFILE OF THESE STI. OF THE TOTAL HIV RAPID TESTS (RT) ACCOMPLISHED IN PERNAMBUCO IN 2015"@pt ;
