<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5053> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TO THE MAGISTRATE, EVERYTHING? THIS THESIS EXAMINES THE CNJ'S DECISION-MAKING PROCESS BETWEEN 2005 AND 2015, SEEKING TO ASCERTAIN WHETHER THE AGENCY HAS BEEN CAPTURED BY THE JUDICIARY. IN PARTICULAR, THE GENERAL HYPOTHESIS WAS TESTED THAT THE PROCESS REPORTED BY A RAPPORTEUR AT THE TOP OF THE JUDICIARY SUFFERS LESS CHALLENGE / LESS DIVERGENCE THAN ONE REPORTED BY A MEMBER OF THE BODY ESSENTIAL TO JUSTICE. IN ADDITION, THE FOLLOWING SPECIFIC ASSUMPTIONS ARE EXAMINED REGARDING THE CASES REPORTED B"@pt ;
