<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5054> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "MUCH HAS BEEN WRITTEN ABOUT CHINESE ENGAGEMENT ON THE AFRICAN CONTINENT IN AN ATTEMPT TO DEEPEN KNOWLEDGE ABOUT ISSUES RELATED TO TRADE, INVESTMENT, SECURITY, COOPERATION, AMONG OTHERS. MOST EMPIRICAL RESEARCH FOCUSES ON THE DETERMINANTS OF CHINESE INVESTMENT IN AFRICA WITHOUT MUCH DEEPENING OR MORE FOCUSED ON CHINESE TRADE WITH AFRICA THAN IN FACT ON INVESTMENT AND FINANCING MECHANISMS. FROM TWO VERY CHARACTERISTIC EXAMPLES OF CHINA'S OIL RELATIONS WITH THE AFRICAN NATIONS, ANGOLA AND NIGERIA, "@pt ;
