<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5058> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE THESIS IS PART OF THE RESEARCH FIELD OF BEHAVIOR OF JUDICIAL INSTITUTIONS AND SEEKS TO UNDERSTAND THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE FEDERAL SUPREME COURT AND PUBLIC OPINION. THE RESEARCH PROBLEM CONSISTS OF THE FOLLOWING QUESTION: IS THERE A RELATION BETWEEN SALIENCE IN THE PRESS ABOUT PENDING CASES AND THE COURT'S LIKELIHOOD OF STRIKING DOWN PUBLIC POLICIES? IF THE BASELINE MODEL IS CORRECT, COURTS SHOULD BE MORE LIKELY TO STRIKE DOWN PUBLIC POLICIES WHEN THEY BELIEVE THAT THEIR DECISIONS WILL B"@pt ;
