<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5059> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE POLITICAL LITERATURE HAS HIGHLIGHTED RELEVANT ASPECTS REGARDING THE JUDICIALIZATION OF POLITICS IN THE BRAZILIAN SCENARIO. THE PRESENT THESIS FOCUSES ON ONE OF ITS NUANCES, WHEN DEALING WITH THE INTERFERENCE OF THE JUDICIARY IN THE FORMATION AND EXECUTION OF THE PARLIAMENTARY AGENDA OF THE FEDERAL LEGISLATURE. ARTICLE 5, LXIX AND LXX OF THE FEDERAL CONSTITUTION OF 1988 PROVIDE FOR THE CONTOURS OF THE WRIT OF MANDAMUS AND ITS ARTICLE 105, LXX, CONFERS ON THE POLITICAL PARTIES, WITH REPRESENTA"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "15MAR2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DECIDINDO SOBRE DECISÕES: O SUPREMO TRIBUNAL FEDERAL E A JUDICIALIZAÇÃO DA AGENDA PARLAMENTAR DO CONGRESSO NACIONAL."@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUIS_FELIPE_ANDRADE_BARBOSA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIA_POLÍTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5060> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH TESTS THREE COMPLEMENTARY HYPOTHESES. THE FIRST ARGUES THAT POLITICAL PARTY ALIGNMENT EXPLAINS THE VOLUME OF RESOURCES MADE AVAILABLE VIA FEDERAL VOLUNTARY TRANSFERS (TVF). IN PARTICULAR, MAYORS IDEOLOGICALLY CLOSEST TO THE PRESIDENT'S PARTY SHOULD RECEIVE MORE RESOURCES. THE SECOND HYPOTHESIS HOLDS THAT THE AMOUNT OF FUNDS TRANSFERRED AFFECTS THE PROBABILITY OF RE-ELECTION OF THE MAYOR. FINALLY, WE BELIEVE THAT THE EFFECT OF FVT ON THE ELECTORAL PERFORMANCE IS HIGHER IN SMALL MUNI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DETERMINANTES POLÍTICOS DAS TRANSFERÊNCIAS VOLUNTÁRIAS FEDERAIS AOS MUNICÍPIOS DO BRASIL (2009-2017)"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/ANDRE_VALENTE_DO_COUTO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIA_POLÍTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5061> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WHICH FACTORS DETERMINE THE SPREAD OF PUBLIC POLICIES THROUGHOUT THE BRAZILIAN TERRITORY? TO ADVANCE THE ANSWER TO THIS QUESTION, WE UNDERTOOK THE PRESENT INVESTIGATION BASED ON TWO BRANCHES OF POLITICAL SCIENCE RESEARCH: THE DIFFUSION STUDIES AND THE DECENTRALIZATION OF PUBLIC POLICIES IN BRAZILIAN FEDERALISM. IN FIRST PLACE WE ASK ABOUT THE LIMITS OF THE CONCEPTS CONSIDERED AND ABOUT THE STATE OF THE BRAZILIAN ACADEMIC RESEARCH IN THESE FIELDS. AIMING AT ANSWERING THOSE, IN CHAPTER TWO WE UNDE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "28AUG2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DIFUSÃO DO PROGRAMA DE AQUISIÇÃO DE ALIMENTOS DA AGRICULTURA FAMILIAR ENTRE OS MUNICÍPIOS BRASILEIROS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/FIDEL_PARENTE_DE_ALENCAR_PIMENTEL> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIA_POLÍTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5062> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "WHAT ARE THE DETERMINANTS OF POLITICAL CORRUPTION? IN THIS DISSERTATION, I BUILD ON (1) A DEFINITION OF CORRUPTION AS THE OPPOSITE OF IMPARTIALITY, (2) AN OPERATIONALIZATION OF THE CONCEPT THAT ATTEMPTS TO MEASURE THE COMMON DIMENSION AMONG CORRUPT PRACTICES, (3) A THEORETICAL BASIS CENTERED ON THE IDEA OF SOCIAL TRAPS, AND (4) A NOVEL (FOR CORRUPTION STUDIES) STRATEGY OF IDENTIFICATION TO TEST THE EFFECTS OF EDUCATIONAL LEVELS ON POLITICAL CORRUPTION. EDUCATIONAL IMPROVEMENTS ENHANCE VARIABLES "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "E A EDUCAÇÃO VOS LIBERTARÁ: OS EFEITOS DE MISSÕES PROTESTANTES SOBRE NÍVEIS DE CORRUPÇÃO NO MUNDO"@pt ;
