<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5244> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PERITROPHIC MEMBRANE (PM) IS A CHITIN STRUCTURE PRESENT IN THE MIDGUT OF MOST INSECTS. THE PM HAS THE FUNCTION OF PROTECTING THE INTESTINAL EPITHELIUM AND DIGESTION COMPARTMENTALIZATION. MP IS MAINLY COMPOSED OF CHITIN AND ASSOCIATED PROTEINS, AND THIS MAKES THE ENZYMES INVOLVED IN THE METABOLISM OF CHITIN IN THE MIDGUT PIVOTAL FOR THE PHYSIOLOGY AND PROTECTION OF INSECTS. IN THIS STUDY, WE IDENTIFIED AND CHARACTERIZED THE MAIN ENZYMES INVOLVED IN CHITIN METABOLISM, SUCH AS CHITIN SYNTHASE ("@pt ;
