<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5245> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE LADY BEETLE, ERIOPIS CONNEXA (GERMAR) (COLEOPTERA: COCCINELLIDAE), IS A NATURAL ENEMY FOUND IN SEVERAL CROP ECOSYSTEMS, ASSOCIATED MAINLY WITH APHIDS INFESTATION. IT HAS PROBABLY BEEN UNDER SELECTION PRESSURE OF PYRETHROID APPLICATIONS, AGAINST DEFOLIATOR PEST SPECIES, RESULTING IN SELECTION FOR RESISTANCE (R). THE RESISTANCE TRAIT CONFERS THE LADY BEETLE ABILITY TO SURVIVAL PYRETHROIDS APPLICATION; THEREBY SURVIVING BEETLES WILL PROVIDE APHID CONTROL PRECLUDING THE RECURRENT APHID OUTBREAK"@pt ;
