    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENT RESEARCH WAS BASED ON THE UPPER ECHELONS THEORY PROPOSED BY HAMBRICK AND MASON (1984) AND AIMED TO INVESTIGATE HOW SOME CHARACTERISTICS OF THE CEO IMPACT ON THE ADOPTION AND THE USE OF THE MANAGEMENT CONTROL SYSTEMS IN STARTUPS COMPANIES FOUNDED IN BRAZIL. FROM THIS PREMISE, THE STUDY SOUGHT TO OBSERVE HOW THE CEO'S TIME OF EXPERIENCE, WHETHER OR NOT HE IS A FOUNDER, AND HIS BACKGROUND INFLUENCE THE INTENSITY OF USE AND THE STYLE OF USE OF MIS. THE METHODOLOGY FOR DATA COLLECTION CON"@pt ;
