<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5293> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH AIMED TO ANALYZE THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN BRAZILIAN COMPANIES CARBON PERFORMANCE AND MONETARY INCENTIVES GRANTED TO EXECUTIVES IN ORDER TO REACH ENVIRONMENTAL GOALS. THE PRESENT RESEARCH CONSISTS IN TWO STAGES DEVELOPED IN TWO ARTICLES DELINEATED FOR A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF THE MATTER. THE FIRST ARTICLE FOCUSES ON THE RELATIONSHIP TIMING BETWEEN EXECUTIVE COMPENSATIONS AND CARBON PERFORMANCE, WHERE THE DEPENDENT VARIABLE IS REMUNERATION. RESULTS SHOW THAT CARBON PERFORMANCE IS NO"@pt ;
