<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5685> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INVASIVE SPECIES ARE ONE OF THE WORLD'S MAJOR THREATS TO BIODIVERSITY AND IT HAS BEEN WIDELY STUDIED RESULTING IN TRADITIONAL LITERATURE FOCUSED MAINLY ON NEGATIVE RELATIONSHIPS. HOWEVER, AN INCREASING NUMBER OF STUDIES ON INVASIVE ALIEN PLANTS PROVIDE EVIDENCE THAT IT MAY ALSO HAVE POSITIVE IMPACTS ON ECOSYSTEMS, CONTRIBUTING TO THE RESTORATION OF ECOSYSTEM FUNCTIONS AND THE INCREASE OF BIODIVERSITY, WITH PARADOXICAL EFFECTS BEING REPORTED BY STUDIES CONDUCTED ON DIFFERENT GEOGRAPHIC SCALES. UN"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "21FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "EFEITOS POSITIVOS DE UMA PLANTA INVASORA: EVIDÊNCIAS DO AUMENTO NA SOBREVIVÊNCIA E DIMINUIÇÃO DA HERBIVORIA DE PLANTAS NATIVAS"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/THEO_BRANCO_DE_OLIVEIRA_WANDERLEY> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ETNOBIOLOGIA_E_CONSERVAÇÃO_DA_NATUREZA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5686> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CONSIDERING THE TRADITIONAL QUILOMBOLA COMMUNITIES, IN AN ANALYSIS OF THE SCIENTIFIC LITERATURE FOCUSED ON THE ETHNOBOTANY AND ETHNOPHARMACOLOGICAL APPROACH OF THESE SITES, IT WAS NOTICED THAT THERE IS STILL A SMALL NUMBER OF STUDIES, MAINLY IN THE NORTHEAST OF BRAZIL. IN THIS SENSE, THIS DISSERTATION, IN GENERAL, HAD THE PURPOSE OF: TO IDENTIFY WHICH SPECIES OF THE GENUS PLECTRANTHUS HAVE ALREADY BEEN REPORTED FOR ANTI-INFLAMMATORY AND/OR ANALGESIC TREATMENT, BOTH FROM THE POINT OF VIEW OF TRAD"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "18FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ESTUDO SOBRE A VALIDAÇÃO ETNOFARMACOLÓGICA DA ATIVIDADE ANTIEDEMATOGÊNICA DO USO DO DECOCTO DAS FOLHAS DE PLECTRANTHUS ORNATUS CODD POR COMUNIDADE QUILOMBOLA DO CARIRI CEARENSE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2020"^^xsd:gYear ;
