<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5692> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SEVERAL FACTORS CAN INFLUENCE THE ATTITUDES OF HUMANS TOWARDS ANIMALS, SUCH AS BELIEFS, FEELINGS, CULTURE AND KNOWLEDGE. THE GROWING PROCESS OF URBANIZATION HAS FAVORED THE DISTANCE BETWEEN HUMANS AND NATURE, WHICH MAY INCREASE APATHY, AVERSION AND IGNORANCE ABOUT WILDLIFE. IN THIS SENSE, THE PRESENT STUDY AIMED TO INVESTIGATE THE AVERSION AND NON-CONSERVATIONIST ATTITUDES TOWARDS REPTILES, AS WELL AS TO EXPERIMENTALLY EVALUATE THE EFFECT OF PRACTICAL EXPOSURES AS A STRATEGY TO MITIGATE ATTITUDE"@pt ;
