<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5748> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS WORK AIMS AT COVERING THE CURRENT GAPS IN THE ACADEMIC BIBLIOGRAPHY THROUGH THE EVALUATION OF THE CLASS SIZE IMPACT ON STUDENTS' PERCEPTIONS ABOUT EDUCATIONAL SERVICE QUALITY FROM THREE BRAZILIAN PRIVATE HEI AS WELL AS ON ITS EVENTUAL MODERATION ON THE CORRELATION BETWEEN PERCEIVED QUALITY AND SATISFACTION, REPURCHASE AND RECOMMENDATION INTENTIONS. IT WAS ASSUMED THAT BIGGER CLASSES INFLUENCE NEGATIVELY STUDENTS' JUDGMENTS ABOUT SERVICE QUALITY AND ITS CORRELATION WITH ALL OTHER CONSTRUCTS."@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "14DEC2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "O PAPEL DO TAMANHO DA TURMA NA QUALIDADE PERCEBIDA DO ENSINO E SUA RELAÇÃO COM AS ATITUDES DOS ALUNOS PARA COM A IES"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/MARCUS_FABIO_RODRIGUES_PEIXOTO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/INOVAÇÃO_E_DESENVOLVIMENTO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5749> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "UBER, THE LARGEST TAXI COMPANY IN THE WESTERN WORLD, HAS NO ASSETS, IE: IT DOES NOT OWN ANY TAXI. THIS IS AN APPLICATION INSTALLED ON PEOPLE'S HANDSETS OR SMARTPHONES, USED TO CONNECT POTENTIAL PASSENGERS AND DRIVERS, ALL MANAGED BY A DIGITAL PLATFORM. THIS STUDY AIMED TO ANALYZE THE ASPECTS AND IMPACTS OF THE SHARING ECONOMY AND ITS DISRUPTIVE EFFECTS PRODUCED BY THE INTRODUCTION OF ITS LARGEST REPRESENTATIVE, THE UBER APPLICATION AS A COMPETITOR OF THE TAXI MARKET. THE CITY OF RECIFE WAS CHOSE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "14DEC2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "PERCEPÇÕES SOBRE A ECONOMIA DO COMPARTILHAMENTO: AVALIAÇÕES DOS USUÁRIOS DO SERVIÇO UBER NO RECIFE"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/JOSE_FELIX_BEZERRA> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/INOVAÇÃO_E_DESENVOLVIMENTO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/5806> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE NATIONAL HUMANIZATION POLICY PRESENTS ACCEPTION AS AN IMPORTANT GUIDELINE AND OPERATIVE DEVICE FOR A MORE HUMANIZED HEALTH CARE, SINCE IT ALLOWS A GREATER REFLECTION OF THE ATTENTION AND MANAGEMENT MODELS AND THE ACCESS RELATIONS TO THE SERVICE, RAISING THE RESPONSIBILITY AND COMMITMENT OF THE PROFESSIONAL OR TEAM OF HEALTH BY A QUALIFIED LISTENER.THIS RESEARCH HAD AS OBJECTIVE TO ANALYZE THE PRACTICE OF THE HOST IN THE FAMILY HEALTH STRATEGIES. A DESCRIPTIVE STUDY WAS CARRIED OUT WITH A QUA"@pt ;
