<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6279> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CHILDHOOD OVERWEIGHT/OBESITY HAS BECOME INCREASINGLY HIGHER IN THE PAST YEARS AND HENCE SEVERAL METABOLIC DYSFUNCTIONS ARE ASSOCIATED WITH SUCH CONDITION. SEROTONIN PLAYS A DYNAMIC ROLE IN THE ORGANISM AND IN THE CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM COORDINATES THE ENERGY BALANCE REGULATION INDUCING HUNGER OR SATIETY MECHANISMS. MITOCHONDRIAL FUNCTION RELATED TO ENERGY PRODUCTION REMAINS A KEY FACTOR IN ENERGY BALANCE REGULATION MAINLY IN CONDITIONS OF METABOLIC IMPAIRMENTS SUCH AS OVERWEIGHT/OBESITY. HOW"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "13FEB2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
