    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/NEUROPSIQUIATRIA_E_CIÊNCIAS_DO_COMPORTAMENTO> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6280> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SEPSIS IS DEFINED AS AN ORGANIC DYSFUNCTION CAUSED BY AN UNREGULATED HOST RESPONSE TO INFECTION THAT REMAINS ONE OF THE MAIN CAUSES OF MORBIDITY AND MORTALITY WORLDWIDE. STUDIES POINT TO A CLOSE CORRELATION BETWEEN THE CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM, THE IMMUNE SYSTEM AND THE HOST'S RESPONSE TO SEPSIS. A PROOF OF THIS RELATIONSHIP IS A NEUROHYPOPHYSEAL DYSFUNCTION THAT OCCURS IN SEPSIS, WITH EMPHASIS ON CHANGES IN THE SYNTHESIS AND SECRETION OF VASOPRESSIN (AVP), WHICH EXHIBITS A BIPHASIC PATTERN, CONTR"@pt ;
