    capes:hasAbstract "THE RESEARCH ABOUT THE INSTITUTIONAL FRAMEWORK OF THE ACCESS TO INFORMATION IS ESSENTIAL TO COMPREHEND THE APPLICATION OF THE PRINCIPLES OF DEMOCRACY AND HUMAN RIGHTS. THIS PAPER FOCUSES ON THE INSTITUTIONALIZATION OF THE ACCESS TO PUBLIC INFORMATION IN THE MEMBER STATES OF THE COMMUNITY OF PORTUGUESE SPEAKING COUNTRIES (CPLP). THIS STUDY IS BASED ON LITERATURE REVIEW AND DOCUMENTARY RESEARCH, PROCEDURE THROUGH WHICH THE AUTHOR ANALYSES CONSTITUTIONS AND FREEDOM OF INFORMATION LAWS. IT PRESENTS "@pt ;
