<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6309> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CORRUPTION IS NOT SOMETHING DIFFICULT TO NOTICE WHEN IT IS PRESENT IN THE POLITICAL STRUCTURE OF A COUNTRY. IT COMES AMID BREACHES OF LAWS AND RULES, CORRUPTING THE INTERESTS OF THE STATE AND FAVORING PRIVATE GAINS. THUS, CORRUPTION ULTIMATELY WEAKENS THE INSTITUTIONS AND VALUES OF DEMOCRACY, COMPROMISING THE CREDIBILITY OF THE STATE AND THEREBY THREATENING THE STABILITY AND SECURITY OF SOCIETIES. IN THIS SENSE, THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH IS TO UNDERSTAND, THROUGH THE LITERATURE, THE IMPACT "@pt ;
