<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6459> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TEMPOROMANDIBULAR DISORDER (TMD) IS DEFINED AS A SET OF CHANGES THAT COMPROMISE THE TEMPOROMANDIBULAR JOINT, CHEWING MUSCLES AND ASSOCIATED STRUCTURES. THIS IS THE MOST COMMON FORM OF CHRONIC OROFACIAL PAIN. THIS DISORDER HAS A GENETIC PREDISPOSITION. THUS, IT IS IMPORTANT TO IDENTIFY THE POSSIBILITY OF GENETIC POLYMORPHISMS BEING ASSOCIATED WITH THIS DISORDER IN ORDER TO DEVELOP MORE SPECIFIC TREATMENT. THUS, THE POLYMORPHISMS -308 A/G TNF-¿ AND -1082 A/G IL-10 WERE EVALUATED, THE ALLELIC AND G"@pt ;
