<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6483> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TRIPLARIS GARDNERIANA WEDD. (POLYGONACEAE) KNOWN AS PAJEÚ IS WIDELY USED IN TRADITIONAL MEDICINE, HIGHLIGHTING ITS USE TO TREAT PAIN AND INFLAMMATION, WHICH MAKES IT PROMISING IN THE DEVELOPMENT OF A NEW HERBAL MEDICINE. DUE TO THE LACK OF STUDIES THAT EVALUATE THE ANALGESIC ACTIVITY AND STANDARDIZATION OF THE LEAVES OF THE SPECIES, THE OBJECTIVE WAS TO DEVELOP A STANDARDIZED RAW MATERIAL WITH ANTINOCICEPTIVE ACTION USING THE LEAVES OF T. GARDNERIANA. TO THIS END, A REVIEW OF THE LITERATURE ON T"@pt ;
