<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6586> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "\"THIS PAPER EXPLORES SOME REFLECTIONS ABOUT THE USE OF INDIAN LITERATURE: AS A MEAN OF HUMAN RIGHTS ENFORCEMENT. THEREFORE, WE INTENDED TO USE LITERATURE AS A MEDIATOR IN THE TEACHING ACTIVITIES DEVELOPED BY THE TEACHER(S) AND STUDENT(S) WITH THE DIFFERENCE THAT THE INDIAN REPRESENTATION IS STILL PERCEIVED, AS A POLITICAL INSTANCE, IN RELATION TO THE CONTINUOUS TREATMENT GRANTED TO THE INDIAN CAUSE WITHIN OUR SCHOLLS. THE CONCERN THAT UNDERLIES THIS STUDY IS THE ENACTMENT OF LAW 11.645/08 THAT R"@pt ;
