<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6765> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "STRYPHNODENDRON ADSTRINGENS (MART.) COVILLE (FABACEAE), POPULARLY KNOWN AS \"BARBATIMÃO\" IS A TREE NATIVE TO BRAZIL AND TYPICAL OF THE CERRADO. IT IS USED IN THE TREATMENT OF VAGINAL INFLAMMATIONS AND INFECTIONS IN GENERAL. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO STANDARDIZE PLANT DRUG AND ACTIVE PHARMACEUTICAL INGREDIENT OF LEAVES OF S. ADSTRINGENS WITH ANTIMICROBIAL ACTION. IT WAS COLLECTED AT JACARAPÉ BEACH, JOÃO PESSOA (PB) AND THE DRY PLANT MATERIAL WAS SIEVED AT PARTICLE SIZES: 50-100 MESH (BF1)"@pt ;
