<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6803> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SUBSIDENCE PROCESSES ARE CHARACTERIZED BY THE MOVEMENT OF THE EARTH´S SURFACE, CAUSING A SUDDEN SINKING OR GRADUAL SETTLING OF THE TERRAIN. THE SEDIMENTARY DEPOSITIONAL ENVIRONMENTS, SUCH AS DELTA, ARE PRONE TO SUBSIDENCE DUE TO SEDIMENT COMPACTION. THE STUDY AREA IS SITUATED ON THE SERGIPE ALAGOAS BASIN AND IT CORRESPONDS TO SAO FRANCISCO DELTAIC PLAIN. THE NORTHERN PART OF THIS PLAIN IS COMPOSED BY CONSTANTLY FLOODED REGIONS AND PREVIOUS STUDIES INDICATED THE SUBSIDENCE EXISTENCE IN THIS REGIO"@pt ;
