    capes:hasAbstract "THE PALEONTOLOGY OF THE GRAMAME FORMATION, PARAÍBA BASIN, HAS BEEN STUDIED FOR MORE THAN A CENTURY. THERE ARE MANY WORKS WITH ITS MACROFOSSILS, BUT FEW WERE DONE WITH STRATIGRAPHIC CONTROL. THIS RESEARCH HAD THE OBJECTIVE OF PERFORMING A TAXONOMIC AND PALEOECOLOGICAL STUDY OF THE MACROFOSSILS AT THE ROGER QUARRY IN JOÃO PESSOA-PB, IN ORDER TO UNDERSTAND THE VARIATIONS OF THE FAUNAL ASSOCIATIONS AND THE PALEOPROFUNDITY, ALONG 30 METERS OF GRAMAME FORMATION. A BIBLIOGRAPHICAL SURVEY WAS CARRIED OU"@pt ;
