<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6840> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE JUDICIALIZATION OF ACCESS TO PRODUCTS AND SERVICES AND HEALTH IS A PHENOMENON THAT HAS PERMEATED BRAZILIAN COURTS SINCE THE EARLY 1990S. GIVEN THE MAGNITUDE ACHIEVED, THE EXECUTIVE AND JUDICIARY POWERS SEEK ALTERNATIVES TO MINIMIZE THE IMPACTS CAUSED BY JUDICIAL DEMANDS AND IN THIS CONTEXT NATJUS IS A FUNDAMENTAL STRATEGY FOR TECHNICAL DISCUSSION ABOUT THE CASES REFERRED TO THE JUDICIARY FOR ANALYSIS. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS WORK IS TO KNOW THE JUDICIALIZATION PROCESS IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUC"@pt ;
