    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/INOVAÇÃO_TERAPÊUTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/6841> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "AMERICAN CUTANEOUS LEISHMANIASIS (ATL) IS A NEGLECTED TROPICAL DISEASE THAT CAUSES LESIONS ON THE SKIN AND MUCOUS OF INFECTED INDIVIDUALS, AND CAN ALSO CAUSE DEFORMATIONS ON THE FACE. THIS DISEASE IS CAUSED BY PROTOZOA FROM THE SUBGENERA LEISHMANIA AND VIANNIA, AND IS TRANSMITTED BY FEMALE SANDFLIES. IN BRAZIL, 15 TO 20 THOUSAND CASES OF ATL ARE REGISTERED ANNUALLY AND, IN THE STATE OF PERNAMBUCO, 1,855 NEW CASES OF THIS DISEASE WERE REGISTERED IN THE PERIOD FROM 2013 TO 2018, THUS BEING CONSIDE"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "17JUL2020:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "OBTENÇÃO, CARACTERIZAÇÃO ESTRUTURAL, ATIVIDADE ANTIOXIDANTE E LEISHMANICIDA DE DERIVADOS HETEROCÍCLICOS PENTAGONAIS"@pt ;
