    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/GEOCIÊNCIAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/7147> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE BEBERIBE RIVER WATER HAS BEEN USED FOR PUBLIC SUPPLY OF THE RECIFE AND OLINDA MUNICIPALITIES SINCE THE XIX CENTURY. AFTER 1970, A CRESCENT NUMBER OF PRECARIOUS SETTLEMENTS WAS INSTALLED IN THE MIDDLE AND LOWER RIVER COURSES, CONTRIBUTING FOR THE INCREASING OF DOMESTIC RESIDUALS AND, CONSEQUENTLY, WATER CONTAMINATION. BESIDES, IN THE WATERSHED, THERE WERE TWO TANNERIES (POTENTIAL SOURCE OF CR), A TEXTILE INDUSTRY (PB) AND A BREWING INDUSTRY (POTENTIAL SOURCE OF CR AND CU) IN ITS EFFLUENTS. RE"@pt ;
