<http://example.com/capes#thesis/7148> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN LOW-PERMEABILITY CARBONATE RESERVOIRS, THE POROUS NETWORKS REPRESENTED BY FRACTURE SYSTEMS REPRESENT A CRITICAL ASPECT FOR UNDERSTANDING HYDRO-MECHANICAL PROCESSES. THE PRESENT STUDY TREATED THE INFLUENCE OF DEPOSITIONAL AND DIAGENETIC PROCESSES ON THE MECHANICAL STRATIGRAPHY AND DISTRIBUTION OF FRACTURES IN LAMINATED LIMESTONES OF C6 INTERVAL (APPROXIMATELY 15 M HEIGHT) OF CRATO FORMATION (APTIAN), ARARIPE BASIN. THE APPROACH INCLUDED THE FULL VISUAL SCAN OF OUTCROPS SURFACES THAT OCCUR IN Q"@pt ;
