<http://example.com/capes#thesis/7149> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE PERNAMBUCO BASIN COMPRISES ONE OF THE MOST MARGINAL SEDIMENTARY BASINS OF THE SOUTH ATLANTIC, FORMED DURING THE GONDWANA BREAKUP IN THE MESOZOIC ERA. THIS STUDY WAS DEVELOPED IN CARBONATE ENVIRONMENTS INTENSELY DOLOMITIZED OF THE ESTIVA FORMATION, DEPOSITED DURING THE DRIFT PHASE (LATE ALBIAN TO TURONIAN AGES). IT WAS DETERMINED THE PETROGRAPHIC FEATURES, SPECTRAL SIGNATURES, AND THE GEOCHEMICAL DATA OF TOTAL ORGANIC CARBON (TOC), TOTAL SULPHUR (TS), AND TOTAL NITROGEN (TN), AS WELL AS THE C"@pt ;
