    capes:hasAbstract "THE PRESENT DISSERTATION IS ABOUT THE CONSTRUCTION OF THE MEMORY OF THE CONFLICT THAT LASTED FOR MORE THAN FIFTY YEARS INVOLVING GUERRILLA MOVEMENTS, PARAMILITARY GROUPS AND THE PUBLIC FORCES IN COLOMBIA. THE STUDY INVESTIGATES INITIATIVES AIMED AT BUILDING THE MEMORY ADOPTED BY THE VARIOUS ACTORS INVOLVED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY IN THE CONFLICT AND SEEKS TO IDENTIFY HOW DIFFERENT VERSIONS OF HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS ARE COUNTERED BY THE ATTEMPTS OF EACH OF THESE ACTORS TO MAKE THEIR VISION OF CON"@pt ;
