<http://example.com/capes#thesis/7257> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BRAZIL HAS ADOPTED A PLURAL AND INCLUSIVE FAMILY SYSTEM SINCE THE ADVENT OF THE 1988 FEDERAL CONSTITUTION, WHICH HAS BROUGHT OTHER FAMILY TYPES BEYOND MARRIAGE. HISTORICALLY, THE BRAZILIAN POPULATION WAS FORMED FROM THE TOLERANCE OF THE CONCUBINE RELATIONSHIPS ESTABLISHED IN THE VIOLENT COLONIZATION PERIOD, EVEN THOUGH THE IMPORTED LEGISLATION AND ADAPTED TO THE COLONY, HAVE FOUGHT THESE FAMILY FORMATIONS, THROUGH THE IMPOSITION OF MONOGAMY. BRAZILIAN LEGISLATION AND CUSTOMS, THEREFORE, INCORPOR"@pt ;
