<http://example.com/capes#thesis/7281> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE CONVENTION ON THE RIGHTS OF PERSONS WITH DISABILITIES (CRPD) IS THE FIRST HUMAN RIGHTS TREATY OF THE TWENTY-FIRST CENTURY, OF WHICH BRAZIL IS A SIGNATORY SINCE 2006. IT WAS APPROVED BY LEGISLATIVE DECREE IN 2008 WITH THE QUALIFIED QUORUM PROVIDED FOR IN ART. 5, § 3, THE CRFB / 1988, GIVING IT STATUS OF CONSTITUTIONAL RULE AND HAD HIS INTERNALIZED TEXT IN 2009 BY PRESIDENTIAL DECREE. PRIORITIZING THE VALUES OF AUTONOMY, INCLUSION AND ACCESSIBILITY, CDPD INAUGURATED THE BRAZILIAN LEGAL SYSTEM "@pt ;
