<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8171> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "BETA REGRESSIONS ARE COMMONLY USED WITH RESPONSES THAT ASSUME VALUES IN THE STANDARD UNIT INTERVAL, SUCH AS RATES, PROPORTIONS AND CONCENTRATION INDICES. HYPOTHESIS TESTING INFERENCES ON THE MODEL PARAMETERS ARE TYPICALLY PERFORMED USING THE LIKELIHOOD RATIO TEST. IT DELIVERS ACCURATE INFERENCES WHEN THE SAMPLE SIZE IS LARGE, BUT CAN OTHERWISE LEAD TO UNRELIABLE CONCLUSIONS. IT IS THUS IMPORTANT TO DEVELOP ALTERNATIVE TESTS WITH SUPERIOR FINITE SAMPLE BEHAVIOR. WE DERIVE THE BARTLETT CORRECTION "@pt ;
