    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/ESTATÍSTICA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8173> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN STATISTICAL ANALYSIS, THE PRESENCE OF MISSING DATA IS COMMON IN MANY APPLICATIONS AND STUDIES IN NUMEROUS AREAS, WITH SPECIAL EMPHASIS ON HEALTH. STUDIES WERE DEVELOPED THROUGHOUT THE SECOND HALF OF THE XX CENTURY TO OVERCOME THE PROBLEM OF MISSING DATA, OF WHICH THE WORKS OF RUBIN (1988) AND SCHAFER (1997) FOR DATA IMPUTATION STAND OUT. IN ADDITION TO PROCESSING THE DATABASE AND FILLING IN THE DATA FOR THE USE OF STATISTICAL MODELING TECHNIQUES, WHICH ARE MOSTLY RESTRICTED TO COMPLETE DATA, "@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "22FEB2022:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
