<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8181> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SEDIMENT FLOWS ARE NATURAL PROCESSES THAT OCCUR IN WATER COURSES, CAUSED BY EROSIONS IN THE ENVIRONMENT. HOWEVER, ANTHROPOGENIC INTERVENTIONS CAN ACCELERATE OR INCREASE EROSIVE PROCESSES OR EVEN REDUCE SEDIMENT CONCENTRATIONS. THE DAMS INSTALLED ALONG THE SÃO FRANCISCO RIVER ALTERED THE NATURAL FLOW REGIME IN THE REGIONS DOWNSTREAM OF EACH DAM AND PRESENTED AS A MAIN CONSEQUENCE THE FLOW REGULATION AND THE DECREASE OF SEDIMENT CONCENTRATIONS. IN THIS CONTEXT, THE OBJECTIVE OF THE RESEARCH WAS TO"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "06FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
