    capes:hasAbstract "THIS RESEARCH DEMONSTRATES THE RISE OF A CHANGE IN THE CULTURE OF CONSUMPTION OF FOODS PRODUCED IN A TRADITIONAL WAY FOR THOSE WITHOUT THE USE OF PESTICIDES, DEMONSTRATING THIS EVOLUTION THROUGH AN ENVIRONMENTAL EDUCATION ACQUIRED FROM THE LEVEL OF INFORMATION AND SOCIAL INTEREST ABOUT THE BENEFITS OF ORGANIC FOODS IN DETRIMENT TO THE HARMS PRESENTED BY THOSE WHO USE PESTICIDES IN THEIR PRODUCTION. DISCOURSE ABOUT THE GROWTH OF THE ORGANIC FOOD MARKET AT THE NATIONAL LEVEL, IN CONTRAST TO A SCEN"@pt ;
