<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8550> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS THESIS IS DIVIDED INTO TWO CHAPTERS THAT ADDRESS THE THEME OF ECONOMIC UNCERTAINTY, THE HOUSING MARKET AND REAL ESTATE SECTOR IN THE UNITED STATES. THE FIRST USES A STOCHASTIC DYNAMIC GENERAL EQUILIBRIUM (DSGE) MODEL TO UNDERSTAND THE IMPACT OF UNCERTAINTY ARISING FROM THE HOUSING SECTOR AND AGGREGATE UNCERTAINTY IN THE PRODUCTIVE SECTOR ON THE REAL ACTIVITY OF THE US ECONOMY. THE MAIN RESULTS WERE: (I) UNDER A CONTEXT OF NOMINAL RIGIDITY AND BORROWING CONSTRAINT, UNCERTAINTY IN THE PRODUCT"@pt ;
