<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8555> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "TAXATION RULES AND ALLOCATION OF PUBLIC RESOURCES VARY A LOT AROUND THE WORLD, MAKING IT VERY IMPORTANT TO STUDY THE ADVANTAGES AND DRAWBACKS FOR THE POPULATION OF EACH SYSTEM. IN A FEDERATION, THE DISTRICTS MAY HAVE THE AUTONOMY TO CHOOSE POLICIES AND COLLECT TAXES. IN BRAZIL, STATES HAVE BEEN COMPETING FOR FIRMS FOR THE PAST DECADES. THUS, THIS STUDY AIMS TO ANALYZE PUBLIC GOODS PROVISION FOR FIRMS AND INDIVIDUALS AND COMPARE THE PROVISION WHEN THE GOVERNMENT IS CENTRALIZED AND DECENTRALIZED. "@pt ;
