    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_FARMACÊUTICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8746> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "NEGLECTED TROPICAL DISEASES ARE A GROUP OF DISEASES CAUSED BY INFECTIOUS AND PARASITIC AGENTS SUCH AS VIRUSES, BACTERIA, PROTOZOA AND HELMINTHS THAT AFFECT MAINLY A POOR POPULATION OF THE WORLD AND LIVE WITHOUT BASIC SANITATION, THESE DISEASES ARE GROUPED IN THE COUNTRIES OF THE TROPICAL AND SUBTROPICAL REGIONS OF THE GLOBE. SCHISTOSOMIASIS IS RECOGNIZED BY THE WHO AS A SERIOUS PUBLIC HEALTH PROBLEM BECAUSE OF ITS POTENTIAL FOR MORBIDITY. THE CONTROL OF THIS PARASITE IS A CHALLENGE FOR THE ENDEM"@pt ;
