    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIÊNCIAS_FARMACÊUTICAS> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8749> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "ORAL MUCOSITIS IS THE MOST COMMON AND DISTRESSING PATHOLOGY THAT DEVELOPS AS AN ACUTE ADVERSE EFFECT OF CHEMOTHERAPY AND RADIATION THERAPY OF THE HEAD AND NECK AND IS AMONG THE MAIN CAUSES OF INTERRUPTIONS OR DOSE REDUCTIONS IN CANCER THERAPY, THEREBY EXPOSING THE PATIENT TO PROGRESSION OF THE DISEASE. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS RESEARCH WAS TO INVESTIGATE THE ACTION OF BORNEOL IN ORAL MUCOSITES INDUCED BY 5-FLUOROURACIL (5-FU) IN AN EXPERIMENTAL MODEL OF WISTAR RATS AND TO PREPARE BUCCAL GELS BASED "@pt ;
