<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8752> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN GENERAL, THE ACCESS TO MEDICINAL PLANTS IS FACILITATED BY THE POSSIBILITY OF OWN CULTIVATION OR BY THE WIDE COMMERCIALIZATION IN MARKETS AND FREE MARKETS. THEREFORE, THE INCREASING USE OF PLANT PRODUCTS HAS BEEN A MATTER OF CONCERN TO THE HEALTH AUTHORITIES AS REGARDS THEIR RATIONAL USE AND QUALITY SPECIFICATIONS. AS TO THE PHARMACEUTICAL QUALITY OF THESE PRODUCTS, CHROMATOGRAPHIC METHODS HAVE BEEN WIDELY USED FOR THE QUALITATIVE AND QUANTITATIVE EVALUATIONS OF THESE COMPLEX MATRICES AND THEI"@pt ;
