<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8877> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THE COSTS RELATED TO THE TRANSPORTATION OF ORE IS ONE OF THE MINING STEPS THAT MOST INFLATES THE PROCESS AND DIRECTLY IMPACTS THE DISCOUNTED CASH FLOW. THE REALLOCATION OF THE ROADS AND THEIR AVERAGE TRANSPORT DISTANCES DURING THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE MINE ARE FUNDAMENTAL TO PROMOTE SHORTER OPERATING CYCLE TIMES AND LOWER COSTS, BUT DUE TO THEIR VARIABILITY, IT IS NECESSARY TO TREAT THE ISSUE AS STOCHASTIC TO GUAR ANTEE GREATER SUCCESSES IN THE DECISIONS, THAT IS, TO INCORPORATE THE PROBABILITIES "@pt ;
