        <http://example.com/capes#program/PSICOLOGIA_DA_SAÚDE> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8899> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "IN THE CONTEMPORARY WORLD, MOBILE DEVICES INCREASINGLY FEED THE EXCESS AND SPEED OF INFORMATION ON SOCIAL NETWORKS, THEY ALSO HELP TO STIMULATE EVEN MORE THE HABIT OF THE HUMAN BEING TO \"SHOW UP\", SINCE HE LIVES IMMERSED IN THESE NETWORKS. ALONG WITH THAT, COEXIST THE BRANDS THAT PROPAGATE IDEALS OF THE \"PERFECT\" LIFE WITH HEDONIC CHARACTERISTICS, SUCH AS HAPPINESS, STATUS, BEAUTY, SELF-ESTEEM, CONFIDENCE, YOUTH, ETC., DUE TO THE ESTABLISHED RELATIONS ALSO ON NETWORKS. THE PRESENT STUDY HAS STUD"@pt,
        "INTRODUCTION: BIRTH WEIGHT IS A SIGNIFICANT INDICATOR OF THE QUALITY OF LIFE OF CHILDREN AND THEIR MOTHERS. VERY LOW WEIGHT IS CONSIDERED RELEVANT ABOUT INFANT MORTALITY RATE AND MATERNAL STRESS AND IS CONSIDERED BY THE WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION AS THE SINGLE MOST IMPORTANT FACTOR. NEWBORNS WEIGHING 1,500G OR LESS AT BIRTH ARE REFERRED TO AS MBP BY THE CENTERS FOR DISEASE CONTROL WHILE WHO CONSIDERS VERY LOW BIRTH WEIGHT FROM 1,499G OR LESS. THE EXPERIENCE OF HOSPITALIZING A BABY IN A NEONATAL I"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "13DEC2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "31AUG2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ASPECTOS EMOCIONAIS DAS MÃES DE RECÉM-NASCIDOS PRÉ- TERMO DE MUITO BAIXO PESO EM UMA UNIDADE DE TERAPIA INTENSIVA NEONATAL: UM ESTUDO QUALITATIVO"@pt,
        "FACEBOOK COMO PLATAFORMA DE EMBLEMAS DE CONSUMO DE INTERCAMBISTAS DE GRADUAÇÃO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear,
        "2019"^^xsd:gYear ;
