<http://example.com/capes#thesis/8907> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "SCENARIO: IN THE PROCESS OF BECOMING ILL, THE CAREGIVER EXPERIENCES VARIOUS FEELINGS THAT MAY INTERFERE IN THE QUALITY OF PATIENT CARE. THE CARER'S IMPORTANCE HAS MOTIVATED NEW CARE PARADIGMS, ESPECIALLY DURING HOSPITALIZATION. IT IS NECESSARY TO KNOW THE EMOTIONAL REALITY OF THE CAREGIVER SO THAT CARE CAN EXIST MORE EFFECTIVELY. OBJECTIVE: TO INVESTIGATE THE UNDERSTANDING OF FAMILY CAREGIVERS' EXPERIENCES REGARDING INFANT HOSPITALIZATION. METHOD: QUALITATIVE, TRANSVERSAL AND EXPLANATORY RESEARC"@pt,
        "THIS RESEARCH HAS AN INTERDISCIPLINARY CHARACTER, BEING BASED MAINLY IN THE AREAS OF DESIGN, FASHION, SOCIAL SCIENCES AND ANTHROPOLOGY, IN ORDER TO AMPLIFY THE UNDERSTANDING OF THE SIGNIFICANT PROCESS OF CONSUMPTION OF CLOTHING-FASHION. THE OBJECTIVE OF THIS STUDY WAS TO UNDERSTAND HOW FASHION-CLOTHING CONSUMPTION IS ASSOCIATED WITH EMOTIONAL EXPERIENCES, INCLUDING EMOTIONS FROM THE LENSES OF ANTHROPOLOGY OF EMOTIONS (KOURY, 2006). WE USE THE CATEGORIES OF FAVORITE AND LEAN CLOTHING (ROCHA, 2009"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "10FEB2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date,
        "12FEB2019:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "ROUPA PREDILETA X ROUPA ENCOSTADA: INVESTIGAÇÃO SOBRE EMOÇÕES E O CICLO DE VIDA DAS ROUPAS NA CULTURA CONSUMISTA"@pt,
