<http://example.com/capes#thesis/9193> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "CIRRHOSISIS A CHRONIC AND PROGRESSIVE DISEASE, BEING RESPONSABLE FOR A HIGH MORTALITY RATE IN THE WORLD. OF COMPLEX PATHOLOGICAL CONDITION, AT NA ADVANCED STAGE, SEVERAL ORGANS ARE DAMAGED AND THE PICTURE BECOMES IRREVERSIBLE, REASON WHY DIVERSE STUDIES SEARCH NEW THERAPEUTIC OPTIONS FOR THIS DISEASE. FOR MEATONIN TO BE MENTIONED IN THELITERATURE AS A POTENT ANTIOXIDANT AGENT CAPABLE OF REGULATING SEVERAL PHYSIOLOGICAL PROCESSES IN MAMMALS, WE AIMED TO EVALUATE THE EFFECT OF THIS HORMONE IN THE "@pt ;
