    capes:hasAbstract "EXTREMOPHILIC MICROORGANISMS OFFERS AN EXCELLENT OPPORTUNITY IN THE FIELD OF ENZYMOLOGY AND BIOPROCESSES FOR THEIR CAPABILITY IN PRODUCING EXTREMOZYMES. PRIORITY FOR BIOTECHNOLOGY, THESE PROTEINS USUALLY PRESENT PECULIARITIES THAT FIT THE UNFAVORABLE CIRCUMSTANCES FOUND IN THE INDUSTRIAL PROCESSES. ITS TAILORED MACHINERY CAN PRODUCE NUMEROUS BIOCATALYSTS, INCLUDING PROTEASES. ARE ENZYMES THAT CLEAVE PEPTIDE BONDS OF PROTEINS, GENERATING PEPTIDES AND AMINO ACIDS, WITH APPLICATIONS AIMED AT SEVERA"@pt ;
