<http://example.com/capes#thesis/9210> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "PROGESTERONE (P4) AND 17¿-ESTRADIOL (E2) ARE STEROID HORMONES INDUSTRIALLY PRODUCED AS DRUGS FOR HORMONE REPLACEMENT THERAPY AND CONTRACEPTIVE METHODS. DUE TO THE CHEMICAL CHARACTERISTICS OF STEROID HORMONES SUCH AS HYDROPHOBICITY, SUBSTANCES ARE USED TO INCREASE AQUEOUS SOLUBILITY AS THE INCLUSION COMPLEXES BETWEEN HORMONES AND CYCLODEXTRINS (CDS). FREE HORMONES OR COMPLEXED INTO CYCLODEXTRIN CAN BE CLASSIFIED AS ENDOCRINE DISRUPTORS (ED), BEING SUBSTANCES CAPABLE OF MODIFYING THE ENDOCRINE FUN"@pt ;
