<http://example.com/capes#thesis/9910> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INCOME INEQUALITY IS AN OLD SOCIAL PROBLEM IN BRAZIL AND IN THE WORLD. IN BRAZIL, SEVERAL PUBLIC POLICIES WERE DESIGNED TO ALLEVIATE THIS PROBLEM. CONDITIONAL CASH TRANSFER PROGRAMS HAVE BEEN IMPLEMENTED SINCE THE 1990S IN BRAZIL WITH THE AIM OF BRINGING SOCIAL WELFARE TO THE UNDERPRIVILEGED. IN 2003, THE BOLSA FAMÍLIA PROGRAM WAS CREATED, WHICH UNIFIED THE VARIOUS EXISTING PROGRAMS AND IMPOSED CONDITIONALITIES ON BENEFICIARIES IN THE FIELD OF HEALTH AND EDUCATION TO RECEIVE INCOME TRANSFERS. TH"@pt ;
