<http://example.com/capes#thesis/9913> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "THIS PAPER DISCUSSES THE RELATIONSHIP AND CONSEQUENCES OF USING THE PROVISION OF PUBLIC SERVICES WITH AN ELECTORAL BIAS. IT ANALYZES HOW GOVERNORS, APPOINTED DURING THEIR INCUMBENCY, SUBJECT TO ELECTORAL PROCESSES AND SEEKING TO OPTIMIZE THEIR CHANCES OF REELECTION OR OF FORMING A SUCCESSOR, DECIDE HOW MUCH AND TO WHICH SECTORS OF SOCIETY PUBLIC SERVICES WILL BE OFFERED. FROM THE HYPOTHESIS CONSIDERED AND THE CONSTRUCTION OF THE MODEL, THERE IS THE POSSIBILITY THAT POSSIBLE REGIONAL ASYMMETRIES "@pt ;
