    capes:hasAbstract "BACKGROUND: THE LAPAROSCOPIC ROUX-EN-Y GASTRIC BYPASS (RYGB) HAS BEEN CONSIDERED A GOLD-STANDARD PROCEDURE IN THE SURGICAL TREATMENT OF MORBID OBESITY. THE LINEAR STAPLED GASTROJEJUNOSTOMY (GJ) TECHNIQUE HAS PROVED TO BE SAFE AND EFFECTIVE IN LONG-TERM SERIES OF PATIENTS, BUT ITS OPTIMAL SIZE REFERRED TO ACHIEVE BEST POST-OPERATIVE WEIGHT LOSS REMAINS POORLY UNDERSTOOD. AIM: EVALUATE THE ROLE OF THE LINEAR-STAPLED GJ SIZE IN THE MID-TERM POST- RYGB WEIGHT LOSS AND OCCURRENCE OF COMPLICATIONS. ME"@pt ;
