    capes:hasAbstract "BACKGROUND: CHIKUNGUNYA FEVER IS AN EMERGING ARBOVIRUS DISEASE CAUSED BY CHIKUNGUNYA VIRUS (CHIKV) CHARACTERIZED BY ACUTE FEVER, HEADACHE, MYALGIA AND POLYARTHRALGIA. DURING THE OUTBREAK OF THIS DISEASE IN PERNAMBUCO, IN 2016, THE PRESENCE OF LOWER LIMBS (LL) LYMPHEDEMA WAS DIAGNOSED IN SEVERAL PATIENTS. HOWEVER, UNTIL NOW, THERE IS NO LITERATUREAVAILABLE ON LYMPHATIC VESSEL INJURY SECONDARY TO CHIKUNGUNYA FEVER. OBJECTIVE:CLINICALLY CHARACTERIZE THE LYMPHATIC EDEMA AND EVALUATE, THROUGH LYMPHOS"@pt ;
