    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/998> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: GENETIC, EPIGENETIC AND ENVIRONMENTAL INFLUENCES HAVE BEEN CITED AS THE REASONS FOR THE OBESITY WHICH AFFECTS 1 IN 4 AMERICAN ADULTS. MANY DISEASES ARE ASSOCIATED WITH OBESITY, AMONG THEM THE NON-ALCOHOLIC FATTY LIVER DISEASE (NAFLD) AND THE MORE ADVANCED TYPE OF IT, NONALCOHOLIC STEATOHEPATITIS (NASH). PATIENTS WITH NASH DEVELOP FIBROSIS VERY SIMILAR TO ALCOHOLIC AND VIRAL HEPATITIS. NASH IS ASSOCIATED WITH AN INFLAMMATION, IN ADDITION TO CARDIOVASCULAR MORTALITY, NON-HEPATIC CANC"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "02MAR2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "DOENÇA HEPÁTICA GORDUROSA NÃO-ALCOÓLICA: ANÁLISE DA EXPRESSÃO HEPÁTICA DA ADIPONECTINA, TNF-¿, INTERLEUCINA-6 E FRAGMENTO CK-18 COMO MARCADORES DE FIBROSE HEPÁTICA EM PACIENTES OBESOS SUBMETIDOS À CIRURGIA BARIÁTRICA"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/LUCIA_HELENA_DE_OLIVEIRA_CORDEIRO> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

<http://example.com/capes#thesis/999> a capes:Thesis ;
    capes:hasAbstract "INTRODUCTION: OBESITY IS A CHRONIC METABOLIC DISEASE THAT INDIRECTLY INFLUENCES CORONARY RISK THROUGH ITS EFFECT ON RELATED COMORBIDITIES, SUCH AS DYSLIPIDEMIA, ARTERIAL HYPERTENSION, TYPE 2 DIABETES MELLITUS, ENDOTHELIAL DYSFUNCTION AND CHRONIC SUBCLINICAL INFLAMMATION. BARIATRIC SURGERY, KNOWN AS ONE OF THE MOST EFFECTIVE METHODS TO LOSE WEIGHT, HAS SHOWN TO BE BENEFICIAL IN DECREASING CARDIOVASCULAR RISK FACTORS AND PREVENTING CVD EVENTS.THE CORONARY ARTERY CALCIUM SCORE IS AN IMPORTANT PREDI"@pt ;
    capes:hasDefenseDate "20DEC2017:00:00:00"^^xsd:date ;
    capes:hasTitle "EFEITOS DA CIRURGIA BARIÁTRICA NO ESCORE DE CÁLCIO"@pt ;
    capes:hasYear "2017"^^xsd:gYear ;
    capes:isAuthoredBy <http://example.com/capes#author/DANIEL_DA_COSTA_LINS> ;
    capes:isFromProgram <http://example.com/capes#program/CIRURGIA> .

